f China]] has received {{convert|1158|km2|sqmi}} from [[Tajikistan]] after a final ratification of a treaty ceding it<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's area increases by 1000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-12/china/28364278_1_tajik-government-tajikistan-protocol|date=12 January 2011|newspaper=[[Times of India]]|agency=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]]|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615083147/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-12/china/28364278_1_tajik-government-tajikistan-protocol|archive-date=15 June 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|2010||align=center|21&nbsp;October||The [[Union of Myanmar]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of the Union of Myanmar]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;October||The [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] [[Dissolution of the Netherlands Antilles|dissolves]] the [[Netherlands Antilles]] and makes '''[[Cura\u00e7ao]]''' and '''[[Sint Maarten]]''' two of its four constituent countries. [[Bonaire]], [[Saba]], and [[Sint Eustatius]] become [[BES islands|special municipalities]] of the [[Netherlands]].\n|}\n\n<!--*8 April 2013 \u2014 The [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] declares independence from [[Iraq]] and [[Syria]]-->\n\n====2000s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|2009||align=center|1&nbsp;September||The [[United Kingdom]] changes the name of the [[British Overseas Territory]] of [[Saint Helena and Dependencies]] to '''[[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]]'''. [[Jamestown, Saint Helena|Jamestown]] on [[Saint Helena]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;February||The [[Republic of Bolivia]] changes its name to the '''[[Plurinational State of Bolivia]]'''. [[La Paz]] and [[Sucre]] remain the capitals.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|2008||align=center|27&nbsp;August||The [[Russian Federation]] recognizes the independence of the '''[[Republic of South Ossetia]]''' and the '''[[Republic of Abkhazia]]''' from [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. Georgia and much of the [[international community]] maintain that they are both were [[Occupied territories of Georgia|illegally occupied by Russia]] during [[Russo-Georgian War]] and legally remain integral regions of Georgia. Their capitals are [[Tskhinval]] and [[Sukhumi]], respectively. \n|-\n|align=center|28 May||The [[State of Nepal]] changes its name to the '''[[Federal Democratic Republic of Nepal]]'''. [[Kathmandu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;February||The [[Autonomous Province of Kosovo and Metohija]] declares its independence from the [[Republic of Serbia]] as the '''[[Republic of Kosovo]]'''. [[Pri\u0161tina]] remains the capital. Serbia maintains that Kosovo remains a part of Serbia.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|2007||align=center|22&nbsp;October||The [[Republic of Montenegro]] changes its name to '''[[Montenegro]]'''. [[Podgorica]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;February||The [[French Republic]] separates the '''[[Overseas Collectivity of Saint-Barth\u00e9lemy]]''' and the '''[[Overseas Collectivity of Saint-Martin]]''' from the [[Overseas Region of Guadeloupe]]. [[Gustavia, Saint Barth\u00e9lemy|Gustavia]] and [[Marigot, Saint Martin|Marigot]] are the capitals respectively.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[Kingdom of Nepal]] changes its name to the '''[[State of Nepal]]'''. [[Kathmandu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|2006||align=center|7&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Palau]]''' moves its capital from [[Koror]] to [[Ngerulmud]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;August||The [[Federal Republic of Nigeria]] transfers sovereignty of [[Bakassi]] to the '''[[Republic of Cameroon]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;June||The '''[[Republic of Serbia]]''' supersedes the [[State Union of Serbia and Montenegro]]. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;June||[[Montenegro]] secedes from the [[State Union of Serbia and Montenegro]] as the '''[[Republic of Montenegro]]'''. [[Podgorica]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2005||align=center|6&nbsp;November||The '''[[Union of Myanmar]]''' moves its capital from [[Yangon]] to [[Naypyidaw]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|2004||align=center|1&nbsp;September||The [[Secretariat of the Antarctic Treaty]] administering '''[[Antarctica]]''' and all lands and waters south of the [[60th parallel south]] establishes its headquarters in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;February||The [[French Republic]] elevates the [[Overseas Collectivity of French Polynesia]] to the '''[[Overseas Country of French Polynesia]]'''. [[Papeet\u0113]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||The [[Islamic State of Afghanistan]] changes its name to the '''[[Islamic Republic of Afghanistan]]'''. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|2003||align=center|26 May||The [[Rwandese Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Rwanda]]'''. [[Kigali]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|28&nbsp;March||The '''[[French Republic]]''' revises its [[Constitution of France|constitution]]. New [[polity|polities]] include:\n|-\n|\n*The [[Overseas Region of R\u00e9union]]. [[Saint-Denis, R\u00e9union|Saint-Denis]] remains the capital.\n*The [[Overseas Territory of French Southern and Antarctic Lands]]. [[Port-aux-Fran\u00e7ais]] remains the administrative center.\n|-\n|\n*The [[Overseas Collectivity of French Polynesia]]. [[Papeet\u0113]] remains the capital.\n*The [[Overseas Collectivity of Wallis and Futuna]]. [[Mata-Utu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|\n*The [[Overseas Region of Guadeloupe]]. [[Basse-Terre]] remains the capital.\n*The [[Overseas Region of Martinique]]. [[Fort-de-France]] remains the capital.\n*The [[Overseas Collectivity of Saint-Pierre and Miquelon]]. [[Saint-Pierre, Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint-Pierre]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|\n*The [[Overseas Region of Guyane]] ([[French Guiana]]). [[Cayenne]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;February||The [[Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]] changes its name to the '''[[State Union of Serbia and Montenegro]]'''. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|2002||align=center|21 May||The [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland]] changes the title of each of its [[British Dependent Territories]] to that of a [[British Overseas Territory]]. The citizens of each British Overseas Territory gain full [[British citizenship]].\n|-\n|align=center|20 May||[[East Timor]] gains independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste]]'''. East Timor was occupied by [[Indonesia]] in 1975, and was placed under [[United Nations]] administration in 1999. [[Dili]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;March||The '''[[Union of the Comoros]]''' reabsorbs the ''[[de facto]]'' independent [[State of Anjouan]] and the [[Democratic Republic of Moh\u00e9li]]. [[Mutsamudu]] and [[Fomboni]] yield to [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;February||The [[State of Bahrain]] changes its name to the '''[[Kingdom of Bahrain]]'''. [[Manama]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|2001||align=center|23&nbsp;December||The [[Federal Islamic Republic of the Comoros]] changes its name to the '''[[Union of the Comoros]]'''. [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;November||The '''[[Islamic State of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The \"temporarily independent\" [[Puntland State of Somalia]] adopts a new constitution explicitly identifying itself as part of the '''[[Somali Republic]]'''. [[Garowe]] yields to [[Mogadishu]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|January||[[Taloqan]], the ''[[de facto]]'' capital of the [[Islamic State of Afghanistan]] government, falls to the '''[[Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan]]'''. The capital moves to [[Fayzabad, Badakhshan|Fayzabad]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|2000||align=center|16&nbsp;July||[[Somalia]] changes its name to the '''[[Somali Republic]]'''. [[Mogadishu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;June||Colombia returns its capital city's name from Santa Fe de Bogot\u00e1 to [[Bogot\u00e1, Distrito Capital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/MAM-1285140|language=Spanish|access-date=23 November 2019|date=11 June 2000|title=LE SUENA BOGOT\u00c1 SIN SANTA FE|last=Marcela|first=Ruby}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;February||The [[Chechen Republic of Ichkeria]] capitulates and is reabsorbed by the '''[[Russian Federation]]'''. [[Grozny|\u01b5ovxar-\u0120ala]] (Grozny) yields to [[Moscow]] as the capital.\n|}\n\n===20th century===\n====1990s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1999||align=center|31&nbsp;December||The [[United States of America]] transfers full ownership of the [[Panama Canal Zone]] to the '''[[Republic of Panama]]'''.\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|20&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of Venezuela]] changes its name to the '''[[Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela]]'''. [[Caracas]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Portuguese Republic]] transfers sovereignty of [[Macau]] to the '''[[People's Republic of China]]''' as the [[Macau Special Administrative Region]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;June||The '''[[United Nations Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo]]''' i