arch||[[Guyana]] is renamed the [[Co-operative Republic of Guyana]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[Republic of Biafra]] capitulates and is reabsorbed by the [[Nigeria#Military juntas|military junta]] controlled '''[[Federal Republic of Nigeria]]'''. [[Enugu]] falls to [[Lagos]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||The [[Republic of the Congo]] is renamed the [[People's Republic of the Congo]].\n|}\n\n====1960s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"6\"|1969||align=center|18&nbsp;December||The [[Saudi\u2013Kuwaiti neutral zone]] is divided and the border between [[Saudi Arabia]] and [[Kuwait]] is defined.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;October||The '''[[Somali Democratic Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Somali Republic]]. [[Mogadishu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;September||Following a coup d'\u00e9tat led by [[Muammar Gaddafi]], the [[Kingdom of Libya]] becomes the '''[[Libyan Arab Republic]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;May||The '''[[Democratic Republic of the Sudan]]''' supersedes the [[History of Sudan (1956\u201369)|Republic of the Sudan]]. [[Khartoum]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;March||The [[Republic of Anguilla]] is taken back by the [[United Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||[[Ifni]] is ceded to [[Morocco]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1968||align=center|11&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Maldives]]''' supersedes the [[Sultanate of Maldives]]. [[Male, Maldives|Male]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||[[Spanish Guinea]] gains independence from the [[History of Spain|Spanish State]] as the '''[[Republic of Equatorial Guinea]]'''. [[Malabo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;September||The '''[[Kingdom of Swaziland]]''' gains full independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Mbabane]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&n