] ([[Congo-L\u00e9opoldville]]) changes its name to the '''[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]'''. [[L\u00e9opoldville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;July||'''[[Malawi]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Lilongwe]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;April||The [[Republic of Tanganyika]] and the [[Republic of Zanzibar and Pemba]] unite to form the '''[[United Republic of Tanganyika and Zanzibar]]'''. [[Zanzibar City]] yields to [[Dar-es-Salaam]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;March||The '''[[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus]]''' is established in the [[Republic of Cyprus]] between [[Greek Cypriot]] and [[Turkish Cypriot]] communities.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"15\"|1963||align=center|31&nbsp;December||The [[Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland]] is divided into [[Northern Rhodesia]], [[Southern Rhodesia]], and [[Nyasaland]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;December||The [[Francoist Spain|Spanish]] colonies of [[Fernando Po (island)|Fernando P\u00f3]] and [[R\u00edo Muni]] merge to form [[Spanish Guinea]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Kenya]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Nairobi]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;December||Independence of the [[Sultanate of Zanzibar]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||The [[Federation of Nigeria]] is renamed the [[Federal Republic of Nigeria]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;September||The '''[[United Suvadive Republic]]''' is reunited with the [[Sultanate of Maldives]]. [[Hithadhoo (Addu)|Hithadhoo]] yields to [[Male, Maldives|Male]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;September||The [[Federation of Malaya]] unites with the [[United Kingdom|British]] colonies of [[Singapore]], [[Sarawak]], and [[British North Borneo]] ([[Sabah]]) to form '''[[Malaysia]]'''. [[Kuala Lumpur]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;August||The [[Republic of Singapore]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||The [[Rwenzururu|Kingdom of Rwenzururu]] declares independence from [[Uganda]] with no recognition.\n|-\n|align=center|1 May||The [[United Nations Temporary Executive Authority]] in New Guinea is transferred to [[Indonesia]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;April||The '''[[Kingdom of Libya]]''' supersedes the [[United Kingdom of Libya]]. [[Tripoli]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;April||The [[Federal People's Republic of Yugoslavia]] changes its name to the '''[[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]'''. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;March||The disputed area of the [[Trans-Karakoram Tract]] is given to [[China]] by [[Pakistan]], although [[India]] still claims it.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||[[State of Katanga|Katanga]] is taken back by [[Republic of the Congo (L\u00e9opoldville)|Congo (L\u00e9opoldville)]].\n|-\n|||The '''[[Republic of Zanzibar and Pemba]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Zanzibar City]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"16\"|1962||align=center|9&nbsp;December||[[Tanganyika]] is renamed the [[Republic of Tanganyika]].\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;November||The disputed area of the [[Aksai Chin]] is given to [[China]] by [[Pakistan]], although [[India]] still claims it.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;November||[[Eritrea]] becomes a province of the [[Ethiopian Empire]], losing the autonomy it had under federation.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Uganda]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kampala]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1 October||[[Netherlands New Guinea]] is transferred to the [[United Nations Temporary Executive Authority]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;September||[[Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen]] ([[North Yemen]]) is overthrown by the '''[[Yemen Arab Republic]]'''. [[San'a]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;September||The capital of the [[Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen]] is moved from [[Ta'izz]] to [[Sana'a]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;September||[[Algeria]] becomes the '''[[People's Democratic Algerian Republic]]'''. [[Algiers]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Trinidad and Tobago]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Port of Spain]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|6&nbsp;August||The [[United Kingdom]] creates the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[Cayman Islands]]'''. [[George Town, Cayman Islands|George Town]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Jamaica]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;July||The [[Overseas department|French overseas department]] of '''[[Algeria]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Algiers]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The '''[[Kingdom of Burundi]]''' and the '''[[Republic of Rwanda]]''' gain independence from the [[Kingdom of Belgium]]. [[Bujumbura]] and [[Kigali]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|31 May||The '''[[West Indies Federation]]''' is dissolved and member states return to their status as parts of the [[British West Indies]]. [[Chaguaramas, Trinidad|Chaguaramas]] yields to [[London]] as the capital. Changes include the following:\n*The [[Cayman Islands]] are split from [[Jamaica]].\n*[[Barbados]], [[Jamaica]], [[Saint Christopher-Nevis-Anguilla]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]], and the [[Turks and Caicos Islands]] become their own separate British colonies.\n*The [[British Leeward Islands]] are further dissolved into the British colonies of [[Antigua and Barbuda]], [[Montserrat]], and [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]].\n*The [[British Windward Islands]] are further dissolved into the British colonies of [[Dominica]], [[Grenada]], and [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;March||The United Kingdom officially gives the territory claimed in [[Antarctica]] an entity, the [[British Antarctic Territory]], although this is suspended under the [[Antarctic Treaty]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Independent State of Western Samoa]]''' gains independence from [[New Zealand]]. [[Apia, Samoa|Apia]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"15\"|1961||align=center|28&nbsp;December||The '''[[Syrian Arab Republic]]''' secedes from the '''[[United Arab Republic]]''', leaving [[Egypt]] as the sole member of the federation. [[Cairo]] remains the capital of the UAR. [[Damascus]] is again the capital of [[Syria]].\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of India]] [[Annexation of Goa|annexes]] '''[[Goa, Daman and Diu]]''' from [[Portuguese India]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Tanganyika]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Dar-es-Salaam]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;December||The [[Netherlands New Guinea]] is renamed '''[[Netherlands New Guinea|West Papua]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||The southern portion of the [[British Cameroons]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] and unites with the [[Republic of Cameroun]] to form the '''[[Federal Republic of Cameroon]]'''. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital. \n|-\n|align=center rowspan=4|28&nbsp;September||In the [[United Arab States]], [[Syria]] leaves the [[United Arab Republic]] and returns to the name of the [[Syrian Arab Republic]].\n|-\n|The [[Dadra and Nagar Haveli|Free Dadra and Nagar Haveli]] joins India, as [[Portugal]] ceases to claim it.\n|-\n|Portugal cedes [[S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o Baptista de Ajud\u00e1]] to [[Republic of Dahomey|Dahomey]].\n|-\n|Portuguese fort [[S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o Baptista de Ajud\u00e1]] (now Ouidah) is annexed by [[Republic of Dahomey|Dahomey]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;June||The [[Antarctic Treaty System]] enters force to administer the continent of '''[[Antarctica]]''' and all lands and waters south of the [[60th parallel south]].\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;June||The '''[[State of Kuwait]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kuwait City]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|31 May||The [[Union of South Africa]] ceases to be a [[Commonwealth realm]] and changes its name to the '''[[Republic of South Africa]]'''. [[Pretoria]], [[Cape Town]] and [[Bloemfontein]] remain the capitals.\n|-\n|Northern [[British Cameroon]] joins [[Nigeria]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of Sierra Leone]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Freetown]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;January||[[India]] annexes [[Portuguese India]], and Portugal maintains its claims to it.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"24\"|1960||align=center|28&nbsp;November||The '''[[Islamic Republic of Mauritania]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Nouakchott]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1 October||The '''[[Federation of Nigeria]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Lagos]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Mali]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Bamako]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Senegal]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Dakar]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;August||The '''[[Gabonese Republic]]''' ([[Gabon]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Libreville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Cyprus]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Lefkosia]] (Nicosia) remains the capital. The United Kingdom retains control of [[Akrotiri and Dhekelia]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of the Congo]]''' ([[Congo-Brazzaville]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Brazzaville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;August||The '''[[Central African Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Bangui]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Chad]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[N'Djamena]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;August||The '''[[Ivory Coast|C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Abidjan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Upper Volta]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Ouagadougou]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Niger]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Niamey]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Dahomey]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Porto-Novo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The capital of [[Pakistan]] is moved from [[Karachi]] to [[Rawalpindi]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|11&nbsp;July||The [[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic|Czechoslovak Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic]]'''. [[Prague]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The [[State of Katanga]] declares independence from the [[Republic of the Congo (L\u00e9opoldville)]] with no recognition.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The '''[[Somali Republic]]''' ([[Somalia]]) is created from a merger of the former colonies of [[British Somaliland]] and [[Italian Somaliland]]. [[Mogadishu]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||The [[Belgian Congo]] gains independence from the [[Kingdom of Belgium]] as the '''[[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Republic of the Congo]]''' ([[Congo-L\u00e9opoldville]]). [[L\u00e9opoldville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;June||The '''[[Malagasy Republic]]''' ([[Madagascar]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Antananarivo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;June||Independence of [[French Sudan]] from France with [[Senegal]] as the [[Mali Federation]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;April||The '''[[Togolese Republic]]''' ([[Togo]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Lom\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' moves its capital from [[Rio de Janeiro]] to [[Bras\u00edlia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of Cameroun]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| ||The [[British Virgin Islands]] become a separate colony from the [[West Indies Federation]].\n|}\n\n====1950s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=4|1959||align=center|4&nbsp;July||In the [[West Indies Federation]], the '''[[Turks and Caicos Islands]]''' become a separate colony from '''Jamaica'''.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||[[Bioko|Fernando P\u00f3]] and [[R\u00edo Muni]] are merged to form '''[[Spanish Guinea]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;April||In [[French Africa]], the colonies of [[Senegal]] and [[French Sudan|Soudan]] merge to form the '''[[Mali Federation]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||The '''[[United Suvadive Republic]]''' secedes from the [[Sultanate of Maldives]]. [[Hithadhoo (Addu)|Hithadhoo]] is the capital.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"18\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |1958||align=center|19&nbsp;December||The French Colony of '''[[Niger]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;December||The French Colony of '''[[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||Sovereignty over [[Gwadar]] is transferred from the [[Sultanate of Muscat and Oman]] 