ation of Vietnam]].\n|-\n|||[[Gi\u1ea3n \u0110\u1ecbnh \u0110\u1ebf|Gi\u1ea3n \u0110\u1ecbnh]] establishes the '''[[Later Tr\u1ea7n dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1400||||[[H\u1ed3 Qu\u00fd Ly]] establishes the '''[[H\u1ed3 dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Citadel of the H\u1ed3 Dynasty|T\u00e2y \u0110\u00f4]] is the capital.\n|}\n\n===14th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1392||||The '''[[Joseon Dynasty]]''' succeed the [[Goryeo Dynasty]] of [[Korea]]. [[Seoul|Hanseong]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1384||||The [[Burgundian Netherlands]] are established.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1368||||[[Hongwu Emperor|Hongwu]] establishes the '''[[Ming dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Nanjing|Yingtian]] and [[Beijing|Shuntian]] are the capitals.\n|-\n|||[[Toghon Tem\u00fcr|Huizong]] establishes the '''[[Northern Yuan dynasty]]''' in what is now Northern China and Mongolia.\n|-\n|align=center|1366||||[[Li\u00e8ge]] annexes the [[County of Loon]]\n|-\n|align=center|1358||||[[Rudolf IV, Duke of Austria|Duke Rudolf IV of Austria]] has the [[Privilegium Maius]] forged, a set of documents which purports to elevate the [[Duchy of Austria]] to the status of \"Archduchy\". This status remains unrecognised.\n|-\n|align=center|1350||||With the foundation of the '''[[Ayutthaya Kingdom]]''', its capital is created in '''[[Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya (city)|Ayutthaya]]''', instead of the former [[Sukhothai (city)|Sukhothai]].\n|-\n|align=center|1349||||[[Dauphin\u00e9]] sold to France\n|-\n|align=center|1347||align=center|7&nbsp;June||The [[Teutonic Order]] leases the former [[Danish Estonia]] to its autonomous [[Livonian Order]].\n|-\n|align=center|1346||align=center|1&nbsp;November||[[Denmark]] sells and hands the [[Danish Estonia|Duchy of Estonia]] over to the [[Teutonic Order]]\n|-\n|align=center|1341||||King [[Magnus IV of Sweden|Magnus Eriksson]] of [[Sweden]] buys the county of Halland from Denmark.\n|-\n|align=center|1330||align=center|March||The autonomous [[Livonian Order]] of the [[Teutonic Order]] gains control over the nominally [[Independent city|free town]] of [[Riga]].\n|-\n|align=center|1326||||[[Aragonese conquest of Sardinia|The Crown of Aragon conquers Sardinia]], creating the [[Kingdom of Sardinia]]\n|-\n|align=center|1325||align=center|13&nbsp;March||The '''[[Mexicas]]''' ('''[[Aztecs]]''') founded '''[[Tenochtitlan]]''', the foundation of '''[[M\u00e9xico]]'''. It is the oldest continuous capital in the '''[[Americas]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1323||||[[Charles I of Hungary|King Charles I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1301\u20131526)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' to [[Visegr\u00e1d]].\n|-\n|align=center|1323||align=center| 12 August||The treaty of N\u00f6teborg is signed between Sweden and Novgorod, resulting in the first true border regulation in Swedish Finland.\n|-\n|align=center|1316||||France gains the Counties of [[Valentinois]] and [[Diois]]\n|-\n|align=center|1315||||[[Charles I of Hungary|King Charles I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1301\u20131526)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' to [[Temesv\u00e1r]].\n|-\n|align=center|1305||||France gains the County of [[Vivarais]]\n|-\n|align=center|1301||||France gains ''Barrois mouvant'' ([[County of Bar]] west of [[Meuse River]])\n|}\n\n===13th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1299||||[[Ottoman Empire]] founded\n|-\n|align=center|1293||align-center|10 March||[[Sweden]] conquers the southeastern parts of Finland.\n|-\n|align=center|1290||align:center|February||The [[Archbishopric of Riga]] and the [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]] conquer [[Semigallia]], the last independent [[Latvia]]n territory.\n|-\n|align=center|1287||||[[Parakramabahu III of Sri Lanka|King Parakramabahu III]] moves the capital of the '''[[Sri Lanka#Medieval Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' back to [[Polonnaruwa]].\n|-\n|align=center|1279||align=center|19&nbsp;March||The [[Song dynasty]] is conquered by the [[Yuan dynasty]] in [[China]].\n|-\n|align=center|1279|| ||The [[Kingdom of Majorca]] becomes a vassal of the Crown of Aragon\n|-\n|align=center|1278||align=center|8&nbsp;September||The [[Par\u00e9age of Andorra 1278|Par\u00e9age of Andorra]] is signed, establishing a [[condominium (international law)|condominium]]  between the [[Count of Foix]] and the [[Bishop of Urgell]] in the territory of '''[[Andorra]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1278|| ||[[Andorra]] granted independence from the [[Crown of Aragon]]\n|-\n|align=center|1276|| ||Kingdom of Majorca is split from the Crown of Aragon, which are inherited by different sons of James I of Aragon\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1272||||The [[Yuan dynasty]] of China moves its capital from [[Shangdu]] to [[Khanbaliq|Dadu]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||The [[Kingdom of Albania (medieval)]] established.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;August||[[Yekuno Amlak]] overthrows the [[Zagwe dynasty]], establishing the [[Solomonic dynasty]] of '''[[Ethiopia]]'''. [[Lalibela]] ceases to be the capital, and the Emperor of Ethiopia rules from a continually moving encampment around his domains for the following centuries.\n|-\n|align=center|1271||||[[Kublai Khan|Shizu]] establishes the '''[[Yuan dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1266||align=center|2&nbsp;July||Caithness and the territory of the [[Kingdom of the Isles]] (the [[Hebrides]] and [[Isle of Man|Mann]]) is ceded to the Kingdom of Scotland by the [[Treaty of Perth]]\n|-\n|align=center|1260||align=center|2&nbsp;July||[[Division of the Mongol Empire|Mongol Empire splits]]\n|-\n|align=center|1258||align=center|11&nbsp;May||The [[Treaty of Corbeil (1258)|Treaty of Corbeil]] formally ends French feudal overlordship of the counti