 Wei|Eastern Wei dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|508||||Frankish King [[Clovis the Frank]] makes [[Paris]] the capital of the '''[[Frankish Kingdom]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|502||||[[Emperor Wu of Liang|Wu]] establishes the '''[[Liang dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|}\n\n===5th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|493||align=center| ||[[Ostrogoths]] establish a [[Ostrogothic Kingdom|kingdom]] in Italy\n|-\n|align=center|490||align=center| ||Odoacer is defeated at the river [[Adda (river)|Adda]] by the Goths and flees\n|-\n|align=center|486||align=center| ||The [[Kingdom of Soissons]], a Roman rump state ruled by [[Syagrius]], is conquered by the [[Franks]]\n|-\n|align=center|480||align=center| ||A Roman rump state, [[Dalmatia (Roman province)|Roman Dalmatia]], is disestablished after [[Julius Nepos]] is murdered\n|-\n|align=center|479||||[[Emperor Gao of Southern Qi|Gao]] establishes the '''[[Southern Qi|Southern Qi dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Jiankang]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|476||align=center|4&nbsp;September||[[Germanic peoples|Germanic General]] [[Odoacer]] forces [[Roman Empire|Roman Emperor]] [[Romulus Augustus]] to abdicate, bringing the '''[[Western Roman Empire]]''' to an end.\n|-\n|align=center|475||||The '''[[Baekje]]''' of [[Korea]] moves its capital from [[Wiryeseong|Wirye]] to [[Ungjin]] by pressure of Goguryeo.\n|-\n|align=center|469||align=center| ||The [[Hunnic Empire]] is disestablished after [[Dengizich]] dies\n|-\n|align=center|457-461||align=center| ||Western Roman Emperor [[Majorian]] makes a concerted effort to try to restore the Empire, and reconquers most of Hispania and southern Gaul\n|-\n|align=center|451-453||align=center| ||[[Huns]] attack the Western Roman Empire\n|-\n|align=center|435||align=center| ||The Vandals establish a [[Vandal Kingdom|kingdom]] in North Africa\n|-\n|alig