olis]] (now [[Istanbul, Turkey]]), and [[Honorius (emperor)|Honorius]] ([[Flavius Honorius]]) rules the '''[[Western Roman Empire]]''' from [[Mediolanum]] (now [[Milan, Italy]]).\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|386||||[[L\u00fc Guang|Yiwu]] establishes '''[[Later Liang (Sixteen Kingdoms)|Later Liang]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. Guzang is the capital.\n|-\n|||[[Emperor Daowu of Northern Wei|Daowu]] establishes the '''[[Northern Wei|Northern Wei dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|385||||[[Qifu Guoren|Xuanlie]] establishes '''[[Western Qin]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|384||||[[Murong Chui|Chengwu]] establishes '''[[Later Yan]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[Yao Chang|Wuzhao]] establishes '''[[Later Qin]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Chang'an]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||[[Murong Hong|Liewen]] establishes '''[[Western Yan]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|370||align=center| ||The [[Bosporan Kingdom]] is disestablished\n|-\n|align=center|370||align=center| ||[[Huns]] appear north of the [[Black Sea]]\n|-\n|align=center|358||align=center| ||[[Franks]] allowed to settle in Toxandria (present-day Belgium)\n|-\n|align=center|351||||[[Fu Jian (317\u2013355)|Jingming]] establishes '''[[Former Qin]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|337||||[[Murong Huang|Wenming]] establishes '''[[Former Yan]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|330||align=center|11&nbsp;May||[[Roman Empire#305-363: Constantinian dynasty|Roman Emperor]] [[Constantine the Great]] builds a new capital for the '''[[Roman Empire#305-363: Constantinian dynasty|Roman Empire]]''' at [[Byzantium]] which he renames [[Constantinopolis]] (now [[Istanbul, Turkey]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ancienthistory.about.com/od/romehistory/tp/062410-Dominate-Imperial-Rome-Timeline-Part-II.htm|title=Roman Empire Dominate Timeline|first=N.S.|last=Gill|work=About.com Education|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/