.org/pages/showDetails.aspx?objid=08000002804248ee |title=Treaty between the Government of Niue and the Government of the United States of America on the delimitation of a maritime boundary |publisher=[[United Nations]] |accessdate=30 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821191110/https://treaties.un.org/pages/showDetails.aspx?objid=08000002804248ee |archivedate=21 August 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;May||The '''[[Donetsk People's Republic]]''' and '''[[Luhansk People's Republic]]''' declare their independence from [[Ukraine]] following a [[Donbass status referendums, 2014|status referendum]]. [[Donetsk]] and [[Luhansk]] are proclaimed as their capitals. The referendum's results and the so-called republics' declarations were internationally unrecognized.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;March||The [[Republic of Crimea (country)|Republic of Crimea]] [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation|was annexed]] by the '''[[Russian Federation]]''' as [[Federal subjects of Russia|two separate federal entities]]: the [[Republics of Russia|Republic of]] [[Republic of Crimea|Crimea]] and the [[Federal cities of Russia|city of federal significance]] [[Sevastopol]]. Ukraine itself and much of the international community maintain that Crimea is illegally occupied by Russia and legally remains an integral region of Ukraine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/03/18/world/europe/ukraine-crisis/|title=Ukraine cries 'robbery' as Russia annexes Crimea|first1=Matt|last1=Smith|first2=Alla|last2=Eshchenko|date=18 March 2014|website=[[CNN]]|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117190740/http://www.cnn.com/2014/03/18/world/europe/ukraine-crisis/|archive-date=17 November 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;January||The [[Chilean\u2013Peruvian maritime dispute|maritime dispute between Chile and Peru]] is resolved.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icj-cij.org/docket/files/137/17930.pdf|title=Judgment of the ICJ about the maritime dispute between Peru and Chile|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210084913/http://www.icj-cij.org/docket/files/137/17930.pdf|archivedate=10 February 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|2013||align=center|24&nbsp;October||The [[Republic of Cape Verde]] decrees the official English-language rendering of its name to be the '''[[Republic of Cabo Verde]]''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panapress.com/Cape-Verde-changes-name-to--Cabo-Verde---13-885619-0-lang2-index.html|title=Cape Verde changes name to \"Cabo Verde\"|website=[[PanaPress]]|date=30 October 2013|access-date=28 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711032409/http://www.panapress.com/Cape-Verde-changes-name-to--Cabo-Verde---13-885619-0-lang2-index.html|archive-date=11 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> following precedents set by [[C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]] and [[East Timor|Timor-Leste]] (neither of which use English as an [[official language]]).\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;September||The [[United Federated States of Bangsamoro Republik]] ceases to exist with the [[Zamboanga City crisis|loss of Zamboanga City]].<ref name=r1>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/28/13/palace-zamboanga-crisis-over |title=Zamboanga crisis is over, Palace: Zamboanga crisis is over |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=28 September 2013 |accessdate=28 September 2013 |agency=Reuters |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929153614/http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/28/13/palace-zamboanga-crisis-over |archivedate=29 September 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;July||The [[United Federated States of Bangsamoro Republik]] declares independence from the Philippines and claims all of [[Malaysian Borneo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mnlfnet.com/Articles/Editorial_14Aug2013_Who%20is%20Afraid%20of%20Mindanao%20Independence_Prologue.htm|date=14 August 2013|accessdate=19 Nov