poli (2011)|takes over Tripoli]], moving its capital from [[Benghazi]] to [[Tripoli]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;July||[[Southern Sudan]] gains independence from [[Sudan]] as the '''[[Republic of South Sudan]]''' after a referendum the previous January, with [[Juba]] as its capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;February||After the [[2011 Libyan Civil War|Libyan Civil War]] started on 15 February, the [[National Transitional Council]] was formed to act as \"the political face of the revolution\", based in [[Benghazi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Anti-Gaddafi Figures Say Form National Council|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/02/27/libya-council-revolution-idUSWEB194120110227|work=Reuters|date=28 February 2011|last1=Abbas|first1=Mohammed|last2=Blair|first2=Edmund|accessdate=8 August 2012|editor-last=Drees|editor-first=Caroline|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918231150/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/02/27/libya-council-revolution-idUSWEB194120110227|archive-date=18 September 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;February||The [[Fiji|Republic of the Fiji Islands]] changes its name back to the '''[[Fiji|Republic of Fiji]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;January||The [[China|People's Republic of China]] has received {{convert|1158|km2|sqmi}} from [[Tajikistan]] after a final ratification of a treaty ceding it<ref>{{Cite news|title=China's area increases by 1000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-12/china/28364278_1_tajik-government-tajikistan-protocol|date=12 January 2011|newspaper=[[Times of India]]|agency=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]]|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615083147/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-12/china/28364278_1_tajik-government-tajikistan-protocol|archive-date=15 June 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|2010||align=center|21&nbsp;October||The [[Union of Mya