the [[Republic of Kuwait]] as the '''[[Kuwait Governorate]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Abkhazia]]''' declares independence from the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]. [[Sukhumi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;August||The [[State of Kuwait]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Kuwait]]'''. [[Kuwait City]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;July||The [[Byelorussian SSR]] declares sovereignty from the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]] as the '''[[Republic of Belarus]]'''. [[Minsk]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||The [[Fiji|Republic of Fiji]] is renamed the '''[[Fiji|Sovereign Democratic Republic of Fiji]]'''. [[Suva]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;May||The [[Yemen Arab Republic]] ([[North Yemen]]) and the [[People's Democratic Republic of Yemen]] ([[South Yemen]]) reunite to form the '''[[Republic of Yemen]]'''. [[Aden]] yields to [[San'a']] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17 May||The '''[[Autonomous Region of Bougainville|Republic of Bougainville]]''' declares independence from [[Papua New Guinea]]. [[Buka, Papua New Guinea|Buka]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|8 May||The [[Estonian SSR]] is renamed the '''[[Republic of Estonia]]'''. [[Tallinn]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4 May||The [[Latvian SSR]] is renamed the '''[[Republic of Latvia]]''' and it declares Soviet rule illegal and declares the restoration period for the independence of Latvia from the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]. [[Riga]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;April||The [[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Czech and Slovak Federal Republic]]'''. [[Prague]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;March||The [[Estonian SSR]] declares Soviet rule illegal and declares the restoration period for the independence of '''[[Estonia]]''' from the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]. [[Tallinn]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;March||[[South West Africa]] gains independence from [[South Africa]] as the '''[[Republic of Namibia]]'''. [[Windhoek]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|11&nbsp;March||The '''[[Republic of Chile]]''' moves its legislative capital from [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] to [[Valpara\u00edso]]. Santiago remains the administrative capital.\n|-\n|The [[Lithuanian SSR]] re-declares full independence as the '''[[Republic of Lithuania]]''' from the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]. [[Vilnius]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;March||The [[People's Republic of Benin]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Benin]]'''. [[Porto-Novo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;February||The government-in-exile [[Coalition Government of Democratic Kampuchea]] becomes the '''[[Coalition Government of Democratic Kampuchea#History|National Government of Cambodia]]'''.\n|}\n\n====1980s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\"|1989||align=center|30&nbsp;December||The [[Polish People's Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Poland]]'''. [[Warsaw]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;December||The [[Romanian Revolution]]. The [[Socialist Republic of Romania]] changes its name to '''[[Romania]]'''. [[Bucharest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;October||The [[Hungarian People's Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Third Hungarian Republic|Hungarian Republic]]'''. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Senegal]]''' and the '''[[Republic of The Gambia]]''' secede from the [[Senegambia Confederation]]. [[Dakar]] remains the capital of Senegal. [[Banjul]] is again the capital of The Gambia.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;September||The [[Socialist Republic of Vietnam]] ends its occupation of the '''[[People's Republic of Kampuchea#Transition: State of Cambodia (1989 - 1993)|State of Cambodia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;June||The [[Union of Burma]] changes its name to the '''[[Union of Myanmar]]'''. [[Yangon]] remains the capital until 2005.\n|-\n|||The '''[[Federated States of Micronesia]]''' moves its capital from [[Kolonia]] to [[Palikir]] on [[Pohnpei]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;May||The '''[[People's Republic of Kampuchea#Transition: State of Cambodia (1989 - 1993)|State of Cambodia]]''' supersedes the [[People's Republic of Kampuchea]] ([[Cambodia]]). [[Phnom Penh]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;February||The [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]] ends its occupation of the '''[[Republic of Afghanistan]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1988||align=center|16&nbsp;November||The '''[[Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic]]''' declares [[Estonian Sovereignty Declaration|sovereignty]] over the laws of the [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||The '''[[State of Palestine]]''' declares independence from the [[State of Israel]]. It claims the [[West Bank]] and the [[Gaza Strip]], territories considered to be [[Israeli-occupied territories|occupied by Israel]] in the aftermath of the [[Six-Day War]]. [[East Jerusalem]] is the proclaimed capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://middleeast.about.com/od/documents/a/me081115f.htm|title=Text of Palestinian Declaration of Independence (1988) - Full Text of Palestinian Declaration of Independence, or Algiers Declaration of 1988|author=Pierre Tristam|work=About.com News & Issues|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304193735/http://middleeast.about.com/od/documents/a/me081115f.htm|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;September||The [[Socialist Republic of the Union of Burma]] changes its name to the '''[[Union of Burma]]'''. [[Yangon]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1987||align=center|30&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Democratic Republic of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;October||The '''[[Fiji|Republic of Fiji]]''' supersedes the [[Dominion of Fiji]]. [[Suva]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;February||The '''[[People's Democratic Republic of Ethiopia]]''' supersedes the [[Derg|Provisional Military Government of Socialist Ethiopia (Derg)]]. [[Addis Ababa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||'''[[New Zealand]]''' becomes a fully, sovereign independent state from the [[United Kingdom]] after the passing of the [[Constitution Act 1986|Constitution Act]]. [[Wellington]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1986||align=center|4&nbsp;November||The '''[[Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands]]''' becomes an [[insular area]] of the [[United States]] dissolving the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;November||The eastern [[Caroline Islands]] gain independence from the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]] as the '''[[Federated States of Micronesia]]'''. [[Kolonia]] on [[Pohnpei]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;October||The [[Marshall Islands]] gain independence from the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]] as the '''[[Republic of the Marshall Islands]]'''. [[Majuro]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;April||The [[Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]] is renamed the '''[[Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;March||The '''[[Commonwealth of Australia]]''' becomes a fully, sovereign independent state from the [[United Kingdom]] after the passing of the [[Australia Act 1986|Australia Act]]. [[Canberra]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||'''[[Aruba]]''' leaves the [[Netherlands Antilles]] to become one of three [[Countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands|constituent countries]] of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] following a change of the [[Charter for the Kingdom of the Netherlands|Charter for the Kingdom]]. [[Oranjestad, Aruba|Oranjestad]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1985||align=center|12&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of Ivory Coast]]. [[Yamoussoukro]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of the Sudan]]''' supersedes the [[Democratic Republic of the Sudan]]. [[Khartoum]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;October||In the [[Falkland Islands]] disputed by [[Argentina]] and the [[United Kingdom]], the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies]] becomes a separate territory known as '''[[South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1984||align=center|29&nbsp;November||The '''[[Beagle conflict]]''' between [[Chile]] and [[Argentina]] is [[Treaty of Peace and Friendship of 1984 between Chile and Argentina|solved]]. Argentina recognizes [[Picton, Lennox and Nueva|Picton, Lennox and Nueva islands]] as Chilean.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||[[Bourkina-Fasso]] changes its name to '''[[Burkina Faso]]'''. [[Ouagadougou]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;August||The [[Republic of Upper Volta]] changes its name to '''[[Bourkina-Fasso]]'''. [[Ouagadougou]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;February||The '''[[Republic of Cameroon]]''' supersedes the [[United Republic of Cameroon]]. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||[[Brunei]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Nation of Brunei, the Abode of Peace]]''' ([[Negara Brunei Darussalam]]). [[Bandar Seri Begawan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1983||align=center|15&nbsp;November||The '''[[Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]]''' declares independence from the [[Republic of Cyprus]]. [[North Nicosia]] is the capital. The international community considers the northern part of the island as Republic of Cyprus territory under Turkish occupation.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;September||The [[British Dependent Territory]] of [[Saint Christopher and Nevis]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis]]''' (also known as the [[Federation of Saint Christopher and Nevis]]). [[Basseterre]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;March||The '''[[Republic of Ivory Coast]]''' moves its capital from [[Abidjan]] to [[Yamoussoukro]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland]]''' changes the title of each of its [[Crown Colonies]] to that of a [[British Dependent Territory]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|1982||align=center|15&nbsp;August||The unrecognized '''[[Rwenzururu|Kingdom of Rwenzururu]]''' is taken back by [[Uganda]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;June||[[Democratic Kampuchea]] becomes exiled from Kampuchea, despite being a widely recognized [[UN]] member state, becomes the '''[[Coalition Government of Democratic Kampuchea]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;June||The [[United Kingdom]] recaptures the [[British dependent territory]] of the '''[[Falkland Islands]]''' ([[Islas Malvinas]]) from the [[Argentine Republic]]. Britain restores the name of the capital [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Puerto Argentino]] to [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Stanley]].\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;April||The '''[[Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka]]''' moves its capital from [[Colombo]] to [[Sri Jayawardenapura-Kotte]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;April||[[Canada]] becomes a fully sovereign, independent state from the [[United Kingdom]] after the passing of the [[Canada Act]]. [[Ottawa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of Zimbabwe]]''' [[Place names in Zimbabwe|changes many colonial place names]] including that of its capital from [[Harare|Salisbury]] to [[Harare]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;April||The [[Argentine Republic]] seizes the [[British dependent territory]] of the [[Falkland Islands]] from the [[United Kingdom]]. Argentina renames the Islands '''[[Islas Malvinas]]''' and [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Stanley]] the capital [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Puerto Argentino]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||The [[Republic of Senegal]] and the [[Republic of The Gambia]] unite to form the '''[[Senegambia Confederation]]'''. [[Banjul]] yields to [[Dakar]] as the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1981||align=center|26&nbsp;December||The '''[[Saudi-Iraqi neutral zone]]''' ceases to exist as the border between [[Saudi Arabia]] and [[Iraq]] is fixed.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Ciskei]]''' is declared independent by the [[Republic of South Africa]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;November||'''[[Antigua and Barbuda]]''' gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[St. John's, Antigua and Barbuda|St. John's]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;September||The [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Belize]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Belmopan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\"|1980||align=center|19&nbsp;December||The [[United Kingdom]] divides the [[Crown Colony]] of [[Saint Christopher-Nevis-Anguilla]] into the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Saint Christopher and Nevis]]''' and the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Anguilla]]'''. [[Basseterre]] remains the capital of Saint Christopher and Nevis, and [[The Valley, Anguilla|The Valley]] becomes the capital of Anguilla.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|30&nbsp;July||The [[New Hebrides]] gain independence from a [[United Kingdom|British]]-[[France|French]] [[Condominium (international law)|condominium]] as the '''[[Republic of Vanuatu]]'''. [[Port Vila]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|'''[[Israel]]''' passes the [[Jerusalem Law]], expanding its declared capital of [[Jerusalem]] to include the annexed [[East Jerusalem]]. The [[United Nations]] [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 478|declares the law null and void]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;July||[[Peruvian Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Peru]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of Vemerana]]''' is taken back over by the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]][[France|-French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;May||The '''[[Republic of Vemerana]]''' declares independence from the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]][[France|-French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;May||'''[[Tafea]]''' is taken back over by the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]][[France|-French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;April||[[Southern Rhodesia]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Republic of Zimbabwe]]'''. [[Harare|Salisbury]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;February||'''[[Tafea]]''' declares independence from the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]][[France|-French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|}\n\n====1970s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"14\"|1979||align=center|25&nbsp;December||The [[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]] occupies the '''[[Democratic Republic of Afghanistan]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of Zimbabwe Rhodesia]] is dissolved as the [[United Kingdom]] regains control of '''[[Southern Rhodesia]]'''. [[Harare|Salisbury]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;October||'''[[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]''' gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kingstown]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||The [[United States of America]] dissolves the [[Panama Canal Zone]] and returns sovereignty to the '''[[Republic of Panama]]'''. The United States and Panama will jointly operate the [[Panama Canal]] until 31 December 1999.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;September||The [[Central African Empire]] changes its name back to the '''[[Central African Republic]]'''. [[Bangui]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Venda]]''' is given independence by [[South Africa]]. [[Thohoyandou]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;July||The [[Gilbert Islands]] gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Independent and Sovereign Republic of Kiribati]]'''. [[South Tarawa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;June||The '''[[Republic of Zimbabwe Rhodesia]]''' ([[Southern Rhodesia]]) supersedes the [[Republic of Rhodesia]], although neither are recognized. [[Harare|Salisbury]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;April||[[Iran]] changes its name to the '''[[Islamic Republic of Iran]]'''. [[Tehran]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;March||[[Israel]] [[Egypt\u2013Israel Peace Treaty|agrees to return]] the [[Sinai Peninsula]] to '''[[Egypt]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;February||'''[[Saint Lucia]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Castries]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;February||The [[Pahlavi Dynasty|Imperial State of Iran]] changes its name to '''[[Iran]]'''. [[Tehran]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;January||The '''[[People's Republic of Kampuchea]]''' ([[Cambodia]]) supersedes [[Democratic Kampuchea]] ([[Cambodia]]). [[Phnom Penh]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;January||The [[Socialist Republic of Vietnam]] occupies '''[[Democratic Kampuchea]]''' ([[Cambodia]]).\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|1978||align=center|29&nbsp;December||After a transition to democracy, the [[Francoist Spain|Spanish State]] is renamed the '''[[Kingdom of Spain]]'''. [[Madrid]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;November||[[Dominica]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Commonwealth of Dominica]]'''. [[Roseau]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5 October||The [[State of Comoros]] changes its name to the '''[[Federal Islamic Republic of the Comoros]]'''. [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1 October||'''[[Tuvalu]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Funafuti]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;September||The [[Free, Sovereign and Independent Republic of Sri Lanka]] changes its name to the '''[[Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka]]'''. [[Colombo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;July||The '''[[Solomon Islands]]''' gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Honiara]] on [[Guadalcanal]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;April||The '''[[Democratic Republic of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1977||align=center|6&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Bophuthatswana]]''' is declared independent by [[South Africa]]. [[Mmabatho]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;June||The [[French Territory of the Afars and the Issas]] gains independence from the [[French Republic]] as the '''[[Republic of Djibouti]]'''. The city of [[Djibouti (city)|Djibouti]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;March||The [[Libyan Arab Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]]'''. [[Tripoli]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"13\"|1976||align=center|28&nbsp;December||The '''[[Socialist People's Republic of Albania]]''' supersedes the [[People's Republic of Albania]]. [[Tirana]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;December||The [[Central African Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Central African Empire]]'''. [[Bangui]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Transkei]]''' is given independence by [[South Africa]]. [[Mthatha]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of North Solomons]]''' is taken by [[Papua New Guinea]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;July||The [[Republic of Indonesia]] declares that [[East Timor]] is the '''[[Indonesian invasion of East Timor|Indonesian Province of Timor Timur]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;July||The [[Democratic Republic of Vietnam]] ([[North Vietnam]]) and [[Provisional Revolutionary Government of the Republic of South Vietnam]] unite to form the '''[[Socialist Republic of Vietnam]]'''. [[Ho Chi Minh City]] yields to [[Hanoi]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The [[French Republic]] elevates its [[Overseas Territory of Saint-Pierre and Miquelon]] to the '''[[Overseas Department of Saint-Pierre and Miquelon]]'''. [[Saint-Pierre, Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint-Pierre]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;June||The [[Seychelles]] become independent from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Republic of Seychelles]]'''. [[Victoria, Seychelles|Victoria]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;June||The '''[[Republic of the Philippines]]''' reinstates [[Manila]] as the capital. [[Quezon City]], the capital from 1948, was incorporated with Manila and 15 surrounding suburbs to form [[Metro Manila]]. [[Baguio]] is no longer a summer capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;June||In the [[British Indian Ocean Territory]], the islands of '''[[Aldabra]]''', '''[[Farquhar]]''' and '''[[Desroches]]''' are returned to [[Seychelles]] six days before its independence.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;March||[[Trinidad and Tobago]] is renamed the '''[[Republic of Trinidad and Tobago]]'''. [[Port-of-Spain]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;February||The [[Polisario Front]] declares the creation of the '''[[Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic]]''' in the region known as [[Western Sahara]]. [[Laayoune]] is the proclaimed capital, while [[Tifariti]] serves as the temporary capital. [[Morocco]] considers the SADR part of its sovereign territory, while the [[United Nations]] considers [[Spain]] the administering state.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;February||The '''[[People's Republic of Mozambique]]''' changes the name of its capital from [[Louren\u00e7o Marques]] to [[Maputo]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"21\"|1975||align=center|30&nbsp;December||The [[Malagasy Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Democratic Republic of Madagascar]]'''. [[Antananarivo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of Indonesia]] [[Indonesian invasion of East Timor|invades]] '''[[East Timor]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||The '''[[Lao People's Democratic Republic]]''' ([[Laos]]) supersedes the [[Kingdom of Laos]]. [[Vientiane]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;November||The [[Republic of Dahomey]] changes its name to the '''[[People's Republic of Benin]]'''. [[Porto-Novo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||The Portuguese colony of [[East Timor]] declares its independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[Democratic Republic of East Timor]]'''. [[Dili]] remains the capital. Portugal and most other nations refuse to recognize the new government.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;November||[[Suriname (Kingdom of the Netherlands)|Suriname]] ([[Suriname (Kingdom of the Netherlands)|Dutch Guiana]]) gains full independence from the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] as the '''[[Republic of Suriname]]'''. [[Paramaribo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;November||The restored '''[[Spain|Kingdom of Spain]]''' supersedes the [[Francoist Spain|Spanish State]]. [[Madrid]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;November||Due to [[Angola]] achieving independence, [[Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola|Angolan Forces]] invaded the '''[[Republic of Cabinda]]''', successfully taking it back.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;November||The [[Spanish State]] relinquishes control of '''[[Spanish Sahara]]'''. Both the [[Kingdom of Morocco]] and the [[Islamic Republic of Mauritania]] annex the region, now known as '''[[Western Sahara]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;November||The [[State of Angola]] gains independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[People's Republic of Angola]]'''. [[Luanda]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;September||The [[Territory of Papua and New Guinea]] gains independence from the [[Commonwealth of Australia]] as the '''[[Independent State of Papua New Guinea]]'''. [[Port Moresby]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of North Solomons]]''' declares independence from [[Australia]]. [[Buka, Papua New Guinea|Buka]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Cabinda]] '''declares independence from [[Portugal]] with little recognition. [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;July||[[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]] gain independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[Democratic Republic of S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]]'''. The city of [[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;July||The [[Comoros]] gain independence from the [[French Republic]] as the '''[[State of Comoros]]'''. [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]] on [[Grande Comore]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;July||[[Cabo Verde]] gains independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[Republic of Cape Verde]]'''. [[Praia]] on [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;June||[[Mozambique]] gains independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[People's Republic of Mozambique]]'''. [[Louren\u00e7o Marques]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;May||The [[Kingdom of Sikkim]] unites with [[India]] as the '''[[State of Sikkim]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;April||The '''[[Provisional Revolutionary Government of the Republic of South Vietnam]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of Vietnam]]. The name of the capital is changed from [[Saigon]] to [[Ho Chi Minh City]].\n|-\n|align=center| ||The capital of [[Malawi]] is moved from [[Zomba, Malawi|Zomba]] to [[Lilongwe]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;April||'''[[Democratic Kampuchea]]''' ([[Cambodia]]) supersedes the [[Khmer Republic]]. [[Phnom Penh]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"10\"|1974||align=center|13&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Malta]]''' supersedes the [[State of Malta]]. [[Valletta]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;October||[[Niue]] becomes a state in [[associated state|free association]] with [[New Zealand]], [[New Zealand nationality law|sharing New Zealand citizenship]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;September||The [[Guinea-Bissau|Republic of Guinea]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Guinea-Bissau]]''' and moves its capital from [[Madina do Boe]] to [[Bissau]]. The [[Portuguese Republic]] recognizes the independence of the [[Republic of Guinea-Bissau]].\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;August||The Turkish army reaches the [[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus]], gaining about 40% of the territory of the island of [[Cyprus]], after the invasion started on 20 July.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;June||The [[Tanna (island)|Tanna Nation]] is taken back by the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]]-[[France|French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;June||The '''[[Derg|Provisional Military Government of Socialist Ethiopia (Derg)]]''' supersedes the [[Ethiopian Empire]]. [[Addis Ababa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center| 24&nbsp;March||The Tanna Nation declares independence from the [[United Kingdom|Anglo]]-[[France|French]] [[New Hebrides]] Condominium.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;February||The [[Islamic Republic of Pakistan]] recognizes the independence of the '''[[People's Republic of Bangladesh]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;February||'''[[Grenada]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[St. George's, Grenada|St. George's]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||The [[Union of Burma]] changes its name to the '''[[Socialist Republic of the Union of Burma]]'''. [[Yangon]] remains the capital until 2005.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|1973||19&nbsp;November||[[Uruguay]] [[1973 Boundary Treaty between Uruguay and Argentina|recognizes]] '''[[Mart\u00edn Garc\u00eda Island]]''' as [[Argentina|Argentine]].\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;September||[[Portuguese Guinea]] declares its independence from the [[Portuguese Republic]] as the '''[[Guinea-Bissau|Republic of Guinea]]'''. Recognition is limited. [[Madina do Boe]] is the temporary capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||[[The Bahamas]] gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Commonwealth of The Bahamas]]'''. [[Nassau, Bahamas|Nassau]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||The [[United Kingdom]] changes the name of its [[Crown Colony]] of [[British Honduras]] to the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Belize]]'''. [[Belmopan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;June||The [[Kingdom of Greece]] is renamed the [[Hellenic Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center| ||In [[The Gambia]], the capital of Bathurst is renamed [[Banjul]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1972||align=center|2&nbsp;June||The '''[[United Republic of Cameroon]]''' supersedes the [[Federal Republic of Cameroon]]. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;May||The [[Dominion of Ceylon]] changes its name to the '''[[Free, Sovereign and Independent Republic of Sri Lanka]]'''. [[Colombo]] remains the ca