's Republic of South Yemen]] changes its name to the '''[[People's Democratic Republic of Yemen]]'''. [[Aden]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;October||[[Fiji]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Dominion of Fiji]]'''. [[Suva]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;August||The [[Sultanate of Muscat and Oman]] is renamed the [[Sultanate of Oman]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;August||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[British Honduras]]''' from [[Belize City]] to [[Belmopan]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;June||The '''[[Kingdom of Tonga]]''' gains full independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Nuku\u02bbalofa|Nuku{{Okina}}alofa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;June||[[The Gambia]] is renamed the [[Republic of the Gambia]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;March||The '''[[Khmer Republic]]''' ([[Cambodia]]) supersedes the [[Kingdom of Cambodia (1953\u201370)|Kingdom of Cambodia]]. [[Phnom Penh]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2 March||[[Rhodesia]] ([[Southern Rhodesia]]) unilaterally declares itself the '''[[Republic of Rhodesia]]'''. [[Harare|Salisbury]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2 March||[[Guyana]] is renamed the [[Co-operative Republic of Guyana]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[Republic of Biafra]] capitulates and is reabsorbed by the [[Nigeria#Military juntas|military junta]] controlled '''[[Federal Republic of Nigeria]]'''. [[Enugu]] falls to [[Lagos]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||The [[Republic of the Congo]] is renamed the [[People's Republic of the Congo]].\n|}\n\n====1960s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"6\"|1969||align=center|18&nbsp;December||The [[Saudi\u2013Kuwaiti neutral zone]] is divided and the border between [[Saudi Arabia]] and [[Kuwait]] is defined.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;October||The '''[[