nnexes]] '''[[Goa, Daman and Diu]]''' from [[Portuguese India]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Tanganyika]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Dar-es-Salaam]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;December||The [[Netherlands New Guinea]] is renamed '''[[Netherlands New Guinea|West Papua]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||The southern portion of the [[British Cameroons]] gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] and unites with the [[Republic of Cameroun]] to form the '''[[Federal Republic of Cameroon]]'''. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital. \n|-\n|align=center rowspan=4|28&nbsp;September||In the [[United Arab States]], [[Syria]] leaves the [[United Arab Republic]] and returns to the name of the [[Syrian Arab Republic]].\n|-\n|The [[Dadra and Nagar Haveli|Free Dadra and Nagar Haveli]] joins India, as [[Portugal]] ceases to claim it.\n|-\n|Portugal cedes [[S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o Baptista de Ajud\u00e1]] to [[Republic of Dahomey|Dahomey]].\n|-\n|Portuguese fort [[S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o Baptista de Ajud\u00e1]] (now Ouidah) is annexed by [[Republic of Dahomey|Dahomey]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;June||The [[Antarctic Treaty System]] enters force to administer the continent of '''[[Antarctica]]''' and all lands and waters south of the [[60th parallel south]].\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;June||The '''[[State of Kuwait]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kuwait City]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|31 May||The [[Union of South Africa]] ceases to be a [[Commonwealth realm]] and changes its name to the '''[[Republic of South Africa]]'''. [[Pretoria]], [[Cape Town]] and [[Bloemfontein]] remain the capitals.\n|-\n|Northern [[British Cameroon]] joins [[Nigeria]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of Sierra Leone]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Freetown]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;January||[[India]] annexes [[Portuguese India]], and Portugal maintains its claims to it.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"24\"|1960||align=center|28&nbsp;November||The '''[[Islamic Republic of Mauritania]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Nouakchott]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1 October||The '''[[Federation of Nigeria]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Lagos]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Mali]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Bamako]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Senegal]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Dakar]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;August||The '''[[Gabonese Republic]]''' ([[Gabon]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Libreville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Cyprus]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Lefkosia]] (Nicosia) remains the capital. The United Kingdom retains control of [[Akrotiri and Dhekelia]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of the Congo]]''' ([[Congo-Brazzaville]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Brazzaville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;August||The '''[[Central African Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Bangui]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Chad]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[N'Djamena]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;August||The '''[[Ivory Coast|C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Abidjan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Upper Volta]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Ouagadougou]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Niger]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Niamey]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Dahomey]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Porto-Novo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The capital of [[Pakistan]] is moved from [[Karachi]] to [[Rawalpindi]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|11&nbsp;July||The [[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic|Czechoslovak Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic]]'''. [[Prague]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The [[State of Katanga]] declares independence from the [[Republic of the Congo (L\u00e9opoldville)]] with no recognition.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The '''[[Somali Republic]]''' ([[Somalia]]) is created from a merger of the former colonies of [[British Somaliland]] and [[Italian Somaliland]]. [[Mogadishu]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||The [[Belgian Congo]] gains independence from the [[Kingdom of Belgium]] as the '''[[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Republic of the Congo]]''' ([[Congo-L\u00e9opoldville]]). [[L\u00e9opoldville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;June||The '''[[Malagasy Republic]]''' ([[Madagascar]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Antananarivo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;June||Independence of [[French Sudan]] from France with [[Senegal]] as the [[Mali Federation]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;April||The '''[[Togolese Republic]]''' ([[Togo]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Lom\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' moves its capital from [[Rio de Janeiro]] to [[Bras\u00edlia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of Cameroun]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Yaound\u00e9]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| ||The [[British Virgin Islands]] become a separate colony from the [[West Indies Federation]].\n|}\n\n====1950s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=4|1959||align=center|4&nbsp;July||In the [[West Indies Federation]], the '''[[Turks and Caicos Islands]]''' become a separate colony from '''Jamaica'''.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||[[Bioko|Fernando P\u00f3]] and [[R\u00edo Muni]] are merged to form '''[[Spanish Guinea]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;April||In [[French Africa]], the colonies of [[Senegal]] and [[French Sudan|Soudan]] merge to form the '''[[Mali Federation]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||The '''[[United Suvadive Republic]]''' secedes from the [[Sultanate of Maldives]]. [[Hithadhoo (Addu)|Hithadhoo]] is the capital.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"18\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |1958||align=center|19&nbsp;December||The French Colony of '''[[Niger]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;December||The French Colony of '''[[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||Sovereignty over [[Gwadar]] is transferred from the [[Sultanate of Muscat and Oman]] to [[Pakistan]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|4&nbsp;December||The French Colony of '''[[Dahomey]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|The French Colony of '''[[Ivory Coast]]''' joins the French Community.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;December||The French Colony of [[Ubangi-Shari]] joins the French Community as the '''[[Central African Republic]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||The following French colonies join the newly created '''[[French Community]]''':\n*'''[[Chad]]'''\n*'''[[Republic of the Congo|Congo]]'''\n*'''[[Gabon]]'''\n*'''[[Mauritania]]'''\n*'''[[Senegal]]'''\n*[[French Sudan]] (as '''[[French Sudan|Soudan]]''')\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;October||The '''[[Malagasy Republic]]''' ([[Madagascar]]) gains autonomy within the [[French Community]]. [[Antananarivo]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Guinea]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Conakry]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||Sovereignty over [[Christmas Island]] is transferred from the [[United Kingdom]] to [[Australia]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of Iraq]]''' and the '''[[Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan]]''' are created from the [[dissolution (law)|dissolution]] of the [[Arab Federation of Iraq and Jordan]]. [[Baghdad]] remains the capital of Iraq. [[Amman]] is again the capital of Jordan.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;April||[[Spanish West Africa]] is disestablished:\n*The province of [[Ifni]] becomes a separate colony.\n*The province of [[Cape Juby]] is ceded to Morocco.\n*The provinces of [[R\u00edo de Oro]] and [[Saguia el-Hamra]] become [[Spanish Sahara]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;March||The '''[[United Arab States]]''' are created from [[Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen]] (North Yemen) and the [[United Arab Republic]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|22&nbsp;February||The [[Egyptian Republic]] and the [[Syrian Arab Republic]] unite to form the '''[[United Arab Republic]]'''. [[Damascus]] yields to [[Cairo]] as the capital.\n|-\n|The French-administered [[United Nations Trust Territory]] of [[French Togoland]] is renamed [[Togo]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;February||The [[Hashemite Kingdom of Iraq]] and the [[Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan]] unite to form the '''[[Arab Federation of Iraq and Jordan]]'''. [[Amman]] yields to [[Baghdad]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;January||[[Ifni]] is separated from [[Spanish West Africa]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||The [[United Kingdom]] establishes the '''[[West Indies Federation]]''' as a federation of most of the [[British West Indies]], excluding the [[British Virgin Islands]] and the [[Bahamas]]. The ''de jure'' capital is [[Chaguaramas, Trinidad|Chaguaramas]] on [[Trinidad]] and the ''de facto'' capital is [[Port of Spain]] on [[Trinidad]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1957||align=center|31&nbsp;August||The '''[[Federation of Malaya]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kuala Lumpur]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;August||The '''[[Morocco|Sherifian Empire]]''' is renamed the [[Kingdom of Morocco]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||The '''[[Tunisia|Tunisian Realm]]''' is renamed the [[Tunisian Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;March||The '''[[Republic of Ghana]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Accra]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||'''[[Saar (protectorate)|Saar]]''' is given to [[West Germany]] as the state of [[Saarland]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|1956||align=center|13&nbsp;December||'''[[British Togoland]]''' is merged into the [[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]].\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;October||The [[Tangier International Zone]] under joint administration of [[France]], [[Spain]], the [[United Kingdom]], [[Italy]], [[Portugal]], and [[Belgium]] is reintegrated into Morocco.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;June||The '''[[Egyptian Republic]]''' declares its complete independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Cairo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;April||[[Spanish Morocco]] becomes part of Morocco.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;March||[[Dominion of Pakistan|Pakistan]] adopts a new constitution and changes its name to the '''[[Islamic Republic of Pakistan]]'''. [[Karachi]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;March||The '''[[Tunisian Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Tunis]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2 March||The '''[[Kingdom of Morocco]]''' gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Rabat]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[History of Sudan (1956\u201369)|Republic of Sudan]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Khartoum]] is the capital. [[Egypt]] relinquishes its claim to Sudan.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1955||||The '''[[Kingdom of Bhutan]]''' makes [[Thimphu]] the sole capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;November||The United Kingdom gives the '''[[Cocos (Keeling) Islands]]''' to Australia.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;October||The '''[[State of Vietnam]]''' is renamed the [[Republic of Vietnam]] (South Vietnam).\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;September||'''[[Rockall#The United Kingdom's claims|Rockall]]''' is officially claimed by the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||The [[French overseas territory]] of [[Ad\u00e9lie Land]] and the Malagasy dependencies of the [[Crozet Islands]], the [[Kerguelen Islands]], and the [[\u00cele Saint-Paul|Saint-Paul]] and [[\u00cele Amsterdam|Amsterdam]] merge to form the [[French Southern and Antarctic Lands]]\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;May||The '''[[Republic of Austria]]''' regains its independence. [[Allies of World War II|Allied]] occupation ends. [[Vienna]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"10\"|1954||align=center|20&nbsp;December||The [[French Republic]] recognizes the independence of the '''[[Kingdom of Cambodia (1953\u201370)|Kingdom of Cambodia]]'''. [[Phnom Penh]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|15&nbsp;December||The [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] makes the Netherlands [[Territory of Cura\u00e7ao]] one of its three [[Countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands|constituent countries]] as the '''[[Netherlands Antilles]]'''. [[Willemstad, Cura\u00e7ao|Willemstad]] on [[Cura\u00e7ao]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] makes the Netherlands [[Territory of Surinam]] one of its three [[Countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands|constituent countries]] as '''[[Suriname (Kingdom of the Netherlands)|Suriname]]'''. [[Paramaribo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;October||The [[Free Territory of Trieste]] is divided between '''Italy''' and '''[[Yugoslavia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||The [[Republic of India]] [[Annexation of Dadra and Nagar Haveli|annexes]] '''[[Dadra and Nagar Haveli]]''' from the [[Portuguese India]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;August||In the [[Dadra DNH|Free Dadra]], the capital is moved from [[Dadra DNH|Dadra]] to '''[[Silvassa]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;July||The '''[[Dadra DNH|Free Dadra]]''' declared independence from [[Portugal]], with recognition only from India.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;March||The '''[[Sultanate of Maldives]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of Maldives]]. [[Male, Maldives|Male]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;July||The [[French Republic]] recognizes the independence of [[Vietnam]] divided between the '''[[Democratic Republic of Vietnam]]''' ([[North Vietnam]]) and the '''[[Republic of Vietnam]]''' ([[South Vietnam]]). [[Hanoi]] and [[Saigon]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;April||The [[Geneva Conference (1954)|Geneva Accords]] grant independence to [[Vietnam]], which is provisionally divided into '''[[North Vietnam]]''' and '''[[South Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|1953||align=center|9&nbsp;November||The '''[[Kingdom of Cambodia (1953\u201370)|Kingdom of Cambodia]]''' declares its independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Phnom Penh]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;October||The '''[[Kingdom of Laos]]''' ([[Laos]]) gains independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Vientiane]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;August||The British colonies of [[Northern Rhodesia]], [[Southern Rhodesia]], and [[Nyasaland]] merge to form '''[[Rhodesia and Nyasaland]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;July||The [[Korean Armistice Agreement]] is signed, establishing the '''[[Korean Demilitarized Zone]]''' along the border between the [[North Korea|Democratic People's Republic of Korea]] ([[North Korea]]) and the [[South Korea|Republic of Korea]] ([[South Korea]]).\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;June||The '''[[Egyptian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Egypt]]. [[Cairo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;April||The [[United States of Venezuela]] is renamed the '''[[Republic of Venezuela]]'''.<ref>{{cite web|language=es|url=http://www.cervantesvirtual.com/servlet/SirveObras/12371752022348284198846/p0000001.htm#I_34|archive-url=https://archive.today/20141130084207/http://www.cervantesvirtual.com/servlet/SirveObras/12371752022348284198846/p0000001.htm%23I_34|url-status=dead|title=Constituci\u00f3n de los Estados Unidos de Venezuela de 1953|work=[[Biblioteca Virtual Miguel de Cervantes]]|archive-date=30 November 2014|date=15 April 1953|via=[[archive.is]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;January||The [[Estonian Government in Exile]] is established, in parallel to [[Baltic Legations (1940\u20131991)|Estonian diplomatic legations abroad]]. They are later both declared as keepers of the [[State continuity of the Baltic states|legal continuity]] of the restored [[Republic of Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of Maldives]]''' supersedes the [[Sultanate of Maldives]]. [[Male, Maldives|Male]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1952||align=center|17&nbsp;October||The unrecognized [[Republic of the South Moluccas]] is taken back over by '''[[Indonesia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;September||[[Italian Eritrea]] is federated within the '''[[Ethiopian Empire]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||The [[Territory of Puerto Rico]] becomes the '''[[Commonwealth of Puerto Rico]]''' upon ratification of the [[Constitution of Puerto Rico]], choosing [[Associated state|free association]] with the [[United States of America]]. [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;July||The [[Republic of Poland]] changes its name to the '''[[Polish People's Republic]]'''. [[Warsaw]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;April||End of the [[Occupation of Japan|Allied occupation]] of '''Japan'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1951||align=center|24&nbsp;December||The '''[[United Kingdom of Libya]]''' gains independence from a [[United Nations]] [[Allied occupation of Libya|trusteeship]], previously having been divided into the independent [[Emirate of Cyrenaica]], [[British Military Administration (Libya)|British-administered Tripolitania]] and the French [[Fezzan-Ghadames (French Administration)|Military Territory of Fezzan-Ghadames]]. [[Tripoli]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;June||Due to Portuguese colonies being reorganized as overseas provinces, [[Portuguese East Africa]] is renamed '''[[Portuguese Mozambique|Mozambique]]''' and [[Portuguese West Africa]] is renamed '''[[Portuguese Angola|Angola]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;May||The unrecognized state of [[Tibet (1912\u20131951)|Tibet]] is incorporated into the [[China|People's Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;February||The '''[[Republic of Poland]]''' and the '''[[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]''' [[1951 Polish-Soviet territorial exchange|exchange territory]] along their common border.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1950||align=center|5&nbsp;December||The [[Kingdom of Sikkim]] signs a protectorate treaty with '''India''', becoming a part of it.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;August||The [[Republic of the United States of Indonesia]] becomes a unitary state and changes its name back to the '''[[Republic of Indonesia]]'''. [[Jakarta]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;April||The '''[[Republic of the South Moluccas]]''' declares independence from Indonesia with no recognition.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;January||[[Union of India|India]] adopts a republican constitution and changes its name to the '''[[Republic of India]]'''. [[New Delhi]] remains the capital.\n|}\n\n====1940s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"23\"|1949\n|align=center|27&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of Indonesia]] becomes a federation as the '''[[Republic of the United States of Indonesia]]''' and its independence is formally recognised by the Netherlands. The capital returns to [[Jakarta]] from [[Yogyakarta (city)|Yogyakarta]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||The government of the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] leaves [[Mainland China]] for [[Taiwan]] where the regime is based today. [[Taipei]] becomes the ''[[de facto]]'' capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;December||The '''[[State of Israel]]''' declares [[Jerusalem]] its official capital. [[Tel Aviv]] continues to serve as the [[de facto]] capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;November||The [[United Kingdom|British]] administered protectorates of the [[Emirate of Cyrenaica]], the occuptied territory of [[Tripolitania]], and the French occupied territory of [[Fezzan]] merge to form a jointly administered '''[[Libya]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;November||The remains of [[French Indochina]] form the French-administered '''[[Kingdom of Cambodia (1953\u20131970)|Kingdom of Cambodia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;November||The [[Commonwealth of Australia|Australian]] administered [[Territory of New Guinea]] and the [[Territory of Papua]] merge to form the '''[[Territory of Papua and New Guinea]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|November||The British-occupied territory of [[Italian Somaliland]] is transferred to Italy as the '''[[Trust Territory of Somalia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;October||The Soviet-backed [[Second East Turkestan Republic|East Turkestan Republic]] is taken over by the [[China|People's Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;October||The '''[[German Democratic Republic]]''' ([[East Germany]]) is established in occupied eastern Germany. [[East Berlin]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1 October||[[Mao Zedong]] proclaims the '''[[China|People's Republic of China]]'''. [[Beijing]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;September||The [[Kingdom of Tripura]] [[Tripura Merger Agreement|merges]] with India.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;August||The '''[[Hungarian People's Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Hungarian Republic (1946\u201349)|Hungarian Republic]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;August||The Indian protectorate of the '''[[Kingdom of Bhutan]]''' declares independence.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;July||The area of Laos in [[French Indochina]] becomes a separate entity under France as the '''[[Kingdom of Laos]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;June||The [[1948 Arab\u2013Israeli War]] ends, resulting in former [[Mandatory Palestine|mandate]] territory split among '''[[Israel]]''', '''[[Jordan]]''', and '''[[Egypt]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;June||The area of Vietnam in [[French Indochina]] becomes a separate entity under France as the '''[[State of Vietnam]]''', though North Vietnam still claims independence.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;May||The '''[[Federal Republic of Germany]]''' (West Germany) and [[West Berlin]] are established in the U.S., British, and French occupation zones of Germany. [[Bonn]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;May||The [[Thailand|Kingdom of Siam]] changes its name back to the '''[[Thailand|Kingdom of Thailand]]'''. [[Bangkok]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;April||The [[Hashemite Kingdom of Transjordan]] is renamed the '''[[Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;March||The '''[[Dominion of Newfoundland]]''' joins [[Canada]] as the [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Province of Newfoundland]] following the [[Newfoundland referendums, 1948|Newfoundland referendums]]. [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St. John's]] yields to [[Ottawa]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;March||As a result of the [[1948 Arab\u2013Israeli War]], '''[[Israel]]''' captures half of the land allotted to an Arab state under the [[Partition Plan]], '''[[Jordan]]''' occupies the [[West Bank]], and '''[[Egypt]]''' occupies the [[Gaza Strip]].\n|-\n|align=center|2 March||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous state of '''[[Central Java]]''' is established.\n|-\n|align=center|1 March||The '''[[Emirate of Cyrenaica]]''' is created from part of the [[British Military Administration (Libya)|British Military Administration of Libya]]. The capital is [[Benghazi]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"21\" |1948\n|align=center|26&nbsp;November||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous state of '''[[East Java]]''' is established.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;September||The [[Dutch colony]] of [[Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]] is renamed the '''[[Netherlands Antilles]]''', as the dependencies gain equality in level of sovereignty.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;September||The [[State of Hyderabad]] is reintegrated back into the [[Indian Union]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;September||[[Korea]] is [[Division of Korea|divided between]] the '''[[North Korea|Democratic People's Republic of Korea]]''' ([[North Korea]]) and the '''[[South Korea|Republic of Korea]]''' ([[South Korea]]). [[Pyongyang]] and [[Seoul]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;August||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the '''[[South Sumatra|State of South Sumatra]]''' is established.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||Establishment of the '''[[Republic of Korea]]''' out of British/American/United Nations occupied Korea (South Korea).\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of the Philippines]]''' moves its capital from [[Manila]] to [[Quezon City]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;May||The '''[[State of Israel]]''' is established upon the termination of the [[Mandatory Palestine|British Mandate for Palestine]]. [[Tel Aviv]] is the capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yale.edu/lawweb/avalon/un/res181.htm|title=The Avalon Project : UN General Assembly Resolution 181|work=yale.edu|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061029150108/http://www.yale.edu/lawweb/avalon/un/res181.htm|archivedate=29 October 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;April||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the [[West Java|State of West Java]] is renamed the '''[[West Java|Sundanese State]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;April||'''[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]''' is [[Republic of Ireland Act 1948|declared a republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;April||The '''[[Faroe Islands]]''' becomes a self-governing dependency.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;March||[[Khanate of Kalat|Kalat State]] is integrated into the [[Dominion of Pakistan]].\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;February||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the '''[[West Java|State of West Java]]''' is created.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |4&nbsp;February||The [[Crown Colony]] of [[British Ceylon|Ceylon]] ([[Sri Lanka]]) gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]] as the '''[[Dominion of Ceylon]]'''. [[Colombo]] remains the capital until 1982.\n|-\n|In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the [[East Kalimantan|Siak Besar Territory]] is renamed the '''[[East Kalimantan|Federation of East Kalimantan]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;January||In the United Kingdom, the [[Malayan Union]] is renamed the '''[[Federation of Malaya]]'''.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |23&nbsp;January||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the states of [[Bangka Regency|Bangka Council]], the [[Belitung|Belitung Council]], and the [[Riau Sultanate#Riau Hall|Riau Council]] are merged as the '''[[Bangka\u2013Belitung Islands|Bangka Belitung and Riau Federation]]'''.\n|-\n|In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous '''[[Madura|State of Madura]]''' is created.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;January||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous state of the '''[[Banjar Regency|Territory of Banjar]]''' is created.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||The '''[[Union of Burma]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Yangon]] (British [[Rangoon]]) is the capital until 2005.\n|-\n|align=center| ||The '''[[Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen]]''' ([[North Yemen]]) moves its capital from [[Sana'a]] to [[Taiz]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"21\" |1947\n|align=center|30&nbsp;December||The '''[[Romanian People's Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Romania]]. [[Bucharest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;December||Sovereignty over the '''[[Territory of Heard Island and McDonald Islands]]''' is transferred from the [[United Kingdom]] to [[Australia]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;December||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the [[East Sumatra|Special Territory of East Sumatra]] is renamed the '''[[East Sumatra|State of East Sumatra]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;December||[[France]] claims the '''[[Saar (protectorate)|Saar]]''' as a protectorate from occupied [[Germany]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;November||The [[Dominion of New Zealand]] ceases to be a dominion of the [[British Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;November||The League of Nations Mandate of '''[[Nauru]]''' is transferred as a United Nations Trust Territory.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;October||The princely state of '''[[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Jammu and Kashmir]]''' is divided between [[India]] and [[Pakistan]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ek00fuXVz1wC|title=Kashmir in Conflict: India, Pakistan and the Unending War|last=Schofield|first=Victoria|date=1 January 2000|publisher=I. B. Tauris|isbn=9781860648984|language=en|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160518204837/https://books.google.com/books?id=Ek00fuXVz1wC|archive-date=18 May 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;October||Seven of the [[Turtle Islands, Tawi-Tawi|Turtle Islands]] are ceded to the [[Philippines]] by the [[United Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;October||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous state of the '''[[East Sumatra|Special Territory of East Sumatra]]''' is created.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;September||The '''[[Free Territory of Trieste]]''' is created in [[Central Europe]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;August||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the '''[[East Kalimantan|Siak Besar Territory]]''' is created.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||The '''[[Dominion of India]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[New Delhi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;August||The '''[[Dominion of Pakistan]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Karachi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;August||Independence of the '''[[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]]''' ([[Khanate of Kalat|Kalat State]]) from the [[United Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;July||The [[South Pacific Mandate|South Pacific (League of Nations) Mandate]], governed by Japan, is transferred to the United Nations [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]], administered by the United States.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;July||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous states of '''[[Bangka Regency|Bangka Council]]''' and '''[[Riau Sultanate#Riau Hall|Riau Council]]''' are created.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;May||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the [[West Kalimantan|Federation of West Kalimantan]] is renamed the '''[[West Kalimantan|Special Territory of West Kalimantan]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;May||The new [[Constitution of Japan]] is adopted, dissolving the [[Empire of Japan|Greater Japanese Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;February||The [[Italy|Italian Republic]] returns its concession in [[Italian concession of Tientsin|Tientsin]] to the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;January||The New Zealand-administered League of Nations Mandate of [[Western Samoa]] is transferred as a United Nations Trust Territory.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;January||In the [[Dutch East Indies]], the autonomous state of the '''[[South Kalimantan|Federation of South Kalimantan]]''' is established.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"32\" |1946\n|align=center|27&nbsp;December||In the Dutch East Indies, the autonomous [[State of East Indonesia|State of Great East]] is renamed the '''[[State of East Indonesia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;December||In the Dutch East Indies, the [[State of East Indonesia|'''State of Great East''']] is established.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;December||The Soviet-occupied area of the [[Republic of Mahabad]] is returned to Iran.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;December||In the Dutch East Indies, the autonomous [[Belitung|'''Belitung Council''']] is established.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||The League of Nations Mandate of the [[Territory of New Guinea]] is transferred as a United Nations Trust Territory, administered by Australia.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;December||In the Dutch East Indies, the autonomous state of '''[[Great Dayak|Dayak Besar]]''' is established.\n|-\n|align=center|December||Several League of Nations Mandates in Africa are transferred as United Nations Trust Territories:\n*16 December \u2014 [[British Cameroons]] and [[Cameroun]] (French-administered)\n*13 December \u2014 [[British Togoland]], [[French Togoland]], and the Belgian-administered [[Ruanda-Urundi]]\n*11 December \u2014 [[Tanganyika Territory]] is renamed [[Tanganyika]] (British-administered)\n|-\n|align=center|November||The Soviet-occupied area of the [[Azerbaijan People's Government]] is returned to Iran.\n|-\n| align=center rowspan=6 |27&nbsp;October||The [[French Republic]] elevates its unhabited possession of '''[[Ad\u00e9lie Land]]''' to an [[Overseas departments and territories of France|overseas territory]].\n|-\n|The French Republic elevates its colonies of '''[[French Equatorial Africa]]''', '''[[French West Africa]]''', and '''[[Madagascar]]''' to [[Overseas departments and territories of France|overseas territories]]; the [[French Republic|French]] colony of '''[[Comoros]]''' is separated from Madagascar; and [[French Somaliland]] is renamed the [[French Somaliland|'''Territory of French Somaliland''']].\n|-\n|The French Republic elevates its '''[[French Establishments in India]]''' to an [[Overseas departments and territories of France|overseas territory]].\n|-\n|The [[French Establishments in Oceania]] are renamed the '''[[French Settlements in Oceania]]'''.\n|-\n|[[New Caledonia and Dependencies]] is renamed the '''[[Territory of New Caledonia and Dependencies]]'''.\n|-\n|[[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] is renamed the [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon|'''Territory of Saint Pierre and Miquelon''']].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;October||In the Dutch East Indies, the autonomous state of the [[West Kalimantan|'''Federation of West Kalimantan''']] is established.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;October||The [[Provisional Government of the French Republic]] is renamed the '''[[French Fourth Republic|French Republic]]'''. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;September||The '''[[People's Republic of Bulgaria]]''' supersedes the [[Tsardom of Bulgaria]]. [[Sofia]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;July||The Spanish colonies of [[Ifni]] and [[Spanish Sahara]] merge to form '''[[Spanish West Africa]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;July||In [[Montenegro]] (then part of [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]]), the city of [[Podgorica]] is renamed [[List of places named after Josip Broz Tito|Titograd]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |4&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of the Philippines]]''' gains independence from the [[United States of America]]. [[Manila]] is the capital until 1948.\n|-\n|In the [[Soviet Union]], the city of [[K\u00f6nigsberg]] is renamed [[Kaliningrad]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;June||The [[Kingdom of Italy (1861\u20131946)|Kingdom of Italy]] is renamed the '''[[Italian Republic]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;May||The '''[[Hashemite Kingdom of Transjordan]]''' gains independence from a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[League of Nations]] [[British Mandate for Palestine (legal instrument)|Mandate]]. [[Amman]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;April||The colony of the '''[[Malayan Union]]''' is formed from the following protectorates:\n*[[Federated Malay States]]\n*[[Johor|State of Johor Darul Ta'zim]]\n*[[Kedah|State of Kedah Darul Aman]]\n*[[Kelantan|State of Kelantan Darul]]\n*[[Perlis|State of Perlis Indera Kayangan]]\n*[[Terengganu|State of Terengganu Darul Iman]]\n*[[Straits Settlements]] ([[Singapore]] becomes a separate crown colony)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |19&nbsp;March||The [[French Republic]] elevates its [[French colonial empire|colonies]] of '''[[Algeria]]''' and '''[[R\u00e9union]]''' to [[overseas department]]s.\n|-\n|The [[French Republic]] elevates its [[French colonial empire|colonies]] of '''[[Guadeloupe]]''' and '''[[Martinique]]''' to [[overseas department]]s.\n|-\n|The [[French Republic]] elevates its [[French colonial empire|colony]] of '''[[Guyane]]''' ([[French Guiana]]) to an [[overseas department]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;February||The following French concessions are ceded to the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]]:\n*[[Shanghai French Concession|Shanghai]]\n*[[Concessions in Tianjin#French concession (1860\u20131946)|Tientsin]]\n*[[Guangzhouwan|Kouang-Tch\u00e9ou-Wan]] (renamed '''[[Zhanjiang]]''')\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||The '''[[Hungarian Republic (1946\u201349)|Hungarian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u201346)|Hungarian Kingdom]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;January||The Soviet Union occupies part of northwestern Iran, and that area forms the puppet state of the '''[[Republic of Mahabad]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;January||The '''[[People's Republic of Albania]]''' supersedes the [[Democratic Government of Albania]]. [[Tirana]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of Indonesia]]''' moves its capital from [[Jakarta]] to [[Yogyakarta (city)|Yogyakarta]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"62\" |1945\n|align=center|29&nbsp;December||The '''[[Netherlands New Guinea]]''' is separated from the [[Dutch East Indies]].\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;December||The [[People's Republic of Poland|'''Republic of Poland''']] becomes independent.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||The '''[[Federal People's Republic of Yugoslavia]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]]. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;November||The [[Democratic Federal Yugoslavia]] is renamed the '''[[Federal People's Republic of Yugoslavia]]'''. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|November||The Soviet Union invades northwest Iran and creates the puppet state of the '''[[Azerbaijan People's Government]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;October||Taiwan is returned to the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;October||The Soviet Union annexes northern East Prussia.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;October||The Japanese puppet state of the [[Japanese occupation of Cambodia#Pro-Tokyo puppet state|Kingdom of Cambodia]] is taken over by France and put back under French Indochina.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;October||In occupied Japan, [[Banaba Island]] is given back over by the [[Gilbert and Ellice Islands]] under the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;October||In occupied Japan, the [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] are given back to the [[British Raj]].\n|-\n|align=center|October||In occupied Japan, [[Christmas Island]] is given back to the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;September||The [[Kingdom of Laos]], which was under Japanese occupation, is taken back by France as part of [[French Indochina]].\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;September||The [[British occupation of the Faroe Islands]] ends and is handed back to Denmark.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;September||The Soviet Union's occupation of the [[People's Republic of Korea]] ends.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;September||[[Nauru]] is taken over by Allied forces and placed under a United Nations trusteeship administered by Australia, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |12&nbsp;September||[[British Malaya|Malaya]] is given back to the United Kingdom from occupied Japan and is split into the '''[[Federated Malay States]]''' and the [[Johor|'''State of Johor Darul Ta'zim''']].\n|-\n|[[Japanese occupation of Singapore|Syonan-to]] is taken back over by the United Kingdom from Japan as the '''[[Straits Settlements]]'''. [[Singapore in the Straits Settlements|Singapore]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;September||In occupied Japan, [[Timor]] is split between the Portuguese [[Portuguese Timor|'''East Timor''']] and the Dutch [[Dutch East Indies|'''West Timor''']].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;September||[[Japanese occupation of British Borneo|Bourneo Kita]] and the occupation of the British protectorate of the Kingdom of Sarawak are taken back over by the United Kingdom as '''[[North Borneo]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;September||The [[Wang Jingwei regime|Reorganized National Government of the Republic of China]] is taken over by the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |8&nbsp;September||The [[Thailand|Kingdom of Thailand]] changes its name back to the '''[[Thailand|Kingdom of Siam]]'''. [[Bangkok]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The following states are freed from the [[Empire of Japan]] (which becomes [[Occupation of Japan|occupied]] by Allied forces) and become their own states from Malaya:\n*[[Kedah|State of Kedah Darul Aman]]\n*[[Kelantan|State of Kelantan Darul Naim]]\n*[[Perlis|State of Perlis Indera Kayangan]]\n*[[Terengganu|State of Terengganu Darul Iman]]\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;September||The United States occupies [[Wake Island]] from Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;September||The United States occupies the [[Bonin Islands]] and [[Volcano Islands]] from Japan.\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |2&nbsp;September||The '''[[Democratic Republic of Vietnam]]''' declares its independence from the [[French Republic]]. [[Hanoi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The '''[[Empire of Japan]]''' surrenders to [[Allies of World War II|Allied Forces]].\n|-\n|The capital of the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] is moved from [[Chongqing|Chungking]] back to [[Nanjing|Nanking]].\n|-\n|align=center|September||The concessions in [[Shanghai French Concession|Shanghai]], [[Concessions in Tianjin#French concession (1860\u20131946)|Tientsin]], and [[Guangzhouwan|Kouang-Tch\u00e9ou-Wan]] are re-controlled by France.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;August||[[B\u1ea3o \u0110\u1ea1i]] abdicates. End of the [[Nguy\u1ec5n dynasty]] in [[Vietnam]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;August||[[British Hong Kong]] becomes a crown colony.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;August||The [[Kwantung Leased Territory]] is returned to the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;August||The Japanese create a separate political entity for the [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |17&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of Indonesia]]''' declares its independence from the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]. [[Jakarta]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Commonwealth of the Philippines]] takes over the Japanese-occupied independent [[Second Philippine Republic|Republic of the Philippines]].\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;August||Hong Kong is liberated from Japan by Allied forces and put under [[British Hong Kong|British rule]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\" |15&nbsp;August||'''[[Korea]]''' gains independence from the [[Empire of Japan]]. [[Seoul]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Great Empire of Manchuria]] is taken over by the [[Soviet Union]].\n|-\n|'''[[French Indochina]]''' is recovered by France.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||The Japanese-occupied [[Empire of Vietnam]] is taken back over by France.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;June||A treaty is signed between the Soviet Union and [[Third Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovakia]] having the Soviet Union annex [[Subcarpathian Ruthenia]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;June||The [[State of Brunei]] is retaken by the United Kingdom and is classified as a protectorate.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;May||The [[Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia]] is integrated back into [[Third Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovakia]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |9 May||[[Reichskommissariat Norwegen]] (Norway) is liberated by Allied forces and its possessions are returned ([[Bouvet Island]], [[Peter I Island]], and [[Queen Maud Land]]).\n|-\n|The [[Channel Islands]] are liberated from Nazi Germany to the United Kingdom as the '''[[Bailiwick of Guernsey]]''' and the [[Jersey|'''Bailiwick of Jersey''']].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |8 May||The '''[[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]]''' surrenders to the [[Allies of World War II|Allied Forces]].\n|-\n|The [[Independent State of Croatia]] is taken over by Allied forces and given back to [[Yugoslavia]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;May||The [[Dodecanese Islands]] are taken over by Allied forces and given to [[Greece]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |5&nbsp;May||The [[Occupation of Denmark|occupation]] of the [[Kingdom of Denmark]] by the [[Flensburg Government]] ends. [[Greenland]] is returned to Denmark from United States protection.\n|-\n|The [[Reichskommissariat Niederlande]] (the [[Netherlands]]) is liberated and merged with the colonies loyal to the government-in-exile of [[Cura\u00e7ao|Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]] and the [[Surinam (Dutch colony)|Surinam]] to form the '''[[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;May||Following the death of [[Adolf Hitler]] and the Allied victory in the [[Battle of Berlin]], the government of Nazi Germany is moved to [[Flensburg]] and the '''[[Flensburg Government]]''' is created.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;April||The second '''[[Republic of Austria]]''' is established in occupied Austria. [[Vienna]] is the capital. The independence is recognised by the [[Allies of World War II|Allied Forces]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;April||The [[Italian Social Republic]] is recovered from Nazi Germany and given to the [[Kingdom of Italy (1861\u20131946)|Kingdom of Italy]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;April||The [[Kingdom of Laos]] declares independence under Japanese occupation, while Japanese [[Indochina]] ceases to exist as a political entity.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;April||The [[Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)|Slovak Republic]] is liberated and given to the [[Third Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovak Republic]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |3 April||The [[Third Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovak Republic]] is liberated from Nazi Germany.\n|-\n|The United States takes over the [[Ryukyu Islands]] and administers it as the '''[[United States Civil Administration of the Ryukyu Islands]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;March||The [[State of Burma]] is taken back over by Allied forces and becomes the British crown colony of [[British Burma|'''Burma''']].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;March||France regains [[Alsace-Lorraine]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;March||The [[Kingdom of Cambodia]] declares independence from Japan under its occupation.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;March||The [[Empire of Vietnam]] declares independence from Japan under its occupation.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;March||The [[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u20131946)|Kingdom of Hungary]] is liberated from Nazi Germany.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;January||The Polish area of the [[General Government]] is liberated from Nazi Germany by the Allied Forces.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"18\" |1944\n|align=center|17&nbsp;June||The '''[[Kingdom of Iceland]]''' ends its [[personal union]] with the [[Kingdom of Denmark]] and becomes a republic. [[Reykjav\u00edk]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;December||The [[People's Republic of Poland|Republic of Poland]] gains independence.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;December||The [[Kingdom of Montenegro]], a puppet state of the [[Italian Social Republic]] (itself a puppet state of Nazi Germany), is taken over by Allied forces.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;November||The [[Independent State of Macedonia]] is liberated from the Axis powers, and Yugoslavia takes it back.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;November||The [[Second East Turkestan Republic|East Turkestan Republic]] declares independence from the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;November||The [[Hellenic State (1941\u20131944)|Hellenic State]] is completely liberated from the Axis powers. The [[Kingdom of Greece]] takes over the rest of it.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |20 October||The [[Albanian Kingdom (1943\u20131944)|Albanian Kingdom]] is liberated from the Axis powers as the [[Democratic Government of Albania]].\n|-\n|The [[Military Administration in Serbia]] is liberated from the Axis powers, and Yugoslavia resumes control of it.\n|-\n|align=center|16 October||The [[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u20131946)|Kingdom of Hungary]] becomes a puppet state of [[Nazi Germany]], keeping the name of the [[Government of National Unity (Hungary)|Kingdom of Hungary]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |13 October||The [[Kingdom of Greece]] returns to power after [[Athens]] is recovered.\n|-\n|The [[Reichskommissariat Ostland]] is completely taken over by Allied forces and integrated into the Soviet Union.\n|-\n|align=center|11 October||The Soviet Union annexes the [[Tuvan People's Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|11 September||The [[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]] is liberated from Nazi Germany.\n|-\n|align=center|8 September||The [[Independent State of Macedonia]] is created in Bulgarian-controlled Macedonia.\n|-\n|align=center|3 September||The [[Military Administration in Belgium and North France]] is liberated from Nazi Germany. The [[Kingdom of Belgium]] is reformed, as [[Belgian Congo]] is put under the Belgian government's control after having remained loyal to the government-in-exile.\n|-\n|align=center|20 August||The [[Vichy France|French State (Vichy France)]] is renamed the [[Provisional Government of the French Republic]]. All of its colonies had remained loyal to the [[Free French Forces]] until Vichy France was disestablished, and [[Clipperton Island]] is returned.\n|-\n|align=center|10 August||[[Omiya Jima]] is taken over by the United States from Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|2 February||The [[Reichskommissariat Ukraine]] ([[Ukraine]]) is taken back over by the Soviet Union.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"16\" |1943\n|align=center|1 December||The [[Italian Social Republic|National Republic State of Italy]] is renamed the [[Italian Social Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;November||The [[Mandate of Syria]], made up of the [[French Mandate of Lebanon|State of Greater Lebanon]] and the [[French Mandate of Syria|Syrian Republic]], are given independence as the [[Lebanese Republic]] and the [[Syrian Republic (1930-58)|Syrian Republic]], respectively.\n\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;October||The [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] are taken over by Allied forces.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;October||The Japanese-occupied [[Japanese occupation of the Philippines|Philippines]] is given independence as the [[Second Philippine Republic|Republic of the Philippines]].\n|-\n\n|align=center|23&nbsp;September||The part of Italy under German occupation is made into a separate country as the [[Italian Social Republic|National Republican State of Italy]].\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;September||The [[Dodecanese Islands]] becomes an occupied territory under Nazi Germany from Italy.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;September||The [[Kingdom of Montenegro]] becomes a protectorate under Nazi Germany from Italy.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;September||The [[Albanian Kingdom (1939\u20131943)|Albanian Kingdom]] becomes a protectorate of Nazi Germany from Italy.\n|-\n|align=center|September||The [[French West Indies|French Antilles and Guiana]] is split into [[French Guiana]], [[Guadeloupe]], [[Inini]], [[Martinique]], and [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;August||[[Kiska]] is taken over by Allied forces.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;August||[[Japanese occupation of Burma|Burma]] is given independence under Japanese occupation as the [[State of Burma]].\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;July||The [[Shanghai French Concession]] and the [[Concessions in Tianjin#French concession (1860-1946)|Tientsin French Concession]] are taken over by Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;June||The [[Nazi Germany|German Reich]] is officially renamed the [[Nazi Germany|Greater German Reich]].\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;May||[[Attu Island]] is reconquered by the United States.\n|-\n|align=center|February||[[Guangzhouwan|Kouang-Tch\u00e9ou-Wan]] is conquered by Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|January||The French '''[[Fezzan-Ghadames (French Administration)|Military Territory of Fezzan-Ghadames]]''' is created when Free French forces from [[Chad]] invade southern [[Italian Libya]]. [[Sabha, Libya|Sabha]] is the capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"21\" |1942\n|align=center|28&nbsp;December||The Allied Forces take [[French Somaliland]] from [[Vichy France]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;December||The Allied Forces take [[Madagascar]] from Vichy France.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||The Allied Forces take [[R\u00e9union]] from Vichy France.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;November||The Allied Forces take the [[French protectorate of Morocco|Kingdom of Morocco]] from Vichy France.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;November||The [[Karafuto Prefecture]] is integrated into [[Mainland Japan]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |November||The '''[[British Military Administration (Libya)|British Military Administration of Libya]]''' begins when British forces invade [[Cyrenaica]] from [[Egypt]].\n|-\n|The Allied Forces take [[French West Africa]] from Vichy France.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;October||The Allied Forces take [[Tripolitania]] from Italy, and it becomes an occupied territory of the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;October||The [[Commonwealth of Australia]] ceases to be a dominion within the [[British Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;August||The Japanese occupy [[Banaba Island]] and [[Nauru]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;August||The Japanese occupy [[Burma]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;June||The Japanese occupy [[Attu Island|Atsuta Jima]] and [[Kiska|Narukami Jima]] from the United States.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;March||The Japanese occupy [[Christmas Island]] and the [[Straits Settlements]] from the United Kingdom as part of [[Japanese occupation of Malaya|Japanese Malaya]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;March||The Japanese occupy the [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;March||The Japanese occupy the [[Netherlands East Indies]] from the Netherlands as [[Japanese occupation of Indonesia|'''Indonesia''']].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;February||The Japanese occupy [[Portuguese Timor]] and [[Dutch Timor]] as '''[[Timor]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;February||The Japanese occupy [[Singapore]] from the United Kingdom as [[Japanese occupation of Singapore|'''Syonan-to''']].\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;January||The Japanese occupy the [[Johor|State of Johor Darul Ta'zim]] and the [[Federated Malay States]] from the United Kingdom as part of [[Japanese Malaya]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;January||The Japanese occupy [[Japanese occupation of British Borneo|Bourneo Kita]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;January||The Japanese occupy the [[State of Brunei Darussalam]] from the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;January||The Japanese occupy the [[Commonwealth of the Philippines]] from the United States as the [[Japanese occupation of the Philippines|'''Philippines''']].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"22\" |1941\n|align=center|25&nbsp;December||The Japanese occupy [[British Hong Kong]] as the [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong|'''Hong Kong Occupied Territory''']].\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;December||The Japanese occupy the [[Kingdom of Sarawak]] as [[Japanese occupation of British Borneo|'''Sarawak''']].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;December||[[Wake Island]] is taken over by Japan from the United States as [[Wake Island|'''Otori Jima''']].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;December||Within British Malaya, the [[Kelantan|State of Kelantan Darul Naim]] is taken over by Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;December||Within British Malaya, the [[Kedah|State of Kedah Darul Aman]] is taken over by Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;December||The Japanese occupy the [[Terengganu|State of Terengganu Darul Iman]] from the United Kingdom as part of [[Japanese occupation of Malaya|Japanese Malaya]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;December||The [[Guam|Territory of Guam]] is taken over by Japan from the United States as '''[[Omiya Jima]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||The Japanese begin the invasion of Malaya in the [[Perlis|State of Perlis Indera Kavangan]] and take it over as [[Japanese occupation of Malaya|'''Japanese Malaya''']].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||[[Italian East Africa]] is taken over by the Allied Forces.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |17 July||After the invasion of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania, Nazi Germany creates the '''[[Reichskommissariat Ostland]]'''.\n|-\n|After the invasion of Ukraine, Nazi Germany creates the '''[[Reichskommissariat Ukraine]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;July||After Italy invades [[Montenegro]], it creates the protectorate of the [[Kingdom of Montenegro (1941\u20131944)|Kingdom of Montenegro]].\n|-\n|align=center|July||The French share [[French Indochina]] with Japan.\n|-\n|align=center|19 May||[[Eritrea]] is taken over by the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|5 May||The [[Ethiopian Empire]] is revived after being under Italian control.\n|-\n|align=center|30 April||The [[Military Administration in Serbia]] is created after Nazi Germany invades it.\n|-\n|align=center|17 April||The [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]] is dissolved due to Axis invasions.\n|-\n|align=center|9 April||[[Greenland]] and the [[Kingdom of Iceland]] are put under United States protection from the Danish government-in-exile.\n|-\n|align=center|6 April||The [[Kingdom of Greece]] is taken over by Axis forces.\n|-\n|align=center|16 March||The [[British Somaliland]] protectorate is taken over by Allied forces.\n|-\n|align=center|26 February||Allied forces take over [[Italian Somaliland]], which is placed under the protection of the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|February||[[Cyrenaica]] is taken over by the United Kingdom.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"27\" |1940\n|align=center|12&nbsp;November||[[French Equatorial Africa]] is taken over by forces loyal to the Free French Forces (FFF).\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;November||The international city of [[Tangier]] is taken over by Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;September||[[New Caledonia]] and Dependencies are taken over by forces loyal to the Free French Forces (FFF).\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;September||[[French India]] is taken over by forces loyal to the Free French Forces (FFF).\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;September||[[French Oceania]] is taken over by forces loyal to the Free French Forces (FFF).\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;August||[[British Somaliland]] is taken over by Italian forces and becomes a part of [[Italian East Africa]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||The [[Estonian SSR]] is illegally annexed into the Soviet Union as the 16th union republic. This move is not recognized by the [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]] or the international community.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;August||The [[Latvian SSR]] is illegally annexed into the Soviet Union as the 15th union republic. This move is not recognized by the [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]] or the international community.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;August||The [[Lithuanian SSR]] is illegally annexed into the Soviet Union as the 14th union republic. This move is not recognized by the [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]] or the international community.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;August||The [[Moldavian SSR]] is created from a larger part of [[Bessarabia]], a region annexed from Romania on 28 June, and integrated into the Soviet Union as the 13th union republic.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;July||The [[General Government|General Government for the Occupied Polish Territories]] is renamed the [[General Government]].\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;July||The [[Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic|Estonian]], [[Latvian Soviet Socialist Republic|Latvian]] and the [[Lithuanian Soviet Socialist Republic]]s are declared in Soviet-occupied Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania. Most of the international community [[State continuity of the Baltic states#Western non-recognition of annexation|will not recognize]] Soviet rule in these occupied countries and some will keep recognizing [[Baltic Legations (1940\u20131991)|their diplomatic legations abroad]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The [[Jersey|Bailiwick of Jersey]] is taken over by Nazi Germany.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||The [[Guernsey|Bailiwick of Guernsey]] is taken over by [[Nazi Germany|German Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;June||The [[Soviet occupation of Bessarabia and northern Bukovina]] regions of Romania.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;June||The [[Third French Republic|French Republic]] is renamed the [[Vichy France|French State]] (Vichy France).\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;June||The Soviet Union invades the [[Estonia|Republic of Estonia]] and the [[Latvia|Republic of Latvia]].\n|-\n| align=center rowspan=2 |15&nbsp;June||The Soviet Union invades the [[Lithuania|Republic of Lithuania]]. Many states \n|-\n|Nazi Germany annexes [[Alsace-Lorraine]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;June||The [[Reichskommissariat Norwegen|Realm Commissariat for the Occupied Norwegian Territories]] is created when German forces invade the [[Kingdom of Norway]] and its possessions. [[Oslo]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;May||The '''[[Military Administration in Belgium and Northern France]]''' and the [[Reichskommissariat of Belgium and Northern France|'''Realm Commissariat of Belgium and Northern France''']] are created when German forces invade the [[Belgium|Kingdom of Belgium]]. [[Brussels]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;May||The [[Reichskommissariat Niederlande|'''Reich Commissariat for the Occupied Dutch Territories''']] is created when German forces invade the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]. [[Amsterdam]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;May||The '''[[Military Administration of Luxembourg]]''' and the '''[[Civil Administration Area of Luxembourg]]''' are created when German forces invade the [[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]]. [[Luxembourg City]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||The '''[[Faroe Islands]]''' are put under British occupation.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;April||The '''[[Kingdom of Denmark]]''' is invaded by German forces, while [[Greenland]] is granted autonomy.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;March||The [[Provisional Government of the Republic of China (1937\u20131940)|Provisional Government of the Republic of China]] and the [[Reformed Government of the Republic of China]] merge to form the '''[[Wang Jingwei regime|Reorganized National Government of China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;March||The '''[[Karelo-Finnish Soviet Socialist Republic]]''' is formed when Soviet forces invade the [[Finnish Democratic Republic]]. [[Petrozavodsk]] is the capital.\n|}\n[[File:Colonization 1945.png|thumb|220px|right|World map of colonisation in 1945]]\n[[File:Second world war europe 1941-1942 map en.png|thumb|200px|right|The Axis-controlled territory in Europe at the time of its maximal expansion (1941\u201342)]]\n\n====1930s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"16\" |1939\n|align=center|1&nbsp;December||The '''[[Finnish Democratic Republic]]''' is created after the invasion of [[Finland]] by the [[Soviet Union]]. [[Zelenogorsk, Saint Petersburg|Terijoki]] is the ''de facto'' capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||The '''[[General Government for the Occupied Polish Territories]]''' is created after the invasion of the [[Second Polish Republic|Republic of Poland]] by the [[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;October||The former territory of the '''[[Second Polish Republic|Republic of Poland]]''' is partitioned between the [[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]] and the [[Soviet Union]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;September||The '''[[Second Polish Republic|Republic of Poland]]''' falls as a government, inviting military occupation by the [[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;September||The colonies of [[French Guiana]], [[Guadeloupe]], [[Inini]], [[Martinique]], and [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] merge into the colony of the [[French West Indies|French Antilles and Guiana]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;September||The '''[[Free City of Danzig]]''' is annexed by the [[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]]. [[Danzig]] yields to Berlin as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|1&nbsp;September||[[World War II]] begins with the invasion of [[Republic of Poland|Poland]] by [[Nazi Germany]].\n|-\n|The Japanese-occupied [[Mengjiang]] is renamed the \"'''Mengjiang United Autonomous Government'''\".\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;July||Turkey fully annexes the [[Hatay State|Republic of Hatay]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||The third [[Nazi Germany|German Empire]] changes its name to the '''[[Nazi Germany|Greater German Empire]]'''. Berlin remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;June||The [[Thailand|Kingdom of Siam]] changes its name to the '''[[Thailand|Kingdom of Thailand]]'''. [[Bangkok]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||Italy annexes the [[Kingdom of Albania (1928\u201339)|Albanian Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;April||The islands of [[Kanton Island|Canton]] and [[Enderbury Island|Enderbury]] are put under the [[Canton and Enderbury Islands]] condominium of the United States and the United Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;April||The '''[[Spanish State]]''' supersedes the [[Second Spanish Republic]]. [[Madrid]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;March||[[Carpatho-Ukraine]] is annexed by Hungary.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;March||[[Czechoslovakia]] is partitioned into the German protectorate of [[Bohemia and Moravia]], [[Slovakia]], and [[Carpatho-Ukraine]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=9|1938\n|align=center rowspan=2|30&nbsp;September||The [[Munich Agreement]] transfers the [[Sudetenland]] from [[Czechoslovakia]] to [[Nazi Germany|Germany]] and gives parts of Slovakia to Hungary.\n|-\n|The [[First Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovak Republic]] is renamed the [[Second Czechoslovak Republic|Czecho-Slovak Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;September||The area known as [[Hatay Province|Hatay]] gains independence from [[Syrian Republic (1930\u201358)|Syria]] as the [[Hatay State]].\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;July||The [[Australia]]n [[Australian Capital Territory|Federal Capital Territory]] is renamed the [[Australian Capital Territory]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;March||The '''[[Reformed Government of the Republic of China]]''' is formed after Japan invades northeastern China.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;March||The third '''[[Nazi Germany|German Empire]]''' absorbs the '''[[Federal State of Austria]]''' in [[Anschluss]]. [[Vienna]] yields to [[Berlin]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;March||The United States claims the [[Canton and Enderbury Islands]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;January||Norway lays claims in Antarctica as [[Queen Maud Land]], which lies between [[20th meridian west|20\u00b0 west]] and [[45th meridian east|45\u00b0 east]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;January||[[Tristan da Cunha]] becomes a dependency of [[Saint Helena and Dependencies|Saint Helena]], a crown colony of the United Kingdom.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\" |1937\n|align=center|29&nbsp;December||The [[Irish Free State]] changes its name to '''[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]'''. [[Dublin]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;December||The [[Second Sino-Japanese War|Japanese invasion of China]] continues with the creation of the '''[[Provisional Government of the Republic of China (1937\u20131940)|Provisional Government of the Republic of China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;December||The Japanese invade [[Shanghai]], creating the [[Dadao government (Shanghai 1937\u20131940)|Dadao Municipal Government of Shanghai]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;November||The [[Mongol Military Government]] is renamed the [[Mongol United Autonomous Government]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|1&nbsp;April||The [[Aden Settlement]] is separated from [[British India]] and changed into the [[Colony of Aden|Aden Colony and Protectorate]]. The city of [[Aden]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|[[British Burma]] is separated from the [[British Raj]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=11|1936\n|align=center|22&nbsp;December||The [[Anglo-Egyptian Treaty of 1936]] is ratified and all British troops are withdrawn from Egypt, except for the [[Suez Canal Zone]].\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;December||In the [[French Mandate of Syria]], the [[Alawite State|Sanjak of Latakia]] is integrated into the [[Syrian Republic (1930\u201358)|Syrian Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||In the [[French Mandate of Syria]], the [[Jabal al-Druze (state)|Jabal ad-Druze]] is integrated into the [[Syrian Republic (1930\u201358)|Syrian Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;October||[[Spanish Guinea]] is taken over by [[Francoist Spain|Spanish Nationalist]] forces.\n|-\n|align=center|September||[[Ifni]] and [[Spanish Sahara]] are taken over by [[Francoist Spain|Spanish Nationalist]] forces.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||The British reassert their claim to [[Kanton Island]].\n|-\n|align=center|23 July||The [[Francoist Spain|Spanish State]] proclaims itself the sole government of Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|17 July||Spanish Nationalist forces take over [[Spanish Morocco]], starting the [[Spanish Civil War]].\n|-\n|align=center|1 June||The Italian colonies of [[Italian Eritrea|Eritrea]], [[Italian Ethiopia|Ethiopia]], and [[Italian Somaliland]] merge to form [[Italian East Africa]].\n|-\n|align=center|9 May||The [[Ethiopian Empire]] is taken over by Italy as [[Italian Ethiopia]] after the [[Second Italo-Abyssinian War]].\n|-\n| ||The former colony of [[Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]] is renamed the '''[[Territory of Cura\u00e7ao]]''' following the implementation of several laws resulting from the 1922 abolition of colonies in the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]. [[Willemstad, Cura\u00e7ao|Willemstad]] on [[Cura\u00e7ao]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=6|1935\n|align=center|25&nbsp;November||The '''[[East Hebei Autonomous Government]]''' is created in China after the invasion of eastern Hebei by the [[Empire of Japan]]. [[Tongzhou District, Beijing|Tongzhou]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||The United States territory of the [[Philippines]] becomes the semi-independent [[Commonwealth of the Philippines]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;November||The [[Second Hellenic Republic|Hellenic Republic]] is renamed the [[Kingdom of Greece]] after a coup d'\u00e9tat restores the monarchy.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;April||The [[Territory of the Saar Basin]] is taken over by [[Nazi Germany]].\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;March||[[Jarvis Island]] is transferred from the United Kingdom to the United States.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;March||[[Reza Shah Pahlavi]] changes the name of [[Iran|Imperial State of Persia]] to the '''[[Iran|Imperial State of Iran]]'''. [[Tehran]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\" |1934\n|align=center|15 October||The [[Chinese Soviet Republic]] is annexed by the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;October||The '''[[Catalan State]]''' is disestablished and is reabsorbed into the [[Spanish Republic]]. [[Barcelona]] yields to [[Madrid]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;October||The '''[[Catalan State]]''' proclaims itself independent of the [[Spanish Republic]]. [[Barcelona]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;March||[[Manchukuo]] is renamed to \"'''Manchutikuo'''\". [[Changchun|Hsinking]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;February||The [[First East Turkistan Republic|Islamic Republic of East Turkistan]] is taken over by the Republic of China.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||[[Italian Empire|Italy]] creates '''[[Italian Libya]]''' with the merger of the colonies of [[Tripolitania]], [[Cyrenaica]], and [[Fezzan]]. The capital is [[Tripoli]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=4|1933\n|align=center|12&nbsp;November||An [[Uyghurs|Uyghur]] independence movement creates the '''[[First East Turkistan Republic|Islamic Republic of East Turkistan]]'''. [[Kashgar]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;June||The United Kingdom cedes [[Enderby Land]] and [[Victoria Land]] to Australia as the [[Australian Antarctic Territory]].\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;April||[[Erik the Red's Land]] in Greenland is ceded by Norway to Denmark.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;March||The third '''[[Nazi Germany|German Empire]]''' supersedes the [[Weimar Republic]]. [[Berlin]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1932\n\n|align=center|3&nbsp;October||The '''[[Iraqi Kingdom]]''' ([[Iraq]]) gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Baghdad]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;September||The personal union of the [[Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz]] unify to form the [[Kingdom of Saudi Arabia]].\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;September||The [[Socialist Republic of Chile]] changes its name back to the '''[[Republic of Chile]]'''. [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;June||The [[Republic of Chile]] changes its name to the '''[[Socialist Republic of Chile]]'''. [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;February||The [[Empire of Japan]] takes over northeastern China and establishes '''[[Manchukuo]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|1931\n|align=center|11&nbsp;December||By the [[Statute of Westminster 1931]], '''[[Canada]]''' gains full control over its foreign policy and thus independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Ottawa]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;November||The '''[[Chinese Soviet Republic]]''' is established by the [[Communist Party of China]] as a group of discontiguous territories within the larger [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||Norway claims territory in eastern Greenland as [[Erik the Red's Land]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;June||The [[Australia]]n territories of [[North Australia]] and [[Central Australia]] merge to form the [[Northern Territory]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;April||The [[Catalan Republic (1931)|Catalan Republic]] is taken over by Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;April||The '''[[Second Spanish Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Restoration (Spain)|Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Madrid]] remains the capital. The [[Catalan Republic (1931)|Catalan Republic]] subsequently declares independence from Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;January||France officially annexes [[Clipperton Island|Isla de la Pasi\u00f3n]] as [[Clipperton Island]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[Concessions in Tianjin#Belgian concession (1902\u20131931)|Belgian concession]] within the city of [[Tianjin|Tientsin]] is returned to China.\n|}\n\n====1920s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\" |1929||align=center|3&nbsp;October||The '''[[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|October||The '''[[Kingdom of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Emirate of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;June||[[Tacna Region|Tacna]] is returned to [[Peru]] by [[Chile]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;February||Norway claims [[Peter I Island]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |February||'''[[Vatican City]]''' gains independence from the [[Kingdom of Italy (1861\u20131946)|Kingdom of Italy]]. [[Vatican City]] itself is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;January||The [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] is renamed the '''[[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|January||The '''[[Emirate of Afghanistan]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Afghanistan]]. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |1928||align=center|29&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] establishes [[Nanjing|Nanking]] as its official capital, later codified in the [[Constitution of the Republic of China]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;September||The '''[[Kingdom of Albania (1928\u201339)|Kingdom of Albania]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of Albania]]. [[Tirana]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\" |1927\n|align=center|28&nbsp;October||The [[Republic of Ararat]] declares independence from [[Turkey]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;May||The '''[[Commonwealth of Australia]]''' moves its capital from [[Melbourne]] to [[Canberra]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||The [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]] changes its name to the '''[[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland]]'''. London remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;January||Within the Nejd and Hejaz, the [[Sultanate of Nejd]] is renamed the [[Kingdom of Nejd|'''Kingdom of Nejd and its Dependencies''']].\n|-\n| ||In French Syria, the [[State of Souaida]] is renamed the [[Jabal ad-Druze|Jabal Druze State]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |1926\n|align=center|30&nbsp;June||[[Oltre Giuba]] is incorporated into [[Italian Somaliland]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;June||[[Afghanistan]] becomes the '''[[Kingdom of Afghanistan]]'''. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;May||The [[Rif Republic]] is dissolved by Spanish and French occupation forces in Morocco.\n|-\n| ||The [[Kingdom of Belgium]] moves the capital of its colony of the '''[[Belgian Congo|Congo]]''' from [[Boma, Kongo Central|Boma]] to [[Kinshasa|Leopoldville]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\" |1925\n|align=center|6&nbsp;December||Britain adjusts the Egyptian border in favor of [[Italian Libya]], giving it the [[Jarabub]] and [[Kufra]] oases.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||The [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] relocates its provisional capital from [[Nanjing|Nanking]] to [[Guangzhou|Canton]].\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;June||Britain transfers control of northern Jubaland to Italy, becoming the Italian colony of [[Oltre Giuba]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of Albania]]''' supersedes the [[Principality of Albania]]. [[Tirana]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Norway|Kingdom of Norway]]''' changes the name of its capital from [[Kristiania]] to [[Oslo]].\n|-\n|align=center|1924||align=center|26&nbsp;November||The '''[[Mongolian People's Republic]]''' is established. [[Ulan Bator]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1923||align=center|29&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Turkey]]''' is established following the fall of the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Ankara]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\" |1922||align=center|30&nbsp;December||The [[Russian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]], the [[Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]], the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic]] and the [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic]] unite to form the '''[[Union of Soviet Socialist Republics]]'''. [[Tbilisi]], [[Kharkov]], and [[Smolensk]] yield to [[Moscow]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;December||'''[[Northern Ireland]]''' secedes from the Irish Free State to again form a region of the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;December||The '''[[Irish Free State]]''' is constituted as an independent [[dominion]] formed through the secession of the island of Ireland from the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]]. [[Dublin]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;November||The '''[[Ottoman Empire]]''' is dissolved. Its territories are mostly made protectorates of the victorious [[Allies of World War I]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||The [[Far Eastern Republic]] is disestablished and merged with the [[Russian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;March||The [[Socialist Conciliar Republic of Georgia]], [[Azerbaijani Socialist Conciliar Republic]], and the [[Armenian Socialist Conciliar Republic]] unite to form the '''[[Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]]'''. [[Baku]] and [[Yerevan]] yield to [[Tbilisi]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;February||The '''[[Kingdom of Egypt]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Cairo]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\" |1921||align=center|22&nbsp;November||The [[United Kingdom]] recognizes the independence of '''[[Afghanistan]]'''. [[Kabul]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|13&nbsp;October||In the [[Treaty of Kars]], Turkey relinquishes claims to [[Armenia]] but gains the area around [[Kars]] and southern [[Adjara|Achara]].\n|-\n|[[Colony of Niger|Niger]] is established as a separate French colony. [[Zinder]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||[[Upper Silesia]] is divided between Poland and Germany.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;September||The [[Rif Republic]] is declared in Spanish Morocco with no recognition.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;August||The '''[[Tuvan People's Republic]]''' supersedes [[Tannu Uriankhai]] and changes the name of its capital from [[Belotsarsk]] to [[Kyzyl]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;June||France reorganizes [[French West Africa]] and the colony of [[Colonial Mauritania|Mauritania]] is established.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;March||The [[Peace of Riga]] defines new borders between Poland and Soviet Russia, Soviet Ukraine and Soviet Belarus.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;February||The '''[[Socialist Conciliar Republic of Georgia]]''' supersedes the [[Democratic Republic of Georgia]]. [[Tbilisi]] remains the capital until 1922.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\" |1920\n|align=center|29&nbsp;November||The '''[[Armenian Socialist Conciliar Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Democratic Republic of Armenia]]. [[Yerevan]] remains the capital until 1922.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;July||Denmark officially incorporates [[Northern Schleswig]] following a plebiscite held earlier in the year.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;June||The [[Treaty of Trianon]] is signed by [[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u201346)|Hungary]]. Its terms include:\n*The union of [[Transylvania]] and parts of [[Banat]], [[Cri\u015fana]], [[Szatm\u00e1r]] and [[Maramure\u015f]] with the [[Kingdom of Romania]] ([[Union of Transylvania with Romania|declared on 1 December 1918]]) is recognized.\n*[[First Czechoslovak Republic|Czechoslovakia]] is recognized.\n*The [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] and [[Banat, Ba\u010dka and Baranja]] are recognized.\n|-\n|align=center|Late April||[[Western Thrace]] is granted to Greece by the Entente.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;April||The '''[[Azerbaijani Socialist Conciliar Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Azerbaijan Democratic Republic]]. [[Baku]] remains the capital until 1922.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;April||The '''[[Far Eastern Republic]]''' is established. [[Chita, Zabaykalsky Krai|Chita]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;February||The '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1920\u201346)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' supersedes the [[Hungarian Republic (1919\u201320)|Hungarian Republic]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;February||The [[Estonian War of Independence]] ends with the [[Treaty of Tartu (Russian\u2013Estonian)|Treaty of Tartu]], which awards areas around [[Ivangorod]] (''Jaanilinn'') and [[Pechory]] (''Petseri'') from [[Soviet Russia]] to [[Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;January||The United Kingdom officially takes over administration of [[German East Africa]] and changes its name to '''[[Tanganyika (territory)|Tanganyika]]'''.\n|}\n[[File:Europe in 1923.jpg|thumb|right|Map of Europe from the 1920s]]\n\n====1910s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"27\" |1919\n|align=center|27&nbsp;November||[[Bulgaria]] signs the [[Treaty of Neuilly-sur-Seine]], by the terms of which:\n*[[Western Thrace]] is ceded to the [[Allies of World War I|Entente]].\n*The [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] is recognized and a small amount of land along the western border is ceded to it.\n*[[Dobruja]] is returned to [[Romania]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;September||[[Spitsbergen]] is awarded to Norway.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;September||The Bonin\u2013Pichon agreement transfers two desert strips from French control to [[Italian Libya]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;September||[[Austria]] signs the [[Treaty of Saint-Germain-en-Laye (1919)|Treaty of Saint-Germain-en-Laye]], by the terms of which:\n*[[Eastern Galicia]] is ceded to Poland.\n*[[South Tyrol]], [[Trentino]], [[Trieste]] and [[Istria]] are ceded to Italy.\n*The [[Kingdom of Romania|Romanian]] sovereignity over [[Bukovina]] is recognized ([[General Congress of Bukovina|union declared on 28 November 1918]]).\n*The independence of [[Hungary]], [[Second Polish Republic|Poland]], [[Czechoslovakia]], and the [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats, and Slovenes]] is recognized.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |14&nbsp;August||The '''[[Weimar Republic]]''' supersedes the second '''[[German Empire]]'''. [[Berlin]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |8&nbsp;August||'''[[Afghanistan]]''' declares its independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Kabul]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The '''[[Hungarian Republic (1919\u201320)|Hungarian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Hungarian People's Republic (1918\u201319)|Hungarian People's Republic]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;August||The '''[[Hungarian People's Republic (1918\u201319)|Hungarian People's Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Hungarian Soviet Republic]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||France and the United Kingdom agree on a frontier between their mandates in the [[Cameroons]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;June||In the aftermath of [[World War I]], the [[Treaty of Versailles]] and the [[Little Treaty of Versailles]] are signed, by the terms of which:\n*[[Eupen-Malmedy]] and [[Neutral Moresnet]] are ceded to Belgium.\n*[[Alsace-Lorraine]] is officially ceded to France.\n*The '''[[Second Polish Republic]]''' is established in place of the puppet [[Kingdom of Poland (1916\u201318)|Kingdom of Poland]]. Most of [[Province of Posen|Posen]] and [[West Prussia]] are ceded to Poland by Germany.\n*[[Klaip\u0117da Region|Memel]] and [[Saarland]] are put under international administration.\n*Plebiscites are provided for in [[Schleswig]] and [[Upper Silesia]].\n*[[Gda\u0144sk|Danzig]] and the surrounding area are superseded by the '''[[Free City of Danzig]]''', which is administered by the [[League of Nations]].\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;May||[[Ruanda]] and [[Urundi]] (minus Kisaka district) are assigned to Belgium as a mandate.\n|-\n| align=center rowspan=5 |7&nbsp;May||[[German New Guinea]] and the [[Bismarck Archipelago]] are assigned to Australia as a mandate.\n|-\n|[[German Southwest Africa]] is assigned to South Africa as a mandate.\n|-\n|[[German Samoa]] is assigned to New Zealand as a mandate.\n|-\n|The German Northern Pacific Islands are assigned to Japan as a mandate.\n|-\n|[[Nauru]] is assigned to the British Empire (eventually the United Kingdom, Australia, and New Zealand) as a mandate.\n|-\n| align=center rowspan=2 |6 May||The [[Kionga Triangle]] is assigned to Portugal as a mandate.\n|-\n|[[Kamerun]] and [[Togoland]] are assigned to France and the United Kingdom as mandates, respectively.\n|-\n|align=center|3 May||The '''[[Free State of Bavaria]]''' supersedes the [[Bavarian Soviet Republic]]. [[Munich]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19 April||Poland occupies [[Vilnius]], which is disputed by the Lithuanians.\n|-\n|align=center|6 April||The '''[[Bavarian Council Republic|Bavarian Soviet Republic]]''' supersedes the [[People's State of Bavaria]]. Munich remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;March||The '''[[Hungarian Soviet Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Hungarian People's Republic (1918\u201319)|Hungarian People's Republic]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| align=center rowspan=2 |1&nbsp;March||The [[Uruguay|Oriental State of Uruguay]] changes its name to the '''[[Oriental Republic of Uruguay]]'''. [[Montevideo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|[[French West Africa]] is reorganized, with [[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]] as a separate colony.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;February||The '''[[Lithuanian-Belorussian Soviet Socialist Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic]]. [[Vilnius]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||The Soviet puppet state [[Commune of the Working People of Estonia]] loses all territory to the [[Republic of Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Belarusian People's Republic]]. [[Minsk]] and [[Smolensk]] remain joint capitals.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"35\" |1918\n| align=center rowspan=3 |1&nbsp;December||[[Iceland]], a [[dependent territory]] of the [[Danish Realm|Kingdom of Denmark]] with [[home rule]], becomes the fully [[sovereign state]] '''[[Kingdom of Iceland]]''' in [[personal union]] with [[Denmark]]. [[Reykjav\u00edk]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The [[State of Slovenes, Croats and Serbs]] and the [[Kingdom of Serbia]] unite to form the '''[[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]'''. [[Zagreb]] yields to [[Belgrade]] as the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Union of Transylvania with Romania]] is proclaimed.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;November||The puppet state '''[[Commune of the Working People of Estonia]]''' is established in [[Estonian War of Independence|Soviet-occupied]] [[Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|28&nbsp;November||The [[Kingdom of Serbia]] annexes the [[Kingdom of Montenegro]].\n|-\n|The [[Union of Bukovina with the Kingdom of Romania]] is proclaimed.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;November||[[Banat, Ba\u010dka and Baranja|Vojvodna]], formerly part of Austria-Hungary, unites with the [[Kingdom of Serbia]].\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Latvia]]''' gains independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Riga]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;November||The '''[[Hungarian People's Republic (1918\u201319)|Hungarian People's Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Hungary (1867\u20131918)|Hungarian Kingdom]]. [[Budapest]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||The [[Kingdom of Serbia]] invades the short-lived [[Banat Republic]] and divides it between the [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia|Kingdom of Serbs, Croats, and Slovenes]] and [[Romania]].\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Poland]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Poland (1916\u20131918)|Kingdom of Poland]]. [[Warsaw]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of German-Austria]]''' is proclaimed.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Lithuania]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Lithuania]]. [[Vilnius]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\" |1&nbsp;November||The '''[[Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen]]''' ([[North Yemen]]) gains independence from the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Sana'a]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The '''[[Banat Republic]]''' is proclaimed.\n|-\n|The short-lived '''[[West Ukrainian People's Republic]]''' is proclaimed.\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;October||The '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1867\u20131918)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' declares its independence from the [[Austro-Hungarian Empire]]. [[Budapest]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;October||The '''[[State of Slovenes, Croats and Serbs]]''' gains independence from the [[Austro-Hungarian Empire]]. [[Zagreb]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||The '''[[Kingdom of Belgium]]''' reabsorbs the [[Independent State of Flanders]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;July||The '''[[Russian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Russian SFSR|Soviet Russian Republic]]. [[Petrograd]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;July||The '''[[Kingdom of Lithuania (1918)|Kingdom of Lithuania]]''' supersedes the [[State of Lithuania]]. [[Vilnius]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;May||[[Armenia]] changes its name to the '''[[Democratic Republic of Armenia]]'''. [[Yerevan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;May||'''[[Armenia]]''' and '''[[Azerbaijan Democratic Republic]]''' dissolve the [[Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic]]. [[Yerevan]] and [[Baku]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|26 May||The '''[[Democratic Republic of Georgia]]''' secedes from the [[Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic]]. [[Tbilisi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11 May||The '''[[Mountainous Republic of the Northern Caucasus]]''' annexes the [[Emirate of Chechenia]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;April||The '''[[Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Tbilisi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;April||The [[Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic]] annexes the [[Abkhazian Republic]] ([[Abkhazia]]).\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;March||The [[Union of Bessarabia with Romania]] is proclaimed ([[Treaty of Paris (1920)]]).\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;March||The '''[[Abkhazian Republic]]''' ([[Abkhazia]]) gains independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Sukhumi]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;March||The '''[[Belarusian People's Republic]]''' declares its independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Minsk]] and [[Hrodna]] are named the joint capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;March||The [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]] moves its capital from [[Petrograd]] to [[Moscow]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;March||The [[Treaty of Brest-Litovsk]] creates many new states out of the western [[Russian Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;February||The '''[[Republic of Estonia]]''' declares independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Tallinn]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;February||The '''[[State of Lithuania]]''' declares its independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Vilnius]] is named the capital despite occupation by the [[Kingdom of Poland (1916\u20131918)|Kingdom of Poland]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;January||The '''[[Ukrainian People's Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Kiev]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"10\" |1917\n|align=center|22&nbsp;December||The '''[[Independent State of Flanders]]''' declares its independence from the [[Kingdom of Belgium]]. [[Brussels]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;December||The '''[[Republic of Finland]]''' gains independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Helsinki]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||The '''[[Emirate of Chechenia]]''' declares its independence from the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]. [[Vedeno]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;November||The '''[[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Russian Republic]]. [[Petrograd]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;September||The '''[[Russian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Provisional Government of Russia]]. [[Petrograd]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;July||End of the [[Manchu Restoration]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||[[Puyi|Xuantong]] reinstalled as the [[Emperor of China]] in an event now called the \"[[Manchu Restoration]]\".\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||The '''[[Autonomous Governorate of Estonia]]''' is created from the [[Governorate of Estonia]] and some of the [[Governorate of Livonia]] of the [[Russian Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;March||The [[United States]] takes possession of the [[United States Virgin Islands]] ([[Danish West Indies]]) according to the terms of the [[Treaty of the Danish West Indies]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;March||The '''[[Provisional Government of Russia]]''' supersedes the [[Russian Empire]] in the wake of the [[February Revolution]]. [[Petrograd]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1916||align=center|5&nbsp;November||[[Germany]] and [[Austria-Hungary]] proclaim the establishment of the '''[[Kingdom of Poland (1916\u20131918)|Kingdom of Poland]]'''. [[Warsaw]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;March||The [[Empire of China (1915\u20131916)|Empire of China]] is abolished.\n|-\n|align=center|1915||12&nbsp;December||[[Yuan Shikai|Hongxian]] proclaims the '''[[Empire of China (1915\u20131916)|Empire of China]]'''. [[Beijing]] is the capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |1914\n|align=center|17&nbsp;April||[[Tannu Uriankhai]] is officially made a protectorate of the [[Russian Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;March||[[Albania]] becomes the '''[[Principality of Albania]]'''. [[Tirana]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\" |1913\n|align=center|29&nbsp;September||Following the [[Second Balkan War]], the [[Treaty of Constantinople (1913)|Treaty of Constantinople]] is signed, by the terms of which:\n*The [[Ottoman Empire]] regains the portions of [[Eastern Thrace]] it lost in the [[First Balkan War]].\n*The [[Balkan League]] gains all Ottoman territory west of the line joining [[Enez]] and [[K\u0131y\u0131k\u00f6y]] (thus the Ottomans lose all their European territory, except for what is roughly the southeastern half of Turkey's present-day European territory).\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;August||Following the [[Second Balkan War]], the [[Treaty of Bucharest (1913)|Treaty of Bucharest]] is signed, by the terms of which:\n*[[Bulgaria]] gains [[Western Thrace]] and the southern portions of what are now [[Blagoevgrad Province]] and [[Burgas Province]].\n*[[Romania]] gains [[Southern Dobruja]].\n*[[Serbia]] gains [[Kosovo]], most of what is now the [[Republic of Macedonia]], and some new land to the west of its previous borders.\n*[[Greece]] gains [[Epirus]], [[West Macedonia]], [[Central Macedonia]], and most of the islands in the [[Aegean Sea]] that it did not control before the war.\n*[[Albania]] gains southern, eastern, and northern lands that bring it to its current borders.\n*Albania becomes officially independent, though a large portion of its lands are disputed.\n*[[Montenegro]] gains most of what is now its [[List of regions of Montenegro#Northern Region|Northern Region]].\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;February||'''[[Tibet (1912\u20131951)|Tibet]]''' declares independence from the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |1912\n| align=\"center\" |28&nbsp;November||'''[[Albania]]''' declares its independence from the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Tirana]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;November||The [[Treaty Between France and Spain Regarding Morocco]] assigns the northern and southern strips of Morocco to Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;March||The [[Treaty of Fez]] formally re-establishes Morocco as a French Protectorate.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of China (1912\u201349)|Republic of China]]''' overthrows the [[Qing dynasty]] of China in the [[Xinhai Revolution]]. [[Nanjing|Nanking]] is the provisional capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" |1911\n|align=center|29&nbsp;December||The '''[[Mongolia (1911\u201324)|Bogd Khanate of Mongolia]]''' declares independence from the [[Qing dynasty]] of China. [[Ulaanbaatar|Niislel Kh\u00fcree]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;November||In the [[Morocco\u2013Congo Treaty]], Germany acquires the [[Neukamerun]] region from France in exchange for dropping German claims in Morocco.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |1910\n|align=center|5&nbsp;October||The first '''[[Portuguese First Republic|Portuguese Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Portugal]]. [[Lisbon]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;August||The '''[[Korean Empire]]''' capitulates and is annexed by the [[Empire of Japan]].\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;May||The [[British Cape Colony|Cape Colony]], the [[Colony of Natal]], the [[Transvaal Colony|Transvaal]], and the [[Orange River Colony]] unite as the '''[[Union of South Africa]]''' to gain independence from the [[United Kingdom]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[French Republic]] creates '''[[French Equatorial Africa]]''' from its colonies of [[Gabon]], [[Middle Congo]], and [[Oubangui-Chari]]. [[Libreville]] and [[Bangui]] yield to [[Brazzaville]] as the capital.\n|}\n[[File:Map of Bulgaria after Treaty of Neuilly-sur-Sein\u0435-en.svg|thumb|Territory ceded by Bulgaria in the 1919 Treaty of Neuilly-sur-Seine]]\n[[File:Dissolution of Austria-Hungary.png|thumb|New borders of the states formed by the dissolution of Austria-Hungary]]\n[[File:German losses after WWI.svg|thumb|German losses as a result of the 1919 Treaty of Versailles]]\n[[File:London-geographical-institute the-peoples-atlas 1920 poland-and-the-new-baltic-states.jpg|thumb|Poland and the Baltic states after the Treaty of Versailles]]\n\n====1900s====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" |1909\n|align=center|9&nbsp;July||The [[Rattanakosin Kingdom|Kingdom of Siam]] transfers its southernmost provinces to '''[[British Malaya]]''' in the [[Anglo-Siamese Treaty of 1909]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |1908\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||King [[Leopold II of Belgium]] sells his private [[Congo Free State]] to the [[Kingdom of Belgium]]. The colony is renamed the '''[[Belgian Congo]]'''. [[Boma, Kongo Central|Boma]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;October||[[Austria-Hungary]] formally annexes the Ottoman [[Vilayet of Bosnia]] (under ''de facto'' Austro-Hungarian rule since the Treaty of Berlin 1878) as the '''[[Condominium of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]''' (causing the [[Bosnian crisis]])\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;August||The '''[[Kingdom of Bulgaria]]''' gains independence from the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Sofia]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |1907\n|align=center|17&nbsp;December||[[Ugyen Wangchuck]] establishes the '''[[Kingdom of Bhutan]]'''. [[Punakha]] is the winter capital and [[Thimphu]] is the summer capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;September||'''[[New Zealand]]''' gains independence from the [[United Kingdom]]. [[Wellington]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;April||The border between the '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' and the '''[[Republic of Colombia]]''' is defined by the Bogot\u00e1 Treaty. Brazil gains lands on the margins of the [[Solimoes River]] at the area known as ''Cabe\u00e7a de Cachorro'' (\"The Dog's Head\").\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;March||The [[Rattanakosin Kingdom|Kingdom of Siam]] concedes territory to '''[[French Indochina]]''' in exchange for [[Trat]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\" |1906\n| ||The [[French Republic]] divides its colony of [[French Congo]] into the colonies of '''[[Gabon]]''' and '''[[Middle Congo]]'''. [[Libreville]] remains the capital of Gabon. [[Brazzaville]] becomes the capital of Middle Congo.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |1905\n|align=center|26&nbsp;October||The [[Kingdom of Sweden]] recognizes the [[Dissolution of the union between Norway and Sweden in 1905|union dissolution]] and the independence of '''[[Norway|Kingdom of Norway]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" |5&nbsp;September||The [[Liaodong Peninsula]] and the Russian railway in south [[Manchuria]] are leased to the '''[[Empire of Japan]]''' following the [[Treaty of Portsmouth]].\n|-\n|The '''[[Empire of Japan]]''' annexes [[Sakhalin]] Island south of [[50th parallel north|50\u00b0 N]] following the [[Treaty of Portsmouth]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;June||The '''[[Norway|Kingdom of Norway]]''' declares its independence from the [[United Kingdoms of Sweden and Norway]] through [[Dissolution of the union between Norway and Sweden in 1905|dissolution]] of the [[personal union]] with [[Kingdom of Sweden]]. [[Kristiania]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |1904\n|align=center|4&nbsp;October||The Franco-Spanish Convention of Paris acknowledges formal control of '''[[Saguia el-Hamra]]''' (later northern [[Spanish Sahara]]) by the [[Kingdom of Spain]].\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;February||Following the Franco-Siamese Convention, the [[Rattanakosin Kingdom|Kingdom of Siam]] concedes border territories to '''[[French Indochina]]''' in exchange for French-occupied [[Chantaburi]].\n|-\n| ||The border between the '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' and '''[[British Guiana]]''' is defined by arbitration. Approximately half of the disputed land goes to each side.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\" |1903\n|align=center|18&nbsp;November||The new [[Republic of Panama]] grants the [[United States of America]] control of the '''[[Panama Canal Zone]]'''. [[Balboa, Panama|Balboa]] is the administrative center.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Bolivia]]''' and the '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' sign the [[Treaty of Petr\u00f3polis]]. Bolivia receives land in [[Mato Grosso]] from Brazil, and Brazil absorbs the [[Republic of Acre]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Panama]]''' secedes from the [[Republic of Colombia]]. [[Panama City]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;May||'''[[Mauritania]]''' becomes a protectorate of the [[French Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;January||The third '''[[Republic of Acre]]''' declares its independence from [[Bolivia]]. The capital is [[Antimary]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\" |1902\n|align=center|20&nbsp;November||King [[Edward VII]] of Britain adjusts borders in the [[Cordillera of the Andes Boundary Case 1902 (Argentina, Chile)]].\n|-\n|align=center|31 May||The [[United Kingdom]] creates the '''[[Orange River Colony]]''' from the [[Orange Free State]] and the '''[[Transvaal Colony]]''' from the [[South African Republic|South African Republic (Republic of Transvaal)]]. [[Bloemfontein]] and [[Pretoria]] remains the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|20 May||The '''[[Republic of Cuba]]''' gains independence from the [[United States of America]]. [[Havana]] is the capital.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\" |1901\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The '''[[Commonwealth of Australia]]''' is established by federation of the [[United Kingdom|British]] colonies of [[New South Wales]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Queensland]], [[South Australia]], [[Western Australia]] and [[Tasmania]]. [[Melbourne]] is the capital until 1927.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"3\" |1900\n|align=center|28 May||The [[United Kingdom]] occupies the '''[[Orange Free State]]'''. [[Bloemfontein]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|March||The first [[Republic of Acre]] capitulates and is reabsorbed by the '''[[Republic of Bolivia]]'''. Later the same year, the second Republic of Acre is declared with [[Antimary]] as its capital, and it is again reabsorbed by Bolivia.\n|-\n| ||The border between the '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' and the [[French colonial empire|French colony]] of '''[[Guyane]]''' ([[French Guiana]]) is defined by arbitration. The French troops that advanced to the margins of the [[Araguari River (Amap\u00e1)|Araguari River]] repair to the [[Oiapoque River]].\n|}\n\n===19th century===\n====1890s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1899||align=center|14&nbsp;July||The first '''[[Republic of Acre]]''' declares independence from [[Bolivia]]. The capital is [[Antimary]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|1898||style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|10&nbsp;December||The [[Monarchy of Spain]] cedes the '''[[Captaincy General of Cuba]]''' and the '''[[Captaincy General of Puerto Rico]]''' to the [[United States of America]] with the [[Treaty of Paris (1898)|Treaty of Paris]] at the conclusion of the [[Spanish\u2013American War]]. [[Havana]] and [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|The [[Monarchy of Spain]] cedes the '''[[Guam|Island of Guam]]''' to the [[United States of America]] with the [[Treaty of Paris (1898)|Treaty of Paris]] at the conclusion of the [[Spanish\u2013American War]].\n|-\n|The [[Monarchy of Spain]] cedes the '''[[Captaincy General of the Philippines]]''' to the [[United States of America]] with the [[Treaty of Paris (1898)|Treaty of Paris]] at the conclusion of the [[Spanish\u2013American War]]. [[Manila]] is the Spanish capital. The [[First Philippine Republic|Philippine Republic]] maintains its sovereignty with [[Malolos]] as its capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;November||The '''[[Puna de Atacama dispute]]''' is defined by arbitration, of the 75,000 km2 in dispute 64,000 (85%) were awarded to the [[Argentine Republic]] and 11,000 (15%) to the [[Republic of Chile]].\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;August||The '''[[United States of America]]''' annexes the [[Republic of Hawaii]] as the [[Territory of Hawaii]]. [[Honolulu, Hawaii|Honolulu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||The [[United States of America]] seizes control of '''[[Puerto Rico]]''' from the [[Spanish Empire]] during the [[Spanish\u2013American War]]. [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;June||The '''[[First Philippine Republic|Philippine Republic]]''' declares independence from [[Kingdom of Spain]]. [[Malolos]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||The '''[[Republic of Bolivia]]''' moves its administrative capital from [[Sucre]] to [[La Paz]]. [[Sucre]] remains the constitutional and judicial capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1897||||The [[Joseon Dynasty]] becomes the '''[[Korean Empire]]'''. [[Seoul|Hanseong]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1895||align=center |16&nbsp;November||The [[United Kingdom]] annexes the [[Crown Colony]] of [[British Bechuanaland]] to the '''[[Cape Colony]]'''. [[Vryburg]] yields to [[Cape Town]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;October||The [[Empire of Japan]] conquers the [[Republic of Formosa]]. Taiwan becomes a Japanese colony under the name \"'''[[Taiwan under Japanese rule|Takasago Koku]]'''\". [[Taihoku Prefecture|Taihoku]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|June||The [[Republic of Formosa]] moves its capital from [[Taipei]] to [[Tainan]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;May||The '''[[Republic of Formosa]]''' declares independence upon its annexation by the [[Empire of Japan]]. [[Taipei]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;April||The [[Qing dynasty]] of [[China]] cedes Taiwan to the [[Empire of Japan]] by the [[Treaty of Shimonoseki]].\n|-\n|5 February||The border between the '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' and the '''[[Argentine Republic]]''' is defined by [[Grover Cleveland]].\n|-\n|align=center|1894||align=center|4&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of Hawaii]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Hawai\u02bbi]]. [[Honolulu, Hawaii|Honolulu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1891||||[[Pratap Singh of Jammu and Kashmir|Pratap Singh]] defeats the ruler of [[Chitral (princely state)|Chitral]] and forces [[Hunza (princely state)|Hunza]] and [[Nagar (princely state)|Nagar]] to accept the suzerainty of [[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Kashmir and Jammu]] state.\n|-\n|align=center|1890||align=center|29&nbsp;November|| The end of the personal union between the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] and the [[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]]\n|}\n\n====1880s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1889||align=center|15&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of the United States of Brazil]]''' supersedes the [[Empire of Brazil]]. [[Rio de Janeiro]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;March||[[Menelik II of Ethiopia|Emperor Menelik II]] of '''[[Ethiopia]]''' moves his capital to [[Addis Ababa]].\n|-\n|align=center|1888||||The '''[[Republic of Honduras]]''' moves its capital from [[Comayagua]] to [[Tegucigalpa]], ending a century of indecision as to the country's capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1887||16 December||The '''[[Sultanate of Maldives]]''' becomes a [[British Protectorate]]. [[Male, Maldives|Male]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1886||align=center|1 May||[[Leopold II of Belgium|King Leopold II of Belgium]] selects [[Boma, Kongo Central|Boma]] as the capital of his '''[[Congo Free State]]'''.\n|-\n| ||The [[United States of Colombia]] become the [[Republic of Colombia]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1885||align=center|6&nbsp;September||The '''[[Principality of Bulgaria]]''' annexes [[Eastern Rumelia]]. [[Sofia]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center |1&nbsp;September||The [[United Kingdom]] establishes the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[British Bechuanaland]]'''. [[Vryburg]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center |2 May||[[Leopold II of Belgium|King Leopold II of Belgium]] establishes his '''[[Congo Free State]]''', a private government run by the [[International African Association]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"9\"|1884||align=center|18 October||Argentina ends the [[Conquest of the Desert|conquest campaign]] of Eastern [[Patagonia]], subduing the remaining [[Amerindian]] resistance (modern [[Provinces of Argentina|Provinces]] of [[Chubut Province|Chubut]] and [[Santa Cruz Province, Argentina|Santa Cruz]])\n|-\n|align=center|3 August||The British suzerainty in the '''[[South African Republic|South African Republic (Republic of Transvaal)]]''' [[London Convention (1884)|ends]]. [[Pretoria]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4 April||Chile gains [[Antofagasta Region|Antofagasta]] as part of the truce ending the ([[War of the Pacific]]) (made permanent in 1904)\n|-\n| ||The [[Greenwich]] [[prime meridian]] becomes the international standard reference for [[cartographers]]\n|-\n| ||[[German South-West Africa]] created<ref name=\"Scramble for Africa\">{{cite web|last1=Evans|first1=Alistair|title=What Caused the Scramble for Africa|url=http://africanhistory.about.com/od/eracolonialism/a/ScrambleWhy_2.htm|website=About Education|publisher=About.com|accessdate=28 April 2016|ref=Scramble for Africa|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407044852/http://africanhistory.about.com/od/eracolonialism/a/ScrambleWhy_2.htm|archive-date=7 April 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| ||[[German East Africa]] created\n|-\n| ||[[Togo]] created\n|-\n| ||[[Cameroon]] created\n|-\n|||The [[United Kingdom]] establishes the [[Crown Colony]] of the [[Territory of Basutoland]]. [[Maseru]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1883||align=center|20 October||Chile gains [[Tarapac\u00e1 Province (Peru)|Tarapac\u00e1]], [[Arica Province|Arica]], and [[Tacna Region|Tacna]] ([[Treaty of Anc\u00f3n]])\n|-\n| ||Argentina [[Conquest of the desert|incorpores]] the [[Patagonia]]n lands of modern [[Neuqu\u00e9n Province]], until the [[Limay River]]\n|-\n|align=center|1882||align=center|6&nbsp;March||The '''[[Kingdom of Serbia]]''' supersedes the [[Principality of Serbia]]. [[Belgrade]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"4\"|1881||align=center|3 August||The '''[[South African Republic|South African Republic (Republic of Transvaal)]]''' [[Pretoria Convention|regains independence]] under British suzerainty. [[Pretoria]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23 July||The border between the '''[[Republic of Chile]]''' and the '''[[Argentine Republic]]''' [[Boundary Treaty of 1881 between Chile and Argentina|is defined]].\n|-\n|align=center|14 March||The '''[[Kingdom of Romania]]''' is proclaimed. [[Bucharest]] is the capital.\n|-\n| ||[[Tunisia]] becomes a French protectorate\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1880||||The [[French Republic]] establishes the protectorate of '''[[French Congo]]'''. [[Brazzaville]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6 December||[[Federalization of Buenos Aires]]. [[Buenos Aires]] is declared the official capital of the '''[[Argentine Republic]]'''.\n|}\n\n====1870s====\n[[File:Bulgaria-SanStefano -(1878)-byTodorBozhinov.png|thumb|The Principality of Bulgaria according to the terms of the Treaties of San Stefano (black outline) and Berlin (green). Eastern Rumelia is shown in red.]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=18|1878||12&nbsp;November||The territories between the [[Pilcomayo River]] and Verde River, claimed by [[Argentina]] and [[Paraguay]], are awarded to Paraguay in an arbitration by [[Rutherford B. Hayes]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|13&nbsp;July||The '''[[Principality of Bulgaria]]''' moves its capital from [[Plovdiv]] to [[Sofia]]. ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|The [[Principality of Bulgaria]] is shrunk significantly ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|[[Eastern Rumelia]] is created as an autonomous province of the Ottoman Empire ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|[[Austro-Hungarian rule in Bosnia and Herzegovina|Austro-Hungarian occupation of the Vilayet of Bosnia]] ([[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]) is recognized; ''De facto'' under Austro-Hungarian rule. ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire cedes [[Thessaly]] and small parts of [[Epirus]] to Greece ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|[[Ele\u015fkirt|Alashkerd]] and [[Do\u011fubeyaz\u0131t|Bayazid]] are returned to the Ottoman Empire ([[Treaty of Berlin (1878)|Treaty of Berlin]])\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;May||The '''[[Principality of Romania]]''' gains independence from the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Bucharest]] is the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\"|3&nbsp;March||The '''[[Principality of Bulgaria]]''' is established by the [[Treaty of San Stefano]]. [[Plovdiv]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire recognizes Montenegro and cedes it territory including [[Nik\u0161i\u0107]], [[Podgorica]] and [[Antivari]] ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|Serbia gains independence and annexes [[Ni\u0161]] and [[Leskovac]] ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire recognizes Romanian independence ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|Russia cedes [[Northern Dobruja]] to Romania (ceded to Russia by the Ottoman Empire) ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|Romania cedes [[Southern Bessarabia]] to Russia ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire cedes Armenian and Georgian territories in the Caucasus to Russia, including [[Ardahan]], [[Artvin]], [[Batum]], [[Kars]], [[Olti]], Beyazit, and Alashkert. ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|The [[Vilayet of Bosnia]] becomes an autonomous province ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n|[[Crete]], [[Epirus]] and [[Thessaly]] receive limited self-government ([[Treaty of San Stefano]])\n|-\n| ||The [[Argentine]] [[Conquest of the Desert|campaign to take control]] of [[Patagonia|Patagonic]] territories start. By the end of 1879 Argentina's control would go as far as the [[R\u00edo Negro (Argentina)|Negro River]] (modern Provinces of [[R\u00edo Negro Province|R\u00edo Negro]] and [[La Pampa Province|La Pampa]], as well as southern [[Mendoza Province|Mendoza]], [[San Luis Province|San Luis]], [[C\u00f3rdoba Province (Argentina)|C\u00f3rdoba]] and [[Buenos Aires Province]]s).\n|-\n|align=center|1877||align=center|12&nbsp;April||The [[United Kingdom]] annexes the [[South African Republic|South African Republic (Republic of Transvaal)]] as the '''[[Transvaal Colony]]'''. [[Pretoria]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1876||align=center|3&nbsp;February||Limits between [[Paraguay]] and Argentina [[Treaty of the Triple Alliance#Argentina|are established]], following the [[Paraguayan War]]. Argentina is awarded the [[Gran Chaco#Geography|Central Chaco]] (current [[Formosa Province]]) and some territories in [[Misiones Province|Misiones]]. The territories between the [[Pilcomayo River]] and Verde River are pending arbitration.\n|-\n|align=center|1875||align=center|7&nbsp;May||Japan cedes southern [[Sakhalin]] Island to Russia in exchange for the [[Kuril Islands]] north of [[Iturup]] ([[Treaty of Saint Petersburg (1875)|Treaty of Saint Petersburg]])\n|-\n|align=center|1874||align=center|29&nbsp;December||The restored '''[[Restoration (Spain)|Monarchy of Spain]]''' supersedes the first [[First Spanish Republic]]. [[Madrid]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1873||align=center|17&nbsp;November||With the unification of [[Buda]], [[\u00d3buda]] and [[Pest, Hungary|Pest]], [[Budapest]] becomes the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1867\u20131918)|Hungarian Kingdom]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;July||[[Prince Edward Island]] joins Canada.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;February||The '''[[First Spanish Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Madrid]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |1871||align=center|9&nbsp;January||Limits between [[Paraguay]] and the [[Brazilian Empire]] [[Treaty of the Triple Alliance#Brazil|are established]], following the [[Paraguayan War]]. Brazil enlarges its [[Mato Grosso]] region.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1871||align=center|20&nbsp;July||[[British Columbia]] joins Canada.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;May||Germany annexes [[Moselle (department)|Moselle]] and most of [[Alsace]] from France following the [[Franco-Prussian War]], which becomes the [[Alsace-Lorraine|Imperial Territory of Alsace-Lorraine]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The second '''[[German Empire]]''' supersedes the [[North German Confederation]]. Berlin remains the capital. ([[Unification of Germany]])\n|-\n| ||Rome replaces [[Florence]] as the capital city of Italy.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1870||align=center|20&nbsp;September||[[Italy]] annexes the [[Unification of Italy#Capture of Rome|area around Rome]], ending the [[Papal States]], succeeded by the [[Prisoner in the Vatican|States of the Church]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;September||The third '''[[French Third Republic|French Republic]]''' supersedes the second [[French Second Empire|French Empire]]. Paris remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;July||The [[Crown Colony]] of [[Colony of British Columbia (1866\u201371)|British Columbia]] joins the '''Dominion of [[Canada]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;July||[[Hudson's Bay Company]] transfers [[North-Western Territory]] to Canada.\n|}\n\n====1860s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1868||align=center|1 October||The [[Bolivian Republic]] changes its name to the '''[[Republic of Bolivia]]'''. [[Sucre]] remains the capital until 1898.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;January||[[Japan]] becomes the '''[[Empire of Greater Japan]]'''. The capital is moved from [[Kyoto]] to Edo, which is renamed [[Tokyo]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1867||align=center|18&nbsp;October||The [[Russian Empire]] sells '''[[Alaska]]''' to the [[United States of America]]. [[New Archangel]] ([[Novoarkhangelsk]] now [[Sitka, Alaska|Sitka]]) is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1&nbsp;July||The [[United Kingdom]] unites its colonies of [[New Brunswick]], [[Nova Scotia]], and the [[Crown Colony]] of the [[United Province of Canada]] as '''[[Canada]]'''. [[Ottawa]] is the capital.\n|-\n|The '''[[North German Confederation]]''' supersedes the [[German Confederation]]. [[Berlin]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;June||The '''[[Mexico|United Mexican States]]''' supersedes the [[Second Mexican Empire|Mexican Empire]]. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;May||'''[[Austria-Hungary]]''' supersedes the [[Austrian Empire]]. [[Vienna]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1866||align=center|22&nbsp;October||The '''[[Kingdom of Italy]]''' annexes the [[Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia]]. [[Venice]] yields to [[Florence]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||The [[United Kingdom]] unites the colonies of [[Colony of British Columbia (1858\u201366)|British Columbia]] and the [[Colony of Vancouver Island|Island of Vancouver and its Dependencies]] as the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Colony of British Columbia (1866\u201371)|British Columbia]]'''. [[New Westminster]] yields to [[Victoria, British Columbia|Victoria]] as the capital.\n|-\n|||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from the city of [[Quebec City|Qu\u00e9bec]] to [[Ottawa]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1865||align=center|11&nbsp;April||The '''[[Confederate States of America]]''' capitulates and is reabsorbed by the [[United States of America]]. The USA will readmit the 11 CSA states to full statehood between 24 July 1866, and 15 July 1870.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;April||The '''[[Confederate States of America]]''' moves its capital to [[Danville, Virginia]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;March||The '''[[Dominican Republic]]''' regains its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Santo Domingo]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||The '''[[Kingdom of Italy]]''' moves its capital from [[Turin]] to [[Florence]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1864||align=center|July||The [[Taiping Heavenly Kingdom]] is conquered by the [[Qing dynasty]] in [[China]].\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;May||Britain transfers the [[Ionian Islands]] to Greece\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;April||The '''[[Second Mexican Empire|Mexican Empire]]''' supersedes the [[Second Federal Republic of Mexico|United Mexican States]]. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1863||align=center|20&nbsp;June||The [[Union Army|Union]]-occupied northwestern counties of the Commonwealth of [[Virginia]] (which considered itself a part of the [[Confederate States of America]]) secede from the state and are admitted to the [[United States|United States of America]] as the '''[[U.S. state|State]] of [[West Virginia]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;July||The [[Northern Territory]] is annexed by the British colony of [[South Australia]] from the colony of [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;May||The [[Granadine Confederation]] becomes the [[United States of Colombia]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1862||align=center|12&nbsp;October||The '''[[State of Buenos Aires]]''' reunites with the [[Argentine Republic]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;October||[[Buenos Aires]] is declared provisional capital of the '''[[Argentine Republic]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||The British colony of [[Queensland]]'s western border is shifted from 141\u00b0E to 138\u00b0E\n|-\n| ||The [[United Kingdom]] creates the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[British Honduras]]''' at the Settlement of Belize in the Bay of Honduras. The capital is [[Belize City]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"25\"|1861||align=center|12&nbsp;December||The '''[[Argentine Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Argentine Confederation]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;December||The splinter government of [[Kentucky]] is admitted to the [[Confederate States of America]]\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||[[Paran\u00e1, Entre R\u00edos|Paran\u00e1]] is no longer the capital of the '''[[Argentine Confederation]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||The splinter government of [[Missouri]] is admitted to the [[Confederate States of America]]\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;November||A splinter government of [[Kentucky]] declares the state's secession from the United States of America\n|-\n|align=center|31&nbsp;October||A splinter government of [[Missouri]] declares the state's secession from the United States of America\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;September||After the [[Battle of Pav\u00f3n]] the Capital city of Argentina is moved to [[Buenos Aires]]\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;December||[[Confederate Arizona|Arizona Territory]] is annexed by the [[Confederate States of America]]\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;May||The '''[[Confederate States of America]]''' moves its capital from [[Montgomery, Alabama]], to [[Richmond, Virginia]].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;May||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[North Carolina]] secedes from the [[United States of America]] and joins the '''[[Confederate States of America]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;May||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Tennessee]] secedes from the [[United States of America]] and joins the '''[[Confederate States of America]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;May||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Arkansas]] secedes from the [[United States of America]] and joins the '''[[Confederate States of America]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;April||The [[U.S. state|Commonwealth]] of [[Virginia]] secedes from the [[United States of America]] and joins the '''[[Confederate States of America]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;March||[[Confederate Arizona|Arizona Territory]] secedes from the United States of America\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;March||The [[Kingdom of Italy]] is proclaimed in place of the [[Kingdom of Sardinia|Kingdom of Sardinia-Piedmont]]\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;February||[[Gaeta]] surrenders to [[Kingdom of Sardinia|Sardinia-Piedmont]]\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;February||The '''[[Confederate States of America]]''', formed from the seven seceding states, declare their independence from the [[United States of America]]. [[Montgomery, Alabama]], is the capital for three months. Four more [[slave state]]s will join by 20 May.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Texas]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Texas in the American Civil War|Republic of Texas]]'''. [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;January||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Louisiana]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Republic of Louisiana]]'''. [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana|Baton Rouge]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;January||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], as the independent '''[[Georgia in the American Civil War|State of Georgia]]'''. [[Milledgeville, Georgia|Milledgeville]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;January||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Alabama]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Alabama in the American Civil War|Alabama Republic]]'''. [[Montgomery, Alabama|Montgomery]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;January||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Florida]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Republic of Florida]]'''. [[Tallahassee, Florida|Tallahassee]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;January||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[Mississippi]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Republic of Mississippi]]'''. [[Jackson, Mississippi|Jackson]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| ||The '''[[Dominican Republic]]''' returns to [[Spain|Spanish]] rule.\n|-\n| ||The '''[[Principality of Monaco]]''' declares independence from the [[Second French Empire]]. Monaco itself is the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\"|1860||align=center|20&nbsp;December||The [[U.S. state|State]] of [[South Carolina]] secedes from the [[United States of America]], declaring itself the '''[[Republic of South Carolina]]'''. [[Columbia, South Carolina|Columbia]] remains the capital. Six more [[slave state]]s will secede by 1 February 1861.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;November||[[Kingdom of Sardinia|Sardinia-Piedmont]] annexes the Papal States of [[Umbria]] and [[Marche|The Marches]]\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;October||The [[Kingdom of Two Sicilies]] is annexed to [[Kingdom of Sardinia|Sardinia-Piedmont]], except for the Fortress of [[Gaeta]]\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;October||The [[Argentine Confederation|Argentine Nation]] becomes the [[Argentine Republic]]\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;June||France annexes the [[Duchy of Savoy]] ([[Treaty of Turin (1860)|Treaty of Turin]])\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;June||France annexes the [[County of Nice]] ([[Treaty of Turin (1860)|Treaty of Turin]])\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;March||The [[United Provinces of Central Italy]] are annexed by [[Sardinia-Piedmont]]\n|-\n| ||The British colony of [[South Australia]]'s western border is changed from 132\u00b0E to 129\u00b0E\n|-\n| ||[[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Kashmir and Jammu]] annexes [[Gilgit]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dsal.uchicago.edu/reference/gazetteer/pager.html?objectid=DS405.1.I34_V15_099.gif|title=Imperial Gazetteer2 of India, Volume 15, page 93 -- Imperial Gazetteer of India -- Digital South Asia Library|website=dsal.uchicago.edu|access-date=11 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221425/http://dsal.uchicago.edu/reference/gazetteer/pager.html?objectid=DS405.1.I34_V15_099.gif|archive-date=3 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|}\n\n====1850s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"7\"|1859||align=center|8 December||The [[Duchy of Parma]], the [[Duchy of Modena and Reggio]], the [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]], and the [[Papal Legations]] combine to form the Sardinian client state of the [[United Provinces of Central Italy]]\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;November||After the [[Battle of Cepeda (1859)|Battle of Cepeda]], the [[Buenos Aires Province|State of Buenos Aires]] rejoins the [[Argentine Confederation]]\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|10&nbsp;November||[[Austrian Empire|Austria]] cedes [[Lombardy]] from [[Kingdom of Lombardy-Venetia|Lombardy-Venetia]] to France ([[Treaty of Z\u00fcrich]])\n|-\n|France immediately cedes Lombardy to [[Kingdom of Sardinia|Sardinia-Piedmont]] ([[Treaty of Z\u00fcrich]])\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;June||[[Queen Victoria]] signs the Proclamation separating the colony of [[Queensland]] from British [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;January||[[Moldavia]] unites with [[Wallachia]] to form the [[Romanian United Principalities]] (later [[Romania]])\n|-\n| ||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from the city of [[Quebec City|Qu\u00e9bec]] back to [[Toronto]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"4\"|1858||align=center|2 August||The continental portion of Canada's part of [[Oregon Country]] organized as the [[Colony of British Columbia]]\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;May||The [[Qing dynasty]] of [[China]] cedes [[Outer Manchuria]] to the [[Russian Empire]] by the [[Treaty of Aigun]].\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;May||The [[Republic of New Granada]] becomes the [[Granadine Confederation]]\n|-\n| ||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from [[Toronto]] back to the city of [[Quebec City|Qu\u00e9bec]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"3\"|1856||align=center|30&nbsp;March|| Part of the territory ([[Southern Bessarabia]]) annexed by the [[Russian Empire]] in 1812 returns to [[Moldavia]] by the [[Treaty of Paris (1856)]]\n|-\n|align=center|1 January||The British colony [[Van Diemen's Land]] changes its name to [[Tasmania]]\n|-\n| ||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from the city of [[Quebec City|Qu\u00e9bec]] back to [[Toronto]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1855||align=center rowspan=\"2\"|7&nbsp;February||Russians in north of [[Sakhalin]] Island, Japanese in south, with no defined border between ([[Treaty of Shimoda]])\n|-\n|Russia recognizes Japanese sovereignty of the [[Kuril Islands]] from [[Iturup]] on southwards ([[Treaty of Shimoda]])\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1854||align=center|24 March||The '''[[Argentine Confederation]]''' moves its capital to [[Paran\u00e1, Entre R\u00edos|Paran\u00e1]].\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;February||The '''[[Orange Free State]]''' is established. [[Bloemfontein]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"3\"|1853||align=center|24&nbsp;June||The [[Gadsden Purchase]] gives a portion of southern [[Arizona]] and [[New Mexico]] from Mexico to the United States\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;May||The [[Argentine Confederation]] [[Argentine Constitution of 1853|becomes]] a [[Federal Republic]], renamed the [[Argentine Confederation|Argentine Nation]]\n|-\n|align=center|March||The [[Taiping Heavenly Kingdom]] establishes its capital at [[Nanjing|Tianjing]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1852||align=center|2&nbsp;December||The second '''[[French Second Empire|French Empire]]''' supersedes the second [[French Second Republic|French Republic]]. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;September||The [[Province of Buenos Aires]] secedes from the [[Argentine Confederation]] as the '''[[State of Buenos Aires]]'''. [[Buenos Aires]] remains the capital, the Confederation is without capital until 1854.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;February||The [[Battle of Caseros]] ends the [[Argentine Civil War]]. [[Entre R\u00edos Province|Entre R\u00edos]] and [[Corrientes Province|Corrientes]] rejoin the Argentine Confederation. The Capital city is moved to [[Paran\u00e1, Entre R\u00edos|Paran\u00e1]]\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;January||The '''[[South African Republic|South African Republic (Republic of Transvaal)]]''' is established. [[Pretoria]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from [[Toronto]] to the city of [[Quebec City|Qu\u00e9bec]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1851||align=center|1&nbsp;July||The colony of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] is split off from the British colony of [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;May||The [[Provinces of Argentina|Argentine Provinces]] of [[Entre R\u00edos Province|Entre R\u00edos]] and [[Corrientes Province|Corrientes]] secede from the [[Argentine Confederation]]\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;January||[[Hong Xiuquan]] establishes the '''[[Taiping Heavenly Kingdom]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|}\n\n====1840s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1849||align=center|13&nbsp;August||The '''[[Hungarian State (1849)|Hungarian State]]''' capitulates and is reabsorbed by the [[Austrian Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;July||The [[Papal States]] are restored as [[Roman Republic (19th century)|Rome]] falls\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;April||The '''[[Hungarian State (1849)|Hungarian State]]''' declares its independence from the [[Austrian Empire]]. [[Debrecen]] is the temporary capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;March||The [[Sikh Empire]] falls after the Sikh defeat in [[Anglo-Sikh wars]] and is merged in [[British India]]\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;February||Rebels under [[Giuseppe Garibaldi]] take over the area of the [[Papal States]] and create the [[Roman Republic (19th century)|Roman Republic]]\n|-\n| || The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from [[Montr\u00e9al]] to [[Toronto]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1848||align=center|24&nbsp;February||The second '''[[French Second Republic|French Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of France]]. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;February||The [[Second Mexican Republic|United Mexican States]] surrenders its [[Mexican Cession|northern territory]] to the '''[[United States of America]]''' with the [[Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo]] at the conclusion of the [[Mexican\u2013American War]].\n|-\n|align=center|1847||align=center|26&nbsp;July||The [[African American]] colony of [[Liberia]] declares its independence as the '''[[Republic of Liberia]]'''. [[Monrovia]] is the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1846||align=center|28&nbsp;November||The British colony of [[North Australia]] is reincorporated back into the colony of [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;August||The '''[[Second Mexican Republic|United Mexican States]]''' supersedes the [[Centralist Republic of Mexico|Mexican Republic]]. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;June||The [[Oregon Treaty]] establishes the [[49th parallel north]] west of the Lake of the Woods as the continental border between the Province of Canada and the United States.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;February||The colony of [[North Australia]] is separated from the British colony of [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n| ||The princely state of [[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Kashmir and Jammu]], ruled by the [[Dogra|Dogra Dynasty]], is created after the [[First Anglo-Sikh War|first Anglo-Sikh war]], as per the [[Treaty of Amritsar (1846)|Treaty of Amritsar.]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EqZFsNIuVWEC|title=Gilgit Agency 1877-1935Second Reprint|last=Chohan|first=Amar Singh|date=1 January 1997|publisher=Atlantic Publishers & Dist|isbn=9788171561469|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1845||align=center|29&nbsp;December||The [[Republic of Texas]] joins the '''[[United States of America]]''' as the [[State of Texas]]. [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] yields to [[Washington, DC|Washington]] as federal capital while remaining capital of the state.\n|-\n|||The [[Netherlands]] splits its colonial possessions in the [[Americas]] into two parts: '''[[Suriname]]''' and '''[[Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]]'''. [[Paramaribo]] remains the capital of Suriname, while [[Willemstad, Cura\u00e7ao|Willemstad]] on [[Cura\u00e7ao]] becomes the capital of the six Caribbean islands. \n|-\n|||The '''[[Kingdom of Hawai\u02bbi]]''' moves its capital from [[L\u0101hain\u0101, Hawai'i|L\u0101hain\u0101]] to [[Honolulu, Hawaii|Honolulu]].\n|-\n|||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the '''[[Falkland Islands]]''' from [[Port Louis, Falkland Islands|Port Louis]] to [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Stanley]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;March||The [[Riograndense Republic]] is reabsorbed by the '''[[Brazilian Empire]]''' as the province of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] again.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1844||||The [[United Kingdom]] moves the capital of the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]''' from [[Kingston, Ontario|Kingston]] to [[Montr\u00e9al]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;February||The '''[[Dominican Republic]]''' gains independence from [[Haiti]]. [[Santo Domingo]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1841||align=center|10&nbsp;February||The [[United Kingdom]] unites [[Upper Canada]] and [[Lower Canada]] as the [[Crown Colony]] of the '''[[United Province of Canada]]'''. [[Kingston, Ontario|Kingston]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;February||The sole remnant of the [[Federal Republic of Central America]] changes its name back to the '''[[Republic of El Salvador]]'''. [[San Salvador]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1840||align=center|16&nbsp;November||The colony of [[New Zealand]] is separated from the British colony of [[New South Wales]]\n|}\n\n====1830s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1839||align=center|17&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Guatemala]]''' secedes from the [[Federal Republic of Central America]]. [[Guatemala City]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;October||The '''[[Republic of Texas]]''' establishes its permanent capital at [[Austin, Texas|Austin]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;August||The '''[[Peruvian Republic]]''' and the '''[[Bolivian Republic]]''' are formed from the dissolution of the [[Peru-Bolivian Confederation]]. [[Lima]] and [[Sucre]] (previously [[Sucre|Chuquisaca]]) are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;July||The '''[[Juliana Republic]]''' declares independence from Brazil. [[Laguna, Santa Catarina|Laguna]] is the capital. The Republic capitulates and is reabsorbed later in the year.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;April|| The '''[[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]]''' becomes independent, but remains in the personal Union with the [[Netherlands]] as a result of the [[Treaty of London (1839)|Treaty of London]].\n|-\n|||The '''[[Principality of Serbia]]''' moves its capital from [[Kragujevac]] to [[Belgrade]].\n|-\n|align=center|1838||align=center|5&nbsp;November||The '''[[Republic of Costa Rica]]''', the '''[[Republic of Nicaragua]]''', and the '''[[Republic of Honduras]]''' secede from the [[Federal Republic of Central America]]. [[San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica|San Jos\u00e9]], [[Managua]], and [[Comayagua]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1836||align=center|28&nbsp;December||The colony of '''[[South Australia]]''' is separated from the [[United Kingdom|British]] colony of [[New South Wales]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;October||The [[Republic of North Peru]], the [[Republic of South Peru]], and the [[Bolivian Republic]] unite to form the '''[[Peru-Bolivian Confederation]]'''. [[Tacna]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;September||The '''[[Riograndense Republic]]''' declares independence from Brazil. [[Piratini]] is the first of five provisional capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||The '''[[Republic of North Peru]]''' supersedes the [[Peruvian Republic]]. [[Lima]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;March||The '''[[Republic of South Peru]]''' secedes from [[Peruvian Republic]]. [[Cusco]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;March||The '''[[Republic of Texas]]''' declares its independence from [[M\u00e9xico]]. [[Washington-on-the-Brazos|Washington]] is the first of six cities that will serve as temporary capital until 1839.\n|-\n|align=center|1835||align=center|23&nbsp;October||The '''[[Centralist Republic of Mexico|Mexican Republic]]''' supersedes the [[First Mexican Republic|United Mexican States]]. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1834||||The '''[[Federal Republic of Central America]]''' moves its capital from [[Guatemala City]] to [[San Salvador]].\n|-\n|||The '''[[Kingdom of Greece]]''' moves its capital from [[Nafplio]] to [[Athens]].\n|-\n|align=center|1833||align=center|3&nbsp;January||The [[United Kingdom]] [[Reassertion of British sovereignty over the Falkland Islands (1833)|removes a garrison]] installed by the [[United Provinces of the Rio de la Plata]] in October 1832 reasserting its sovereignty claim over the '''[[Falkland Islands]]''' ([[Islas Malvinas]]). [[Port Louis, Falkland Islands|Port Louis]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=7|1832||align=center|3 September||The [[province of Catamarca]] joins the [[Federal Pact]]. End of the [[Unitarian League]].\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;July||The [[province of Tucum\u00e1n]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;July||The [[province of Salta]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|May||The '''[[Kingdom of Greece]]''' supersedes the [[First Hellenic Republic]]. [[Nafplio]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|The [[Province of San Juan (Argentina)|province of San Juan]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;April||The [[province of San Luis]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|||The colony of '''[[Western Australia]]''' supersedes the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Swan River Colony]] in Australia.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=8|1831||align=center|20 October||The '''[[Republic of New Granada]]''' supersedes [[Gran Colombia]]. [[Bogot\u00e1]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||The [[La Rioja Province, Argentina|province of La Rioja]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;August||The [[Province of C\u00f3rdoba (Argentina)|province of C\u00f3rdoba]] and the [[Santiago del Estero Province|province of Santiago del Estero]] join the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;August||The [[province of Corrientes]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;August||The [[province of Mendoza]] joins the [[Federal Pact]].\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;July||[[Belgium]] becomes the '''[[Kingdom of Belgium]]'''. [[Brussels]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=2|4&nbsp;January||The [[United Kingdom]] combines [[Essequibo (colony)|Essequibo]]-[[Demerara]] and [[Berbice]] as the [[Crown Colony]] of [[British Guiana]]. [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]] is the capital.\n|-\n|Signing of the [[Federal Pact]] by the [[province of Buenos Aires]], the [[province of Entre R\u00edos]], and the [[province of Santa Fe]]. Beginning of the '''[[Argentine Confederation]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1830||align=center|4&nbsp;October||'''[[Belgium]]''' declares its independence from the [[United Kingdom of the Netherlands]]. [[Brussels]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;June||The '''[[Uruguay|Oriental State of Uruguay]]''' is created from the Government and Provisional General Captaincy of the Oriental State of Uruguay. [[Montevideo]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;May||The '''[[Republic of Ecuador]]''', and the '''[[Republic of Venezuela]]''' declare independence from [[Gran Colombia]]. [[Quito]], and [[Caracas]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;February||The [[Ottoman Empire]] recognizes the independence of '''[[First Hellenic Republic|Greece]]'''. [[Nafplio]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;July||The '''[[Unitarian League]]''' is created among the Argentine provinces of [[San Luis Province|San Luis]], [[La Rioja Province, Argentina|La Rioja]], [[Catamarca Province|Catamarca]], [[Mendoza Province|Mendoza]], [[San Juan Province, Argentina|San Juan]], [[Tucum\u00e1n Province|Tucum\u00e1n]], [[C\u00f3rdoba Province, Argentina|C\u00f3rdoba]], [[Salta Province|Salta]] and [[Santiago del Estero Province|Santiago del Estero]].\n|}\n\n====1820s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1829|| ||The British [[Swan River Colony]] is established in the west of Australia\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1828||style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|27&nbsp;August||The [[Banda Oriental]] gains independence from the [[United Provinces of the Rio de la Plata]] as '''[[Uruguay|Government and Provisional General Captaincy of the Oriental State of Uruguay]]'''. [[Montevideo]] is the capital.\n|-\n|[[Misiones Orientales]] are awarded to Brazil\n|-\n|align=center|1827||align=center|18&nbsp;August||The centralist and [[unitary state]] of the '''[[United Provinces of the R\u00edo de la Plata]]''' is dissolved. The [[Provinces of Argentina|Argentine Provinces]] resume their sovereignty delegating the foreign affairs on the [[Province of Buenos Aires]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1826||align=center|9&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of Chile]]''' supersedes the [[State of Chile]]. [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|8&nbsp;February ||The '''[[United Provinces of the R\u00edo de la Plata]]''' is proclaimed as a centralist and [[unitary state]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|1825||align=center|3 December||[[Van Diemen's Land]] is declared a separate British colony to [[New South Wales]]\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;November||The [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]] changes its name back to the '''[[Kingdom of Portugal and the Algarves]]'''. [[Lisbon]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;August||The [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]] recognizes the independence of the '''[[Empire of Brazil]]'''. [[Rio de Janeiro]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;August||'''[[Cisplatina]]''' declares its independence from the [[Empire of Brazil]] and reunites with the [[United Provinces of the Rio de la Plata]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||The '''[[Bolivian Republic]]''' gains independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]] at the conclusion of the [[Bolivian War of Independence]]. [[Sucre|Chuquisaca]] (later [[Sucre]]) is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;July||The border of the British colony of [[New South Wales]] is extended from 133\u00b0E to 129\u00b0E\n|-\n|align=center| ||The [[Netherlands]] administratively combines its three colonies of [[Suriname]], [[Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]] (the [[ABC islands (Lesser Antilles)|ABC islands]]), and [[Sint Eustatius and Dependencies]] (the [[SSS islands]]). The capital is [[Paramaribo]]. \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1824||align=center|9 December||The [[Battle of Ayacucho]] end the [[Spanish American wars of independence]] in [[South America]]\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;October||The '''[[First Mexican Republic|United Mexican States]]''' supersedes the [[Second Mexican Empire|Mexican Empire]] upon the execution of [[Maximilian I of Mexico|Emperor Maximilian I]]. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||[[Bolivia]] declares independence from Spain, and refuses to join either [[Peru]] or the [[United Provinces of South America]]\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;July||The '''[[Confederation of the Equator]]''' declares independence from Brazil. [[Recife]] is the capital, but the Confederation capitulates and is reabsorbed at the same year.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1823||align=center|July||The [[Republic of Guatemala]], the [[Republic of El Salvador]], the [[Republic of Nicaragua]], the [[Republic of Honduras]], and the [[Republic of Costa Rica]] unite to form the '''[[Federal Republic of Central America]]'''. [[Guatemala City]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;May||The '''[[Republic of Costa Rica]]''' moves its capital from [[Cartago, Costa Rica|Cartago]] to [[San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica|San Jos\u00e9]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1822||align=center|19&nbsp;December||The '''[[Peruvian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[State of Peru]]. [[Lima]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||The '''[[Empire of Brazil]]''' supersedes the [[Independent Kingdom of Brazil]]. [[Rio de Janeiro]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;September||The '''[[Independent Kingdom of Brazil]]''' declares its independence from the [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]]. [[Rio de Janeiro]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|9&nbsp;February||[[Haiti]] [[Unification of Hispaniola|annexes]] the '''[[Republic of Spanish Haiti]]'''. [[Santo Domingo]] yields to [[Port-au-Prince]] as the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"12\"|1821||align=center|1 December||The '''[[Republic of Spanish Haiti]]''' gains independence from [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Santo Domingo]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||Independence of [[Panama]] from Spain\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Costa Rica]]''' gains independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Cartago, Costa Rica|Cartago]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;September||The '''[[Republic of Guatemala]]''', the '''[[Republic of Honduras]]''', the '''[[Republic of Nicaragua]]''' and the '''[[Republic of El Salvador]]''' become independent from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Guatemala City]], [[Comayagua]], [[Managua]], and [[San Salvador]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;August||The [[Monarchy of Spain]] recognizes the independence of the '''[[First Mexican Empire|Mexican Empire]]'''. [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;August||[[Peru]] becomes the '''[[State of Peru]]'''. [[Lima]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;July||'''[[Peru]]''' declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Lima]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;July||'''[[Cisplatina]]''' formally declares itself as part of the [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;July||The '''[[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]]''' returns the capital from exile in [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]], to [[Lisbon]].\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;March||'''[[Greece]]''' declares its independence from the [[Ottoman Empire]]. [[Nafplion]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;February||'''[[The United States of America]]''' receives '''[[Florida]]''' from [[Spain]] in the [[Adams\u2013On\u00eds Treaty]]\n|-\n| ||[[Alaska Boundary Dispute]] with Russia and Great Britain begins\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1820||align=center|8&nbsp;October||The [[Kingdom of Haiti]] collapses upon the suicide of [[Henri Christophe|King Henri I]]. Haiti is unified under the '''[[Republic of Haiti]]''' with its capital at [[Port-au-Prince]].\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;February||[[Liga Federal|Federal League]] defeats the central government of the [[United Provinces of the R\u00edo de la Plata]] in the [[Battle of Cepeda (1820)|Battle of Cepeda]]. The Federal League is dissolved and the [[Provinces of Argentina|Argentine Provinces]] resume their sovereignty, delegating the foreign affairs on the [[Province of Buenos Aires]].\n|-\n|||The '''[[Kingdom of Hawai\u02bbi]]''' establishes its capital at [[L\u0101hain\u0101, Hawai'i|L\u0101hain\u0101]].\n|}\n\n====1810s====\n[[File:Non-Native American Nations Control over South America 1700 and on.gif|thumb|200px|Retreat of European colonialism and change of political borders in South America, 1700\u2013present]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1819||align=center|17&nbsp;December||[[Gran Colombia]] is established from the previous [[Second Republic of Venezuela]], [[United Provinces of New Granada]], and the [[Royal Audience of Quito|Presidency of Quito]]\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;August||The [[United Provinces of New Granada]] gains independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Bogot\u00e1]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"3\"|1817||align=center|5&nbsp;April||The [[Battle of Maip\u00fa]] secures Chilean independence from [[Spain]]\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;February||The '''[[State of Chile]]''' again declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;January||The [[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]] occupies the [[Banda Oriental]] ([[Uruguay]]) as '''[[Cisplatina]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=\"2\"|1816||align=center|9&nbsp;July||The '''[[United Provinces in South America]]''' ([[Argentina]], [[Bolivia]], and [[Uruguay]]) declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Buenos Aires]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;May||[[Spanish reconquest of New Granada]] ends the early [[Foolish Fatherland|Colombian independent governments]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"23\"|1815||align=center|16&nbsp;December||The '''[[United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of Portugal and the Algarves]]. [[Rio de Janeiro]] remains the capital-in-exile.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;November||[[Milo\u0161 Obrenovi\u0107]] establishes the '''[[Principality of Serbia]]'''. [[Kragujevac]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;June||The '''[[Liga Federal|Federal League]]''', an alliance of several [[Provinces of Argentina|Argentine Provinces]] and modern-day [[Uruguay]], is established.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;July||The restored '''[[Bourbon Restoration|Kingdom of France]]''' supersedes the first [[French First Empire|French Empire]]. Paris remains the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"15\"|9&nbsp;June||The [[Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia]] is formed from the Milanese and Venetian portions of the [[Kingdom of Italy (Napoleonic)|Kingdom of Italy]] and becomes a [[crown land]] of the [[Austrian Empire]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|Austria gains the territory of the former [[Republic of Ragusa]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|[[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]] is re-established and is given [[Piombino]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|The [[Duchy of Lucca]] is created in place of the former [[Republic of Lucca]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|The [[Duchy of Warsaw]] is partitioned into the [[Grand Duchy of Posen]] (Prussia), [[Congress Poland]] (Russia) and the [[Free City of Krak\u00f3w]] (jointly controlled by Prussia, Russia, and Austria) ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|Prussia is awarded [[Danzig]], much of the [[Kingdom of Saxony]], [[Westphalia]] and the [[Rhineland]]. ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|The [[United Kingdom of the Netherlands]] is created from the former [[Dutch Republic]] and [[Austrian Netherlands]], with [[Luxembourg]] in a personal union. ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|Swedish Pomerania is ceded to Prussia. ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|The [[Duchy of Lauenburg]] is ceded by [[Hanover]] to Denmark ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|Hanover becomes a [[Kingdom of Hanover|Kingdom]] annexes the former territories of the Bishop of M\u00fcnster and East Frisia ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|Bavaria gains the [[Palatinate (region)|Palatinate]] and parts of the [[Duchy of W\u00fcrzburg]] and [[Grand Duchy of Frankfurt]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|[[Hesse-Darmstadt]] gains [[Rhenish Hesse]] ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|British control of various colonies, including the [[Cape Colony]], [[Tobago]], and [[Ceylon]], is recognized ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|The [[United States of the Ionian Islands]] is formed as a British protectorate ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|'''[[German Confederation]]''' established. [[Frankfurt]] is the capital. ([[Congress of Vienna]])\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;March||The first '''[[French First Empire|French Empire]]''' supersedes the [[Bourbon Restoration|Kingdom of France]]. Paris remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;March||The '''[[United Kingdom of the Netherlands]]''' supersedes the [[Sovereign Principality of the United Netherlands]]. [[Amsterdam]] and [[Brussels]] are the joint capitals.\n|-\n| ||[[Sir Robert Brownrigg]] establishes the '''[[Crown Colony of Ceylon]]'''. [[Colombo]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n| ||The capital of [[Bermuda]] is moved from [[St. George, Bermuda|St George]] to [[Hamilton, Bermuda|Hamilton]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"11\"|1814||align=center|4&nbsp;November||The [[Kingdom of Norway (1814)|Kingdom of Norway]] joins a''' [[union between Sweden and Norway|personal union]]''' with the [[Sweden|Kingdom of Sweden]]. [[Stockholm]] and [[Oslo|Christiania]] are the capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;October||The '''[[Monarchy of Spain]]''' reconquers [[Chile]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;May||Norway declares full independence, electing its own king and adopting its own constitution.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;April||Napoleon abdicates from the [[Kingdom of Italy (Napoleonic)|Italian]] throne, effectively dissolving the Kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;April||The restored '''[[Bourbon Restoration|Kingdom of France]]''' supersedes the [[First French Empire]]. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;March||The Netherlands are reestablished from France as the [[Sovereign Princedom of the Netherlands]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;May||Denmark cedes Norway to Sweden through the [[peace of Kiel]].\n|-\n| ||Various Italian states are reinstated, including the [[Duchy of Modena and Reggio]] and the [[Papal States]].\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;May||The [[Kingdom of Sardinia]] reclaims its mainland territory and annexes the land of the former [[Republic of Genoa]]. (Ratified by the Congress of Vienna in 1815.)\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;January||The '''[[Kingdom of Norway (1814)|Kingdom of Norway]]''' secedes [[Denmark\u2013Norway]]. [[Oslo|Christiania]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||The '''[[Principality of Andorra]]''' declares independence from the [[First French Empire]]. [[Andorra la Vella]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1813||align=center|11&nbsp;December||The [[Treaty of Valen\u00e7ay]] ends formally the [[Peninsular War]], with the restoration of [[Ferdinand VII of Spain]] and releasing the country from being a [[client state]] of the Napoleonic [[First French Empire|French Empire]].\n|-\n|align=center|2&nbsp;December||The '''[[Sovereign Principality of the United Netherlands]]''' is created from the ruins of the first [[French First Empire|French Empire]]. [[Amsterdam]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;October||The '''[[Confederation of the Rhine]]''' dissolves.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;October||[[Paraguay]] becomes the '''[[Republic of Paraguay]]'''. [[Asunci\u00f3n]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;August||The [[Second Republic of Venezuela]] is declared\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;July||The [[United Kingdom|British]] '''[[Malta Colony]]''' supersedes the [[Malta Protectorate]]. [[Valletta]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1812||align=center|28 July||The [[First Republic of Venezuela]] is crushed by the [[Spanish Empire]]\n|-\n|align=center|28 May||The eastern portion of the [[Principality of Moldavia]] ([[Bessarabia]]) is ceded to the Russian Empire by the Ottoman Empire in the [[Treaty of Bucharest, 1812|Treaty of Bucharest]]\n|-\n|align=center|14 May||[[First French Empire|France]] annexes [[Catalonia]] from Spain, creating the d\u00e9partements of [[Bouches-de-l'\u00c8bre]], [[Montserrat (department)|Montserrat]], [[S\u00e8gre (department)|S\u00e8gre]] and [[Ter (department)|Ter]]. [[Andorra]] is also annexed and incorporated into the d\u00e9partement of S\u00e8gre.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1811||align=center|27&nbsp;November||The [[United Provinces of New Granada]] (modern [[Colombia]]) are established\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;July||[[Venezuela]] declares independence from Spain\n|-\n|align=center|14&nbsp;May||'''[[Paraguay]]''' gains independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Asunci\u00f3n]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;March||The '''[[Kingdom of Haiti]]''' supersedes the [[State of Haiti]]. [[Cap-Ha\u00eftien]] is the capital.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"10\"|1810||align=center|13&nbsp;December||France annexes northern Germany ([[Hamburg]], [[Bremen]], [[Free City of L\u00fcbeck|L\u00fcbeck]], [[Principality of Salm|Salm]], [[Arenberg]], [[Duchy of Oldenburg|Oldenburg]], parts of [[Kingdom of Westphalia|Westphalia]] and [[Berg (state)#French revolution, Grand Duchy of Berg|Berg]])\n|-\n|align=center|18&nbsp;September||'''[[Chile]]''' declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]]. [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;September||'''[[M\u00e9xico]]''' declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;July||'''[[Colombia]]''' declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]].\n|-\n|align=center|13&nbsp;July||The [[Kingdom of Holland]] ([[Netherlands]]) is annexed by the first '''[[French First Empire|French Empire]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;May||[[May Revolution]]. The Spanish viceroy in the [[Viceroyalty of the R\u00edo de la Plata]] ([[Argentina]], [[Bolivia]], [[Paraguay]], and [[Uruguay]]) is replaced by the [[Primera Junta]]. Creation of the '''[[United Provinces of the R\u00edo de la Plata]]'''. [[Buenos Aires]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|22&nbsp;May||By the terms of the [[Treaty of Paris (1810)|Treaty of Paris]], the [[Principality of Regensburg]] is formally incorporated into the [[Kingdom of Bavaria]]\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;April||The [[First Republic of Venezuela]] is established, starting the [[Venezuelan War of Independence]] from [[Spain]]\n|-\n|align=center|April||[[Kamehameha I]] unifies the '''[[Kingdom of Hawai\u02bbi]]'''.\n|-\n| ||The [[Rhodanic Republic]] is annexed by France and becomes the d\u00e9partement of [[Simplon (department)|Simplon]]\n|}\n\n====1800s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|1809|| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|14&nbsp;October||[[Salzburg]] is ceded to Bavaria ([[Treaty of Sch\u00f6nbrunn]])\n|-\n|[[West Galicia]] is ceded to the [[Duchy of Warsaw]] ([[Treaty of Sch\u00f6nbrunn]])\n|-\n|[[Tarnopol]] is ceded to the Russian Empire ([[Treaty of Sch\u00f6nbrunn]])\n|-\n|[[Trieste]] and [[Croatia]] south of the [[Sava]] are ceded to France; these become the [[Illyrian provinces]] ([[Treaty of Sch\u00f6nbrunn]])\n|-\n|align=center|17&nbsp;September||Sweden officially cedes Finland to Russia through the [[peace of Hamina]]\n|-\n|align=center|29&nbsp;March||The Russian Tsar is declared Grand-duke of Finland, effectively separating Finland from Sweden and turning it into a Russian autonomous duchy\n|-\n| ||Napoleon dissolves the [[Teutonic Knights]]; their lands are redistributed between neighboring states of the Holy Roman Empire, mostly to [[W\u00fcrttemberg]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1808||align=center|7&nbsp;March||The '''[[Kingdom of Portugal and the Algarves]]''' removes the capital from [[Lisbon]] to exile in [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]].\n|-\n| ||[[Spain]] becomes a [[client state]] of the [[First French Empire]] after the country was partially occupied by French forces and [[Joseph Bonaparte|Joseph I]] set as king by [[Napoleon Bonaparte|Napoleon]].\n|-\n|align=center|1807||align=center|July||Napoleon creates the [[Duchy of Warsaw]] from land ceded by the [[Kingdom of Prussia]] by the [[Treaties of Tilsit]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1806||align=center|17&nbsp;October||The [[First Empire of Haiti|Empire of Haiti]] collapses upon the assassination of [[Jean-Jacques Dessalines|Emperor Jacques I]]. Haiti splits in two with the '''[[State of Haiti]]''' in the north with its capital at [[Milot, Haiti|Milot]], and the '''[[Republic of Haiti]]''' in the south with its capital at [[Port-au-Prince]].\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;August||[[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor]], dissolves the '''[[Holy Roman Empire of the German Nation]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;July||[[Napoleon I of France]] establishes the '''[[Confederation of the Rhine]]'''. [[Frankfurt]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;June||The '''[[Kingdom of Holland]]''' ([[Netherlands]]) supersedes the [[Batavian Republic]]. [[Amsterdam]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;January||The [[United Kingdom]] establishes the '''[[Cape Colony]]'''. [[Cape Town]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1805||align=center|July||France annexes the [[Principality of Piombino]] and the [[Republic of Lucca]] and reconstitutes them as the [[Principality of Lucca and Piombino]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1804||align=center|22&nbsp;September||[[Jean-Jacques Dessalines]] establishes the '''[[First Empire of Haiti|Empire of Haiti]]'''. [[Port-au-Prince]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;August||[[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor]], establishes the '''[[Austrian Empire]]'''. [[Vienna]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|18 May||The first '''[[French First Empire|French Empire]]''' supersedes the first [[French First Republic|French Republic]]. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;March||The [[French First Republic|French Republic]] [[Louisiana Purchase|sells]] '''[[Louisiana (New France)|Louisiane]]''' to the [[United States of America]]. [[New Orleans]] ([[Nouvelle-Orl\u00e9ans]]) is the capital of the unorganized territory.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The French colony of [[Saint-Domingue]] on [[Hispaniola]] declares its independence from the [[French First Republic|French Republic]] as '''[[Haiti]]'''. [[Port-au-Prince]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1803||align=center|27&nbsp;April||As a result of the [[Reichsdeputationshauptschluss]], all but three ([[Archbishopric of Regensburg]], and the lands of the [[Teutonic Knights]] and [[Knights of Saint John]]) ecclesiastical states of the Holy Roman Empire are either secularized or annexed by other states. The [[Duchy of Salzburg]] (formerly the [[Archbishopric of Salzburg]]) is also raised to an [[prince-elector|electorate]].\n|-\n|align=center|19&nbsp;February||The [[Act of Mediation]] converts the Helvetic Republic into the [[Swiss Confederation (Napoleonic)|Swiss Confederation]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1802||||Napoleon separates the Canton of Valais from the Helvetic Republic to form the [[Rhodanic Republic]]\n|-\n|||[[Gia Long]] establishes the '''[[Nguy\u1ec5n dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Hu\u1ebf]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1801||align=center|20&nbsp;August||'''[[Gozo (independent state)|The Gozitan Nation]]''' is annexed by the [[Malta Protectorate|British protectorate of Malta]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|6&nbsp;June||The [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] signs the [[Treaty of Badajoz (1801)|Treaty of Badajoz]]. Spain cedes the South American '''[[Misiones Orientales]]''' to Portugal.\n|-\n|The [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] signs the [[Treaty of Badajoz (1801)|Treaty of Badajoz]]. Portugal cedes '''[[Olivenza]]''' to Spain.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;January||The [[Kingdom of Great Britain]] and the [[Kingdom of Ireland]] unite to form the '''[[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]]'''. [[Dublin]] yields to [[London]] as the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1800||align=center|17&nbsp;November||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its capital from [[Philadelphia]] to its permanent location at [[Washington, D.C.|Washington]] in the [[Washington, D.C.|District of Columbia]].\n|-\n|align=center|5&nbsp;September||French forces in [[French occupation of Malta|Malta]] surrender to the British. The island becomes the '''[[Malta Protectorate|British protectorate of Malta]]''' with [[Valletta]] as capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1&nbsp;October||After a secretly negotiated treaty between France and Spain, Spain returns the colony of Louisiana to France\n|-\n|align=center|1800||align=center|17&nbsp;February||The French d\u00e9partement of [[Mont-Terrible]] is merged into the d\u00e9partement of [[Haut-Rhin]]5\n|}\n\n===18th century===\n====1790s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1799||align=center|7&nbsp;July||Establishment of the [[Sikh Empire]] after capture of [[Lahore]] by [[Ranjit Singh|Maharaja Ranjit Singh]] and unification of the [[Sikh Confederacy]] under him.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1798||align=center|28&nbsp;October||'''[[Gozo (independent state)|The Gozitan Nation]]''' gains ''de facto'' independence from [[French occupation of Malta|Malta]] with [[Victoria, Gozo|Rabat]] as its capital.\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;June||The [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] capitulates to French forces and '''[[Malta]]''' is under [[French occupation of Malta|French occupation]] with [[Valletta]] remaining the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|12&nbsp;April||The Napoleonic [[Helvetic Republic]] is declared\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;January||France annexes [[Mulhouse]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1797||align=center|17&nbsp;April||The [[House of Habsburg]] annexes the '''[[Republic of Venice]]'''.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|18&nbsp;October||The [[Austrian Netherlands]] and various Mediterranean islands, including [[Corfu]], are ceded to France. ([[Treaty of Campo Formio]])\n|-\n|The [[Republic of Venice]] is dissolved. Venetia (the eastern portion of [[Domini di Terraferma]], roughly modern [[Veneto]] and [[Friuli-Venezia Giulia]]), [[Istria]] and [[Dalmatia]] are annexed by Austria ([[Treaty of Campo Formio]])\n|-\n|Austria recognizes the [[Cisalpine Republic]] and [[Ligurian Republic]] ([[Treaty of Campo Formio]])\n|-\n|The [[Kingdom of Italy (Holy Roman Empire)|Kingdom of Italy]] is recognized as defunct and all subordinate territories are formally released from the Holy Roman Empire ([[Treaty of Campo Formio]])\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1795||align=center|19&nbsp;January||The '''[[Batavian Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Republic of the Seven United Netherlands]]. [[Amsterdam]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|24&nbsp;October||The [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]] is [[Third partition of Poland|partitioned]]. Its vassal state [[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]] and the former [[Bishopric of Courland]], until then in [[personal union]] with Poland-Lithuania, are annexed to the [[Russian Empire]] together as its [[Courland Governorate]].\n|-\n| ||France annexes [[Southern Netherlands]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1793||align=center|25&nbsp;June||[[Avignon]] is transferred from the [[Papal States]] to France\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;March||The [[Rauracian Republic]] is annexed by France to form the d\u00e9partement of [[Mont-Terrible]]\n|-\n|align=center|2 March||France annexes the Principality of [[Salm-Salm]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1792||align=center|17&nbsp;December||Most of the [[Prince-Bishopric of Basel]] becomes the Napoleonic [[Rauracian Republic]], retaining only Schliengen\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;September||The first '''[[French First Republic|French Republic]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of France]]. [[Paris]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|23&nbsp;January||[[Second partition of Poland]]\n|-\n|align=center|1791||align=center|4&nbsp;March||The [[Vermont Republic]] joins the '''[[United States of America]]''' as the [[State of Vermont]]. [[Windsor, Vermont|Windsor]] yields to [[Philadelphia]] as the federal capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1790||align=center|7&nbsp;December||The [[United States of Belgium]] capitulates to the '''[[House of Habsburg]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|6&nbsp;December||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[New York City]] to [[Philadelphia]] pending the construction of the new capital permitted by the new [[United States Constitution]].\n|-\n|align=center|11&nbsp;January||The '''[[United States of Belgium]]''' declares its independence from the [[House of Habsburg]]. [[Brussels]] is the capital.\n|}\n\n====1780s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:15%\"|Date||style=\"width:79%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1789||||The [[L\u00ea dynasty|Later L\u00ea dynasty]] of Vietnam collapses.\n|-\n|align=center|1788||align=center|26&nbsp;January||British colony of [[New South Wales]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|1785||align=center|11&nbsp;January||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Trenton, New Jersey|Trenton]] to [[New York City]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1784||align=center|1&nbsp;November||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis]] to [[Trenton, New Jersey|Trenton]].\n|-\n|align=center| ||[[Joseph II, Holy Roman Emperor|King Joseph II]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1526\u20131867)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' back to [[Buda]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1784||align=center|1&nbsp;July||King Gustav III of Sweden acquires the island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] in the Caribbean from France. It becomes a Swedish colony for nearly a century, until it is sold back to France in 1878.\n|-\n|align=center| ||Russian seafarer and merchant [[Grigory Shelikhov|Grigory Ivanovich Shelikhov]] arrives in [[Three Saints Bay]] in Alaska\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1783||align=center|26&nbsp;November||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Princeton, New Jersey|Princeton]] to [[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;September||The [[Kingdom of Great Britain]] signs the [[Treaty of Paris (1783)|Treaty of Paris]], recognizing the independence of the '''[[United States of America]]'''. [[Princeton, New Jersey|Princeton]] remains the temporary capital.\n|-\n|align=center|26&nbsp;November||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Philadelphia]] to [[Princeton, New Jersey|Princeton]].\n|-\n|align=center|20&nbsp;January||Great Britain surrenders [[East Florida]] and [[West Florida]] to Spain\n|-\n|align=center|{{OldStyleDate|19 April||8 April}}||The [[Crimean Khanate]] is annexed by the Russian Empire and incorporated as the [[Taurida Governorate]]\n|-\n|align=center| ||'''[[Province of Trinidad]]''' moves its capital from [[Saint Joseph, Trinidad and Tobago|San Jos\u00e9 de Oru\u00f1a]] to [[Port of Spain|Puerto de Espa\u00f1a]], its present location.\n|-\n|align=center|1782||align=center|21 April||'''[[Siam]]''' moves its capital from Thonburi to [[Bangkok]], its present location.\n|}\n\n====1770s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1778||||[[Nguy\u1ec5n Nh\u1ea1c|Th\u00e1i \u0110\u1ee9c]] establishes the '''[[T\u00e2y S\u01a1n dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1778||align=center|27&nbsp;July||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[York, Pennsylvania|York]] back to [[Philadelphia]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\"|1777||align=center|1 October||The [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] sign the [[First Treaty of San Ildefonso]], confirming almost all the borders defined by the [[Treaty of Madrid (13 January&nbsp;1750)|Treaty of Madrid]], with the exception that Spain would rule both [[Colonia del Sacramento]] and the [[Misiones Orientales]].\n|-\n|align=center|30&nbsp;September||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Lancaster, Pennsylvania|Lancaster]] to [[York, Pennsylvania|York]].\n|-\n|align=center|27&nbsp;September||'''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Philadelphia]] to [[Lancaster, Pennsylvania|Lancaster]] for one day, following the capture of Philadelphia by British forces.\n|-\n|align=center|8&nbsp;July||The [[Republic of New Connecticut]] changes its name to the '''[[Vermont Republic]]'''. [[Windsor, Vermont|Windsor]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;June||The '''[[Republic of New Connecticut]]''' moves its capital to [[Windsor, Vermont|Windsor]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;March||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital back from [[Baltimore]] to [[Philadelphia]].\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;January||The '''[[Republic of New Connecticut]]''' declares its independence from the [[Kingdom of Great Britain]]. [[Westminster, Vermont|Westminster]] is the temporary capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1776||align=center|20&nbsp;December||The '''[[United States of America]]''' moves its temporary capital from [[Philadelphia]] to [[Baltimore]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;July||The '''[[United States of America]]''' (including the [[Rhode Island|State of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations]]) declares its independence from the [[Kingdom of Great Britain]]. [[Philadelphia]] is the first of eight cities that will serve as a temporary capital until 1800. \n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;May||'''[[Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations|Rhode Island and Providence Plantations]]''' declares its independence from the [[Kingdom of Great Britain]]. [[Providence, Rhode Island|Providence]] is the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1775||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] reunites its South American colonies of the [[Colony of Brazil|State of Brazil]], the [[Colony of Brazil|State of Great-Par\u00e1]], and the [[Colony of Brazil|State of Maranh\u00e3o]] into the '''[[Colony of Brazil]]'''. [[Rio de Janeiro]] is the capital. \n|-\n| ||The [[Habsburg Monarchy]] annexes the northwestern part of [[Moldavia]] (which becomes known as [[Bukovina]]).\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1772 || ||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] divides its colony of the [[Colony of Brazil|State of Great-Par\u00e1 and Maranh\u00e3o]] into the '''[[Colony of Brazil|State of Great-Par\u00e1]]''' (capital, [[Bel\u00e9m]]) and the '''[[Colony of Brazil|State of Maranh\u00e3o]]''' (capital, [[S\u00e3o Lu\u00eds, Maranh\u00e3o|S\u00e3o Luis]]). \n|-\n| ||[[Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya (city)|Ayutthaya]] having been destroyed in 1767, the new capital of '''[[Siam]]''' is created in [[Thonburi]].\n|-\n|align=center|5 August||[[First Partition of Poland|First partition]] of [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth|Poland]]\n|}\n\n====1760s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1768||align=center|21&nbsp;December||[[Prithvi Narayan Shah]] unifies the '''[[Kingdom of Nepal]]'''. [[Kathmandu]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|15&nbsp;May||[[Republic of Genoa|Genoa]] sells to France its rights to [[Corsica]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1763||align=center|12&nbsp;February||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] moves the capital of its colony of the '''[[Colonial Brazil|State of Brazil]]''' from [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]] to [[Rio de Janeiro]].\n|-\n|align=center|10&nbsp;February||The [[Treaty of Paris (1763)|Treaty of Paris]] creates a number of territory transfers between Great Britain, France, and Spain. [[New France]] (Canada) now belongs to the British.\n|-\n|align=center|1762|| ||The [[Louisiana Territory]] is transferred from France to Spain in the [[Treaty of Fontainebleau (1762)|Treaty of Fontainebleau]]\n|-\n|align=center|1761||align=center|12&nbsp;February||The [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] sign the [[Treaty of El Pardo (1761)|Treaty of El Pardo]], nullifying the [[Treaty of Madrid (13 January&nbsp;1750)|Treaty of Madrid]].\n|}\n\n====1750s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1758||||The [[Dzungar Khanate]] is annexed by the [[Qing dynasty]] of [[China]].\n|-\n|align=center|1752||||[[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] becomes a colony of [[British North America]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buzzle.com/articles/history-of-the-13-colonies.html|title=History of the 13 Colonies|author=Loveleena Rajeev|work=Buzzle|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414022601/http://www.buzzle.com/articles/history-of-the-13-colonies.html|archive-date=14 April 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1751||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] changes the name of its colonial [[Colonial Brazil|State of Maranh\u00e3o]] to '''[[Colonial Brazil|State of Great-Par\u00e1 and Maranh\u00e3o]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|21&nbsp;September||Through the [[Treaty of Str\u00f6mstad]], the border between Sweden and Norway is finally settled, from the beginning of the land border in [[Iddefjord]] until Norway's border on Russia at [[Varanger Peninsula|Varanger]] (since Finland was part of Sweden at this time, the border between the two countries continued beyond the present end point of the border between Norway and Sweden).\n|-\n|align=center|1750||align=center|13&nbsp;January||The [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] signs the [[Treaty of Madrid (13 January&nbsp;1750)|Treaty of Madrid]]. Based on the ''uti possidetis'' concept, Portugal gains lands on the actual south, central and north regions of Brazil. The treaty also stipulated that Spain would receive the [[Colonia del Sacramento]] and Portugal the [[Misiones Orientales]].\n|}\n\n====1740s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1747||||[[Safavid Empire]] collapses<ref>Beck, Roger et al.(2008). ''World History: Patterns of Interaction''. p. 513</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|October||The [[Durrani Empire]] is founded near [[Kandahar]] on a [[Loya jirga]], when [[Ahmad Shah Abdali]] is chosen as the king of the newly independent empire. He is later regarded as the founder of modern [[Afghanistan]].\n|-\n|align=center|1740||||[[Prussia]] annexes [[Silesia]] from Austria\n|}\n\n====1730s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1737||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] moves the capital of its colonial '''[[Colonial Brazil|State of Maranh\u00e3o]]''' from [[S\u00e3o Lu\u00eds, Maranh\u00e3o|S\u00e3o Lu\u00eds]] to [[Bel\u00e9m]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1739||style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|18 September||The Habsburg Monarchy cedes the Kingdom of Serbia, the southern part of the Banat of Temeswar and northern Bosnia to the Ottoman Empire ([[Treaty of Belgrade]])\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eef;\"|The Habsburg Monarchy returns [[Lesser Walachia]] (Oltenia) to [[Wallachia]] ([[Treaty of Belgrade]])\n|-\n|align=center|1 January||[[Jean-Baptiste Charles Bouvet de Lozier]] discovers [[Bouvet Island]] in the South Atlantic Ocean\n|}\n\n====1720s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1729||||[[North Carolina]] and [[South Carolina]] become royal colonies, due to the division of the [[Province of Carolina]]\n|-\n|align=center|1728||||On [[Greenland]] (then part of [[Denmark-Norway]]), [[Hans Egede]] founds the colony of [[Nuuk|Godth\u00e5b]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1721||align=center|22 October||[[Peter the Great]] proclaims the Tsardom of Russia an [[Russian Empire|Empire]]\n|-\n|align=center|30 August|| [[Duchy of Estonia (1561\u20131721)|Swedish Estonia]], [[Swedish Ingria|Ingria]], [[Swedish Livonia|Livonia]], and most of [[Karelia]] is ceded by [[Swedish Empire|Sweden]] to the [[Tsardom of Russia]] according to the terms of the [[Treaty of Nystad]].\n|-\n|align=center|1720||align=center|21 January||Sweden cedes the portion of Swedish Pomerania south of the [[Peene]] and east of the [[Peenestrom]] to Prussia\n|}\n\n====1710s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1719||align=center|9&nbsp;November||Sweden cedes [[Bremen-Verden]] to the [[Electorate of Hanover]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|1718||style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|21&nbsp;July||The Ottoman Empire cedes to the Habsburg Monarchy the [[Banat]], southeastern [[Syrmia]], central Serbia, and part of northern [[Bosnia]], while part of [[Wallachia]] (an Ottoman vassal) known as the [[Lesser Wallachia]] (Oltenia) is also ceded to the Habsburg Monarchy ([[Treaty of Passarowitz]])\n|-\n|The [[Kingdom of Serbia (1718\u201339)|Kingdom of Serbia]] is established as a Habsburg crown land ([[Treaty of Passarowitz]])\n|-\n|The [[Banat of Temeswar]] is established as a Habsburg crown land ([[Treaty of Passarowitz]])\n|-\n|Venice return [[Morea]] (gained by the Treaty of Karlowitz) and its [[Crete|Cretan]] holdings to the Ottomans.\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire cede parts of Dalmatia ([[Imotski]], [[Sinj]], and [[Vrgorac]]).\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |1717||||The former [[Bishopric of Courland]], until then in [[personal union]] with the [[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]], it in turn a vassal state of the [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]], comes into [[personal union]] directly with Poland-Lithuania.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1715||||The [[Kingdom of Spain]] returns '''[[Colonia del Sacramento]]''' to the [[Kingdom of Portugal]].\n|-\n|align=center|28&nbsp;November||[[Kingdom of Castile]] integrates the [[Kingdom of Majorca]], the last part of the [[Crown of Aragon]], through invasion\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1714||align=center|11 September||Fall of the [[Crown of Aragon]] invaded by [[Kingdom of Castile]] marked by the invasion of the City of [[Barcelona]] ([[Siege of Barcelona (1713\u20131714)|Siege of Barcelona]]). Creation of a unified [[Kingdom of Spain]] through the [[Nueva Planta decrees]].\n|-\n|align=center|7&nbsp;September||The [[Duchy of Milan]] is ceded to the Habsburg Monarchy\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1713||align=center|March&nbsp;and April||The [[Treaty of Utrecht]] is signed. The [[United Kingdom]] takes sovereignty over [[Gibraltar]] and [[Menorca]] from the [[Kingdom of Spain]]. Spain also ceded: [[Sicily]] and parts of the [[Duchy of Milan]] to [[Savoy]]; [[Spanish Netherlands]], the [[Kingdom of Naples]], [[Sardinia]], and the bulk of the [[Duchy of Milan]] to [[Charles VI, Holy Roman Emperor]]; lands in South America between [[Amazon River]] and [[Oiapoque River]] to the [[Kingdom of Portugal]].\n|-\n| ||[[Gibraltar]] passes from Spain to Great Britain\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1711|| ||The Principality of Transylvania is integrated ''de jure'' into the Habsburg Monarchy as a [[crown land]] ([[Principality of Transylvania (1711\u20131867)]])\n|-\n|align=center | 21&nbsp;July||The Russian Empire returns [[Azov]] to the Ottoman Empire by the [[Treaty of the Pruth]]\n|}\n\n====1700s====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1707||align=center|1 May||The [[Kingdom of England]] and the [[Kingdom of Scotland]] unite to form the '''[[Kingdom of Great Britain]]'''.<ref>[http://www.parliament.uk/actofunion/ Welcome] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081015044930/http://www.parliament.uk/actofunion/ |date=15 October 2008 }} parliament.uk, accessed 30 July 2009</ref> [[Edinburgh]] yields to London as the capital for all but judicial functions.\n|-\n|align=center|25&nbsp;April||[[Kingdom of Castile]] integrates the [[Kingdom of Valencia]] part of the [[Crown of Aragon]] through invasion ([[Battle of Almansa]])\n|-\n|align=center|1 May||The creation of the [[Kingdom of Great Britain]] through the [[Acts of Union 1707|Acts of Union]]\n|}\n\n===17th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1700||||The Ottoman Empire cedes [[Azov]] to the Russian Empire by the [[Treaty of Constantinople (1700)|Treaty of Constantinople]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|1699||style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|26&nbsp;January||The Ottoman Empire cede the [[E\u011fri Eyalet]], the [[Varat Eyalet]], northern parts of the [[Teme\u015fvar Eyalet]], most of the [[Budin Eyalet]] and parts of the [[Bosnia Eyalet]] to the Habsburg Monarchy. This territory plus the [[Principality of Transylvania (1570\u20131711)|Principality of Transylvania]] corresponds to most of the territory of mediaeval Hungary previously lost to the Ottomans ([[Ottoman Hungary]]). ([[Treaty of Karlowitz]])\n|-\n|The Principality of Transylvania, while nominally independent, comes ''de facto'' under Habsburg rule.([[Treaty of Karlowitz]])\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire return [[Podolia]] to Poland-Lithuania.([[Treaty of Karlowitz]])\n|-\n|The Ottoman Empire cede the [[Morea]] and most of Dalmatia to the Republic of Venice.([[Treaty of Karlowitz]])\n|-\n|align=center|1684||||The [[Kingdom of England|English]] [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Bermuda]]''' supersedes the [[Somers Isles Company]]. [[Hamilton, Bermuda|Hamilton]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1685||||[[New York (state)|New York]] becomes a royal colony\n|-\n|align=center|1682||||[[Robert de La Salle]] sails down the [[Mississippi River]]<ref>Beck, Roger et al.(2008). ''World History: Patterns of Interaction''. p. 555</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|1681||||[[Pennsylvania]] becomes a colony\n|-\n|align=center|1677||||The [[M\u1ea1c dynasty]] of Vietnam collapses.\n|-\n|align=center|1674||||Shivaji founded Maratha Empire in Maharashtra\n|-\n|align=center|1664||||[[New Jersey]] founded\n|-\n|align=center|1663||||[[Rhode Island]] becomes a colony\n|-\n|align=center|1662||||[[Connecticut]] becomes a British royal colony\n|-\n|align=center|1661||align=center|25&nbsp;February||The former [[Bishopric of Courland]], a vassal state of the [[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]], it in turn a vassal state of the [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]], comes into [[personal union]] with Courland and Semigallia.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1661||||[[Aurangzeb]] of the Mughal Empire gives the port of [[Bombay]] to the British\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|1660||align=center|27 May||The [[Kingdom of Sweden]] cedes [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] to the '''[[Denmark-Norway|Kingdom of Denmark and Norway, the Wends and the Goths]]''' as part of the [[Treaty of Copenhagen (1660)|Treaty of Copenhagen]].\n|-\n|align=center|3&nbsp;May||The [[Treaty of Oliva]] cedes [[Ruhnu|Run\u00f6]] Island in Estonia from the [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth|Polish-Lithuanian]] vassal state [[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]] to [[Sweden]].\n|-\n|align=center|4&nbsp;April||The restored '''[[Kingdom of England]]''', '''[[Kingdom of Scotland]]''', and '''[[Kingdom of Ireland]]''' supersede the [[Republicanism in the United Kingdom|republican]] [[Commonwealth of England, Scotland and Ireland]]. [[London]], [[Edinburgh]], and [[Dublin]] are the respective capitals.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1658||align=center|26&nbsp;February||The [[Denmark-Norway|Kingdom of Denmark and Norway, the Wends and the Goths]] cedes [[Scania|Sk\u00e5ne]], [[Blekinge]], [[Halland]], [[Bornholm]], [[Bohusl\u00e4n|B\u00e5hus]] and [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] to the [[Kingdom of Sweden]] as part of the [[Treaty of Roskilde]].\n|-\n|align=center|16&nbsp;December||The '''[[Commonwealth of England, Scotland and Ireland]]''' supersedes the [[Commonwealth of England]], the [[Kingdom of Scotland]], and the [[Kingdom of Ireland]]. [[Edinburgh]] and [[Dublin]] yield to [[London]] as the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1658||align=center|26&nbsp;February||Sweden gains in Danish-Norwegian regions of [[Blekinge]], [[Bornholm]], [[Bohusl\u00e4n|Bohusl\u00e4n (B\u00e5huslen)]], [[Scania|Scania (Sk\u00e5ne)]] and [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] and the [[Second Treaty of Br\u00f6msebro (1645)|30 year ownership]] of [[Halland]] is made permanent in the [[treaty of Roskilde]]\n|-\n|align=center|1656||||The former [[Bishopric of Courland]], until then in [[personal union]] with the [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]], is sold to the Polish-Lithuanian vassal state [[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]] and becomes its vassal state instead.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1653||align=center|4 May||The precise borders between Swedish Pomerania and Farther Pomerania (Brandenburg-Prussia) are determined in the [[Treaty of Stettin (1653)|Treaty of Stettin]]\n|-\n|align=center|1649||align=center|19 May||The [[Republicanism in the United Kingdom|republican]] '''[[Commonwealth of England]]''' supersedes the [[Kingdom of England]]. [[London]] remains the capital.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1648|| ||The [[Dutch Republic|Netherlands]], Switzerland, and many [[Italian city-states]] are made independent of the [[Holy Roman Empire]]\n|-\n|| ||The [[Duchy of Pomerania]] is divided between Sweden ([[Swedish Pomerania]]) and Brandenburg-Prussia ([[Farther Pomerania]]), although the precise borders would not be determined until 1653\n|-\n|align=center|1645||align=center|13&nbsp;August||The [[Denmark-Norway|Kingdom of Denmark and Norway, the Wends and the Goths]] cedes [[J\u00e4mtland]], [[H\u00e4rjedalen]], [[\u00c4lvdalen Municipality|Idre & S\u00e4rna]], [[Gotland]], [[Saaremaa|\u00d6sel]] and [[Halland]], the latter for a period of 30 years, to the [[Kingdom of Sweden]] as part of the [[Second Treaty of Br\u00f6msebro (1645)|Treaty of Br\u00f6msebro]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1644||align=center|30&nbsp;October||The [[Qing dynasty]] supersedes the [[Ming dynasty]] as the legitimate dynasty of [[China]].\n|-\n|||[[Zhu Yousong|Hongguang]] establishes the '''[[Southern Ming|Southern Ming dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1640||align=center|1&nbsp;December||Portugal separates from [[personal union]] with Spain\n|-\n|align=center|1638||||[[Delaware]] founded\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1636||||[[Hong Taiji|Taizong]] establishes the '''[[Qing dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[England]] establishes the [[Crown Colony]] of '''[[Connecticut]]'''. [[Hartford]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1635||||[[Fasilides of Ethiopia|Fasilides]] makes [[Gondar]] the first permanent capital of '''[[Ethiopia]]''' since the fall of the [[Zagwe Dynasty]]\n|-\n|align=center|1634||||[[Maryland]] founded\n|-\n|align=center|1629||align=center|26&nbsp;September||The [[Truce of Altmark]] cedes most of the [[Duchy of Livonia]] in [[real union]] with [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]] to [[Sweden]] as [[Swedish Livonia]]. The eastern part of the duchy is retained by Poland-Lithuania and is annexed as the [[Inflanty Voivodeship]].\n|-\n|align=center|1628||||The '''[[Barbados#British colonial rule|Colony of Barbados]]''' moves its capital from [[Holetown|Saint James Town]] to [[Bridgetown]].\n|-\n|align=center|1627||||The [[Kingdom of England]] establishes the '''[[Barbados#British colonial rule|Colony of Barbados]]''' with its capital at [[Holetown|Saint James Town]].\n|-\n|align=center|1626||||Dutch purchase [[Manhattan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thirteen.org/dutchny/interactives/manhattan-island/#.UIW9crQTsxc|title=Document: The Purchase of Manhattan Island, 1626 - Dutch New York|work=Dutch New York|last=Schaghen|first=P.|date=5 November 1626|access-date=21 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024054842/http://www.thirteen.org/dutchny/interactives/manhattan-island/#.UIW9crQTsxc|archive-date=24 October 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|align=center|1623||||[[New Hampshire]] founded\n|-\n|align=center|1621||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] divides the [[Colony of Brazil]] into the '''[[State of Brazil]]''' (capital, [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]]) and the '''[[State of Maranh\u00e3o (colonial)|State of Maranh\u00e3o]]''' (capital, [[S\u00e3o Lu\u00eds, Maranh\u00e3o|S\u00e3o Luis]]). \n|-\n|align=center|1620||||[[Massachusetts]] founded\n|-\n|align=center|1617||align=center|9&nbsp;May||The [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth|Polish-Lithuanian]] vassal state [[Bishopric of Courland]] comes into [[personal union]] with Poland-Lithuania.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1617||align=center|27&nbsp;February||In the [[treaty of Stolbovo]] Sweden gained the Russian province and fortress of [[Kexholm]] (K\u00e4kisalmi, now [[Priozersk]]) and the province of [[Duchy of Ingria|Ingria]] including the fortress of [[N\u00f6teborg Fortress|N\u00f6teborg]] (now [[Shlisselburg]], Russia)\n|-\n|align=center|1616||align=center|30&nbsp;October||[[Nurhaci|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Later Jin (1616\u20131636)|Later Jin dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1612||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] reunites [[Governorate General of Bahia|North Brazil]] and [[Governorate General of Rio de Janeiro|South Brazil]] into the '''[[Colony of Brazil]]'''. The capital is [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]].\n|-\n|align=center|1610|| ||[[Henry Hudson]] discovers [[Hudson Bay]]\n|-\n|align=center|1608||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] divides the [[Colony of Brazil]] into '''[[Governorate General of Bahia|North Brazil]]''' (capital, [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]]) and '''[[Governorate General of Rio de Janeiro|South Brazil]]''' (capital, [[Rio de Janeiro]]) for the second time. \n|-\n|align=center|1607||||[[Jamestown, Virginia|Jamestown]] and Virginia Colony founded\n|-\n|align=center|1601||align=center|17&nbsp;January||France gains [[Bresse]], [[Bugey]], and [[Pays de Gex|Gex]] from [[Savoy]], and cedes [[Saluzzo]] to Savoy in exchange\n|}\n\n===16th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event|||Map\n|-\n|align=center|1598||||[[Kuchum]], Khan of [[Khanate of Sibir|Sibir]] is killed in battle with Russian forces, thus completing the Russian conquest of Siberia.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1596||||[[Willem Barentsz]] makes the first indisputable discovery of the [[Svalbard]] archipelago|||\n|-\n|align=center|1594||||[[Virmadhalasuriya I of Sri Lanka]] moves the capital of the '''[[Sri Lanka#Early modern Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' to [[Kandy]]|||\n|-\n|align=center|1591||||*Moroccans conquer [[Songhai Empire|Timbuktu]]<ref>Beck, Roger et al.(2008). ''World History: Patterns of Interaction''. p. 417</ref>|||\n|-\n|align=center|1585||||The [[Treaty of Kronborg]] cedes the nominally [[Denmark|Danish]], but [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth|Polish-Lithuanian]]-controlled former [[Bishopric of Courland]] formally to Poland-Lithuania.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1584||align=center|20&nbsp;March||Areas under [[Sweden|Swedish]] control in Northern Estonia are annexed as the [[Duchy of Estonia (1561\u20131721)|Duchy of Estonia]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1583||align=center|10&nbsp;August||The [[Treaty of Plussa]] cedes all the remaining [[Tsardom of Russia|Russia]]n-controlled areas in former [[Medieval Livonia|Livonia]] to [[Sweden]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1582||align=center|15&nbsp;January||The [[Truce of Yam-Zapolsky]] cedes the [[Tsardom of Russia|Russia]]n-controlled areas in former Central and Southern [[Medieval Livonia|Livonia]] to the [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1581||align=center|26&nbsp;July||The '''[[Republic of the Seven United Netherlands]]''' declares its independence from the [[Monarchy of Spain]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1581||align=center|14&nbsp;January||The [[Treaty of Drohiczyn]] cedes the [[free imperial city]] of [[Riga]] into the [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth|Polish-Lithuanian]] [[Duchy of Livonia]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1580||align=center|July||[[Yermak Timofeyevich]] invades the territory of the [[Mansi people|Voguls]], beginning the Russian conquest of Siberia.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1580||align=center|July||[[Personal union]] of Spain and Portugal|||\n|-\n|align=center|1578||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] reunites [[Governorate General of Bahia|North Brazil]] and [[Governorate General of Rio de Janeiro|South Brazil]] into the '''[[Colony of Brazil]]'''. The capital is [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1578||||The [[Denmark|Danish]]-controlled [[Bishopric of Courland]] becomes a vassal state of the [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1577||||The [[Tsardom of Russia|Russia]]n vassal state [[Kingdom of Livonia]] is disestablished.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1575||||The capital of [[Chile]] is moved from [[Concepci\u00f3n, Chile|Concepci\u00f3n]] to [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]||[[File:OrteliusWorldMap.jpeg|thumb|200px|Historical map of the world by [[Abraham Ortelius|Ortelius]], 1570 CE]]\n|-\n|align=center|1573||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] divides the [[Colony of Brazil]] into '''[[Governorate General of Bahia|North Brazil]]''' (capital, [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]]) and '''[[Governorate General of Rio de Janeiro|South Brazil]]''' (capital, [[Rio de Janeiro]]). |||\n|-\n|align=center|1572||align=center|9&nbsp;May||The [[Denmark|Danish]]-controlled former [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]] is annexed as [[Duchy of Estonia (1219\u20131346)|Danish \u00d6sel]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1571||align=center|18&nbsp;March||The [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] moves the capital of '''[[History of Malta under the Order of Saint John|Malta]]''' from [[Birgu]] to [[Valletta]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1570||align=center|13&nbsp;December||[[Denmark]] cedes its nominal rights over [[Hiiumaa|Dag\u00f6]] and the [[Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth]] its nominal rights over [[Harju County|Harrien]]-[[Virumaa|Wierland]] (including [[Tallinn|Reval]]), [[J\u00e4rva County|Jerwen]] and [[L\u00e4\u00e4ne County|Wiek]] to [[Sweden]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1570||align=center|10&nbsp;June||The '''[[Kingdom of Livonia]]''' is established as a vassal state of [[Tsardom of Russia|Russia]] in some of its conquered lands in [[Medieval Livonia|Livonia]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1569||align=center|1&nbsp;July||The [[Kingdom of Poland (1385-1569)|Kingdom of Poland]] and the [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]] unite to form the '''[[Commonwealth of the Crown of the Polish Kingdom and Grand Duchy of Lithuania]]'''. [[Vilnius]] yields to [[Krak\u00f3w]] as the capital.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1566||align=center|25&nbsp;December||The [[Union of Grodno (1566)|Union of Grodno]] turns the [[personal union]] between the [[Duchy of Livonia|Principality of Livonia]] and [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]] into a [[real union]] and the former is reorganized as the '''[[Duchy of Livonia]]'''. The Lithuanian vassal state [[Archbishopric of Riga]] is annexed to the Duchy of Livonia.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1564|| ||The Bailiff of [[Maasi#Maasilinna Castle|Soneburg]] of the former [[Livonian Order]], now the [[Duchy of Livonia|Principality of Livonia]] (later Duchy of Livonia), sells its bailiwick in the [[West Estonian archipelago]] to the [[Denmark|Danish]]-controlled former [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]]. In return, Denmark cedes its nominal rights over [[Sweden|Swedish]]-controlled [[L\u00e4\u00e4ne County|Wiek]] to the Lithuanian Principality of Livonia.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1563|| ||[[Sweden]] conquers from [[Denmark]] the former [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]] areas in [[L\u00e4\u00e4ne County|Wiek]] and [[Hiiumaa|Dag\u00f6]], leaving Denmark only with its possessions in [[\u00d6sel]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1561||align=center|28&nbsp;November||The [[Treaty of Vilnius (1561)|Treaty of Vilnius]] dissolves the [[Livonian Order]], which is in part organized as the [[Duchy of Livonia|Principality of Livonia]] in [[personal union]] with [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania|Lithuania]], and in part organized as the Lithuanian vassal state '''[[Duchy of Courland and Semigallia]]''', taking effect on 5 March 1562. The [[Archbishopric of Riga]] also becomes a vassal state of Lithuania and the former [[Condominium (international law)|condominium]] town of '''[[Riga]]''' becomes a [[free imperial city]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1561||align=center|6&nbsp;June||The northern [[Livonian Order]] town [[Tallinn|Reval]] pledges allegiance to [[Sweden]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1561||align=center|4&nbsp;June||The northern [[Livonian Order]] regions of [[Harjumaa|Harrien]]-[[Virumaa|Wierland]] (without [[Reval]]) and [[J\u00e4rvamaa|Jerwen]] pledge allegiance to [[Sweden]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1560||align=center|20&nbsp;May||The [[Bishopric of Courland]] in Western Latvia is sold to [[Denmark]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1559||align=center|November||The [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]] in Western Estonia is sold to [[Denmark]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1558||align=center|18&nbsp;July||[[Tsardom of Russia|Russia]] conquers the [[Bishopric of Dorpat]] in [[Estonia]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1558||||The '''[[Nguy\u1ec5n lords]]''' establishes ''de facto'' control over Central and Southern Vietnam.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1549||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] establishes a central government for its '''[[Colony of Brazil]]''', with [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]] as the capital.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1545||||The '''[[Tr\u1ecbnh lords]]''' establishes ''de facto'' control over Northern Vietnam.|||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1542||||The '''[[Kingdom of Ireland]]''' supersedes the [[feudal]] [[Lordship of Ireland]]. [[Dublin]] remains the capital.|||\n|-\n|||The [[Kingdom of England]] annexes the '''[[Principality of Wales]]'''.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1536||||[[Ferdinand I, Holy Roman Emperor|King Ferdinand I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1526\u20131867)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' to [[Pozsony]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1534||||The [[Kingdom of Portugal]] divides its '''[[Colony of Brazil]]''' into 15 independent captaincies.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1533||||The '''[[L\u00ea dynasty|Later L\u00ea dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]''' is restored under [[L\u00ea Trang T\u00f4ng|Trang T\u00f4ng]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1532||||The [[Early Modern France|Kingdom of France]] annexes the '''[[Duchy of Brittany]]'''.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1532||||[[Francisco Pizzaro]] conquers the [[Inca]]|||\n|-\n|align=center|1530||26 October||The [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]] annexes '''[[History of Malta under the Order of Saint John|Malta]]''' and moves the capital from [[Mdina]] to [[Birgu]].|||\n|-\n|align=center|1529||align=center|22&nbsp;April||Representatives of the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] and the [[Kingdom of Spain]] sign the [[Treaty of Zaragoza]], settling the countries' boundary of conquest in [[Asia]] and [[Oceania]] at a [[Meridian (geography)|meridian]] about 144\u00b040' west of [[Prime meridian|Greenwich]].)|||\n|-\n|align=center|1527||||[[M\u1ea1c Th\u00e1i T\u1ed5|Th\u00e1i T\u1ed5]] establishes the '''[[M\u1ea1c dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.|||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1526|| ||[[Babur]] of the [[Mughal Empire]] defeats the sultan of [[Delhi]]|||\n|-\n|||[[Ferdinand I, Holy Roman Emperor|Archduke Ferdinand of Austria]] is elected the next King of [[Kingdom of Bohemia|Bohemia]] and [[Kingdom of Hungary (1301-1526)|Hungary]] following the death of [[Louis II of Hungary and Bohemia]], uniting the lands which would come to be known as the [[Habsburg Monarchy]] under a single ruler|||\n|-\n|align=center|1525||align=center|14 January||The [[Teutonic Order]] relinquishes its rights over its autonomous '''[[Livonian Order]]'''.|||\n|-\n|align=center|1522|| ||[[Ferdinand Magellan]] circumnavigates the Earth|||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1521||align=center|13&nbsp;August||The combined forces of [[Hern\u00e1n Cort\u00e9s]] conquer [[Tenochtitlan]], capital of the [[Aztec Empire]]. The [[Kingdom of Spain]] subsequently renames the region '''[[New Spain]]'''. The destroyed capital is rebuilt and renamed [[Mexico City|M\u00e9xico]].|||\n|-\n|||[[Mayadunne of Sri Lanka|King Mayadunne I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Sri Lanka#Early modern Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' to [[Sitawaka]].|||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1513|| ||[[Juan Ponce de Le\u00f3n]] claims Florida for Spain|||\n|-\n|||[[Vasco N\u00fa\u00f1ez de Balboa]] crosses the Isthmus of Panama|||\n|-\n|align=center|1504|| ||The [[Kingdom of Naples]] is ceded to the Crown of Aragon|||\n|-\n|align=center|1501|| ||[[Jo\u00e3o da Nova]] discovers [[Ascension Island]]|||\n|-\n|align=center|1500||align=center|22&nbsp;April||Portuguese navigator [[Pedro \u00c1lvares Cabral]] arrives at the coast of Brazil and claims all land in [[South America]] east of the [[Tordesillas Meridian]] for the [[Kingdom of Portugal]], thus establishing the Portuguese '''[[Colonial Brazil|Colony of Brazil]]'''.|||\n|}\n\n===15th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1499-1501|| ||[[Safavid Empire|Safavids]] conquer [[Persia]]\n|-\n|align=center|1495||align=center|7&nbsp;June||Representatives of the [[Kingdom of Spain]] and the [[Kingdom of Portugal]] sign the [[Treaty of Tordesillas]], settling the countries' boundary of conquest in the [[Americas]] (and [[Africa]] and [[Asia]]) at a [[Meridian (geography)|meridian]] about 46\u00b00' west of [[Prime meridian|Greenwich]].\n|-\n|align=center|1493||align=center|4&nbsp;May||[[Spain|Spanish]] [[Pope Alexander VI]] issues the [[papal bull]] ''[[Inter caetera]]'' granting to the Crowns of [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] and [[Crown of Aragon|Aragon]] ([[Spain]]) all newly discovered lands west of the [[Meridian (geography)|meridian]] 100 [[League (unit)|league]]s west of any of the islands of the [[Azores]] (approximately 38\u00b011' west of [[Prime meridian|Greenwich]].)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |1492||align=center|12&nbsp;October||While seeking a route to the [[East Indies]], [[Genoa|Genoese]] navigator ''[[Christopher Columbus|Cristoforo Colombo]]'' (Christopher Columbus) lands on the island of [[Guanahani]] in the [[Lucayan Archipelago]],<ref name=\"EB-online\">[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/127070/Christopher-Columbus%20 Christopher Columbus] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216155719/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/127070/Christopher-Columbus%20 |date=16 December 2014 }} Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica. 2010. ''Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica Online.'' 8 June 2010.</ref> which he mistakes for the [[Japanese Archipelago]]. Columbus claims the archipelago for his patrons the Crowns of [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] and [[Crown of Aragon|Aragon]] ([[Spain]]), and subsequently explores and claims [[Cuba]] and [[Hispaniola]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |3 May||[[Christopher Columbus]] arrives at [[Jamaica|Xamayca]].\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" |1490|| ||[[Vladislaus II of Hungary|King Vladislaus II]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1301\u20131526)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' back to [[Buda]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |20 May||[[Vasco da Gama]] discovers the sea route to India\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |2 January||The combined forces of [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] and [[Aragon]] captured the [[Emirate of Granada]], completing the [[Spain]]'s [[Reconquista]].\n|-\n|align=center|1488||||[[Bartolomeu Dias]] rounds the Cape of Good Hope\n|-\n|align=center|1485||||[[Matthias Corvinus|King Matthias I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1301\u20131526)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' to [[Vienna|B\u00e9cs]].\n|-\n|align=center|1482||||The [[Burgundian Netherlands]] are disestablished\n|-\n|align=center|1481||||France gains the County of [[Provence]]\n|-\n|align=center|1480||||According to temple records, a cyclone destroys the landbridge connecting the [[Kingdom of Kandy]] and [[India|Mainland India]] ([[Adam's Bridge]]).\n|-\n|align=center|1478||||Commenced the completion of the conquest of the [[Canary Islands]] by [[Catholic Monarchs]]' [[Spain]].\n|-\n|align=center|1472||||The [[Kingdom of Scotland]] annexes [[Orkney]] and [[Shetland]].\n|-\n|align=center|1469||||The crowns of the [[Iberian Peninsula|Iberian]] [[Christians|Christian]] kingdoms of [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] and [[Aragon]] were united by the marriage of [[Isabella I of Castile]] and [[Ferdinand II of Aragon]], the [[Catholic Monarchs]].\n|-\n|align=center|1459||||The [[Teutonic Order]] cedes its already leased-out former [[Danish Estonia]] over to its autonomous [[Livonian Order]].\n|-\n|align=center|1453||align=center|29 May||The '''[[Byzantine Empire]]''' falls to the [[Ottoman Empire]]. The capital of the Ottoman Empire is moved to [[Constantinople]], present day [[Istanbul]]. Silk Road closed to trade causing European merchants to seek sea routes to Asian markets thus opening the \"age of discovery.\"\n|-\n|align=center|1452||||The [[Archbishopric of Riga]] and the autonomous [[Livonian Order]] of the [[Teutonic Order]] agree with a [[Condominium (international law)|condominium]] over the nominally [[Independent city|free town]] of [[Riga]], until then ''de facto'' controlled by the Livonian Order. \n|-\n|align=center|1444||align=center|March||The [[Albanian Principalities]] are unified to form the Albanian Confederate of [[League of Lezhe]].\n|-\n|align=center|1435||align=center|1 September||The [[Archbishopric of Riga]], the bishoprics of [[Bishopric of Courland|Courland]], [[Bishopric of Dorpat|Dorpat]] and [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek|\u00d6sel-Wiek]], the autonomous [[Livonian Order]] of the [[Teutonic Order]], and the town of [[Riga]] form the '''[[Livonian Confederation]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1434||||The [[Archbishopric of Riga]] sells its [[Dundaga Castle|Dondangen Parish]] to the [[Bishopric of Courland]].\n|-\n|align=center|1432||align=center|March||[[Burgundy]] acquires the [[County of Hainaut]]\n|-\n|align=center|1428||||[[L\u00ea L\u1ee3i|Th\u00e1i T\u1ed5]] establishes the '''[[L\u00ea dynasty|Later L\u00ea dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Hanoi|\u0110\u00f4ng Kinh]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1427||||End of the [[Fourth Chinese domination of Vietnam]].\n|-\n|align=center|1415||align=center|21 August||The [[Conquest of Ceuta]] marks the beginning of the [[Portuguese Empire]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1413||align=center|7 June||The autonomous '''[[Livonian Order]]''' of the [[Teutonic Order]] becomes ''de facto'' independent from its parent order.\n|-\n|||The [[Ming dynasty]] of China defeats the [[Later Tr\u1ea7n dynasty]] of Vietnam.\n|-\n|align=center|1412||||[[Parakramabahu VI of Sri Lanka|King Parakramabahu VI]] moves the capital of '''[[Sri Lanka#Medieval Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' to [[Kotte]].\n|-\n|align=center|1408||||[[Sigismund, Holy Roman Emperor|King Zsigmond of Luxemburg]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1301\u20131526)|Hungarian Kingdom]]''' back to [[Buda]].\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1407||||The [[Ming dynasty]] of China conquers the [[H\u1ed3 dynasty]] of Vietnam. Start of the [[Fourth Chinese domination of Vietnam]].\n|-\n|||[[Gi\u1ea3n \u0110\u1ecbnh \u0110\u1ebf|Gi\u1ea3n \u0110\u1ecbnh]] establishes the '''[[Later Tr\u1ea7n dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1400||||[[H\u1ed3 Qu\u00fd Ly]] establishes the '''[[H\u1ed3 dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Citadel of the H\u1ed3 Dynasty|T\u00e2y \u0110\u00f4]] is the capital.\n|}\n\n===14th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1392||||The '''[[Joseon Dynasty]]''' succeed the [[Goryeo Dynasty]] of [[Korea]]. [[Seoul|Hanseong]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1384||||The [[Burgundian Netherlands]] are established.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|1368||||[[Hongwu Empero