reaty of Almizra]]\n|-\n|align=center|1238||align=center|7 June||The Treaty of Stensby returns [[Danish Estonia]] from the [[Livonian Order]] back to [[Denmark]], while the order retains [[J\u00e4rva County|Jerwen]].\n|-\n|align=center|1238||||[[Sweden]] conquers central Finland.\n|-\n|align=center|1238||||The [[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]] cedes some area in and around [[Lihula|Leal]] in Western Estonia to the autonomous [[Livonian Order]] of the [[Teutonic Order]].\n|-\n|align=center|1237||align=center|12 May||The [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]] are incorporated into the [[Teutonic Order]] as the autonomous [[Livonian Order]].\n|-\n|align=center|1236||||Mongols invade Northern Korea\n|-\n|align=center|1235||||Aragon conquers [[Ibiza]], which becomes part of the Kingdom of Majorca\n|-\n|align=center|1235||align:center|September||[[Kingdom of Mali]] established\n|-\n|align=center|1234||align:center|24 July||The '''[[Bishopric of Courland]]''' is established from the Western Latvian territory of the [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]].\n|-\n|align=center|1231||||Aragon completes the [[Conquest of Majorca]] and [[Menorca]], establishing the Kingdom of Majorca as part of the Crown of Aragon\n|-\n|align=center|1228||align:center|August||The '''[[Bishopric of \u00d6sel-Wiek]]''' is established from the Western Estonian territory of the [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]]. Some of its land is ceded to the [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]].\n|-\n|align=center|1227||align:center|February||The [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]] and the [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]] subjugate [[Saaremaa]], the last independent [[Estonians|Estonian]] county and the Sword Brothers conquer [[Danish Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1225||||[[Tr\u1ea7n Th\u00e1i T\u00f4ng|Th\u00e1i T\u00f4ng]] establishes the '''[[Tr\u1ea7n dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1225||||The town of '''[[Riga]]''' gains independence from the [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]].\n|-\n|align=center|1224||align:center|August||The [[Bishopric of Dorpat|Bishopric of Estonia]] is renamed the '''[[Bishopric of Dorpat]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1224||align:center|24 July||The [[Bishopric of Dorpat|Bishopric of Estonia]] cedes [[L\u00e4\u00e4ne County|Wiek]] to the [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]].\n|-\n|align=center|1224||align:center|21 July||The [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]] cede Southern Estonia to the [[Bishopric of Dorpat|'''Bishopric of Estonia''']] (established in 1211). The bishopric returns some of the lands to the Sword Brothers.\n|-\n|align=center|1223||||Mongols defeat East Slavic warriors\n|-\n|align=center|1220||||[[Vijayabahu III of Sri Lanka|King Vijayabahu III]] moves the capital of the '''[[Sri Lanka#Medieval Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' to [[Dambadeniya]].\n|-\n|align=center|1219||||[[Denmark]] annexes the Northern Estonian counties of '''[[Revala]]''', '''[[Harjumaa (ancient county)|Harju County]]''', '''[[Viru County]]''' and '''[[J\u00e4rva County]]''' as the [[Danish Estonia|Duchy of Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1218||||The '''[[Principality of Wales]]''' is recognized in the [[Llywelyn the Great#Treaty of Worcester an border campaigns 1216.E2.80.931229|Treaty of Worcester]].\n|-\n|align=center|1217||||'''[[Kingdom of Serbia (medieval)|Serbian Kingdom]]''' established.\n|-\n|align=center|1216||||The '''[[Principality of Wales]]''' is founded at the [[History of Gwynedd during the High Middle Ages#Aberdyfi, Worcester, and Strata Florida; 1216-1240|Council of Aberdyfi]].\n|-\n|align=center|1216||||The [[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]] establish first presence in Southern [[Estonia]].\n|-\n|align=center|1210||||The [[Mongol Empire]] captures much of the [[Qara Khitai|Western Liao dynasty]].\n|-\n|align=center|1207||align:center|August||The [[Archbishopric of Riga|Bishopric of Riga]] cedes one third of its lands to the '''[[Livonian Brothers of the Sword]]''' (established in 1202).\n|-\n|