s disestablished\n|-\n|align=center|1127||||[[Emperor Gaozong of Song|Gaozong]] establishes the '''[[Song dynasty#Southern Song, 1127\u20131279|Southern Song dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Hangzhou|Lin'an]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1124||||[[Yel\u00fc Dashi|Dezong]] establishes the '''[[Qara Khitai|Western Liao dynasty]]''' in what is now Northwest China and Central Asia. [[Balasagun]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1115||||[[Emperor Taizu of Jin|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Jin dynasty (1115\u20131234)|Jin dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|}\n\n===11th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|1097||||[[William II of England|King William II]] moves the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of England]]''' to London.\n|-\n|align=center|1092||||[[William Rufus]], son of William the Conqueror, invades [[Cumberland]] (then part of Scotland) and incorporates it into England.\n|-\n|align=center|1091||||[[Noto]], Sicily is conquered by the County of Sicily, ending the Muslim Emirate of Sicily\n|-\n|align=center|1088||||The [[Principality of Taranto]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|1076||||Muslim [[Almoravids]] conquer [[Kingdom of Ghana|Ghana]]. \n|-\n|align=center|1076||||The kingdoms of Pamplona and Aragon are reunited (in a personal union) under [[Sancho Ram\u00edrez]], who styled himself \"King of the Aragonians and Pamplonese\". The two kingdoms are now ''de jure'' separate entities\n|-\n|align=center|1076||||Muslims conquer Syria\n|-\n|align=center|1076||||[[Palermo]], the capital of the [[Emirate of Sicily]] is taken by the Normans. The Norman [[County of Sicily]] is established.\n|-\n|align=center|1066||||England is conquered by [[William the Conqueror|William, Duke of Normandy]], thus bringing England and the [[Duchy of Normandy]] into a personal union\n|-\n|align=center|1065||||The kingdoms of [[Kingdom of Castile|Castile]] and [[Kingdom of Galicia|Galicia]] are split from the Kingdom of Le\u00f3n\n|-\n|align=center|1065||||The [[Duchy of Limburg]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|1061||||[[Estonians]] reconquer [[Ugandi County]] from the [[Kievan Rus']]\n|-\n|align=center|1061||||[[Messina]], Sicily is captured from the Muslims by the Normans\n|-\n|align=center|1059||||The [[County of Apulia and Calabria]] is raised to a Duchy by the Pope\n|-\n|align=center|1055||||[[Vijayabahu I of Sri Lanka|King Vijayabahu I]] moves the capital of the '''[[Sri Lanka#Medieval Sri Lanka|Kingdom of Sri Lanka]]''' to [[Polonnaruwa]].\n|-\n|align=center|1018-1054||||At some point between 1018 and 1054 the [[Kingdom of Strathclyde]] is conquered by Scotland\n|-\n|align=center|1043||||[[Kingdom of Aragon]] becomes ''de facto'' independent from the Kingdom of Pamplona\n|-\n|align=center|1042||||The Norman County of Apulia and Calabria is established\n|-\n|align=center|1038||||[[Emperor Jingzong of Western Xia|Jingzong]] establishes the '''[[Western Xia|Western Xia dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Xingqing Prefecture|Xingqing]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|1035||||The territory that would come to be the Kingdom of Aragon is united under [[Ramiro I of Aragon]]\n|-\n|align=center|1032||||[[Kingdom of Arles]] is inherited by [[Conrad II, Holy Roman Emperor]] and incorporated in the Holy Roman Empire.\n|-\n|align=center|1030||||[[Kievan Rus']] conquers [[Ugandi County]] in Southeastern Estonia.\n|-\n|align=center|1018||||English (Northumbrian) land north of the [[River Tweed|Tweed]] is ceded to Scotland\n|-\n|align=center|1009||||[[L\u00fd Th\u00e1i T\u1ed5|Th\u00e1i T\u1ed5]] establishes the '''[[L\u00fd dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|1000||||[[Stephen I of Hungary|King Stephen I]] establishes the '''[[Kingdom of Hungary (1000\u20131301)|Hungarian Kingdom]]'''. [[Esztergom]] and [[Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]] are the official capitals.\n|-\n|align=center|1000||||[[Gunnbj\u00f6rn Ulfsson]] spots islands off the coast of [[Greenland]]. European discovery of the island itself is dated to the 980s, when explorers arrived from [[Iceland]] and Norway.\n|-\n|align=center|1000||||[[Leif Ericson]] discovers [[Newfoundland]] and establishes a short-lived colony at [[L'Anse aux Meadows]].\n|}\n\n==1st Millennium CE==\n===10th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|987||||[[Hugh Capet|Hughe Capet]] confirmes [[Paris]] as the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of the West Franks]]''' (soon to become the '''[[Kingdom of France]]''').\n|-\n|align=center|980||||[[L\u00ea Ho\u00e0n]] establishes the '''[[Early L\u00ea dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Hoa L\u01b0]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|975||||[[Erik Segers\u00e4ll]] becomes first king of [[Sweden]]\n|-\n|align=center|968||||[[\u0110inh B\u1ed9 L\u0129nh]] establishes the '''[[\u0110inh dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[Hoa L\u01b0]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|965||||The [[Ng\u00f4 dynasty]] of Vietnam collapses.\n|-\n|align=center|962||align=center|2&nbsp;February||[[Otto the Great]] re-establishes the '''[[Holy Roman Empire]]'''. Rome is the official capital.\n|-\n|align=center|960||align=center|3&nbsp;January||[[Emperor Taizu of Song|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Northern Song Dynasty|Northern Song dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Kaifeng|Bianjing]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|ca. 965||align=center| ||The Byzantine Empire establishes the theme of [[Lucania]].\n|-\n|align=center|ca. 965||align=center| ||The Byzantine Empire establishes the [[Catepanate of Italy]].\n|-\n|align=center|ca. 965||align=center| ||The [[Kalbids]] take the last remaining Byzantine territory in Sicily.\n|-\n|align=center|962||align=center| ||King Otto I of Germany and Italy has himself crowned [[Holy Roman Emperor]] by the Pope, thereby forming the [[Holy Roman Empire]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|961||||[[Otto I, Holy Roman Emperor|King Otto I of Germany]] invades the [[Kingdom of Italy (Holy Roman Empire)|Kingdom of Italy]] (of which his wife [[Adelaide of Italy]] was already queen) and is crowned King.\n|-\n|||The [[Kingdom of Nri]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|959||align=center| ||[[Lower Lorraine]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|954||align=center| ||[[Scandinavian York|The Viking Kingdom of J\u00f3rv\u00edk]] (the Viking-ruled portion of the Kingdom Northumbria) is conquered by England, thus ending the [[Danelaw]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|951||||[[Guo Wei|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Later Zhou|Later Zhou dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Kaifeng]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||[[Liu Chong|Shizu]] establishes '''[[Northern Han]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Taiyuan]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|948||align=center| ||The first Emirs of Sicily, the [[Kalbids]], are appointed, establishing the [[Emirate of Sicily]]\n|-\n|align=center|947||||[[Liu Zhiyuan|Gaozu]] establishes the '''[[Later Han (Five Dynasties)|Later Han dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Kaifeng|Bianzhou]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|942||align=center| ||England re-takes the [[Five Boroughs of the Danelaw]]\n|-\n|align=center|941||align=center| ||J\u00f3rv\u00edk reoccupies the [[Five Boroughs of the Danelaw]] for the Danes\n|-\n|align=center|939||||[[Ng\u00f4 Quy\u1ec1n]] establishes the '''[[Ng\u00f4 dynasty]]''' in '''[[Vietnam]]'''. [[C\u1ed5 Loa Citadel|C\u1ed5 Loa]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|938||||Vietnam declares independence from the [[Southern Han]] of China. End of the [[Third Chinese domination of Vietnam]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|937||||[[Li Bian|Liezu]] establishes '''[[Southern Tang]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Nanjing|Jinling]] is the capital.\n|-\n||| [[Duan Siping|Taizu]] establishes '''[[Dali Kingdom|Dali]]''' in what is now Southwest China.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|936||||[[Shi Jingtang|Gaozu]] establishes the '''[[Later Jin (Five Dynasties)|Later Jin dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[Goryeo Dynasty]] unified the [[Later Three Kingdoms of Korea]].\n|-\n|align=center|934||||[[Meng Zhixiang|Gaozu]] establishes '''[[Later Shu]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Chengdu]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|927||align=center|12&nbsp;July||[[Athelstan of England|King Athelstan of Wessex]] establishes the '''[[Kingdom of England]]'''. [[Winchester]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|927||align=center| ||The [[Kingdom of Northumbria]] is conquered by Wessex, thus uniting all of the [[Anglo-Saxon kingdoms]] under one ruler and forming what would come to be known as the [[Kingdom of England]]\n|-\n|align=center|924||||[[Gao Jixing|Wuxin]] establishes '''[[Jingnan]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Jiangling County|Jingzhou]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|923||||[[Li Cunxu|Zhuangzong]] establishes the '''[[Later Tang|Later Tang dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Luoyang]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|922||align=center| ||The County of Aragon falls under the control of the Kingdom of Pamplona\n|-\n|align=center|920||align=center| ||The [[Seisyllwg|Kingdom of Seisyllwg]] unites with the [[Kingdom of Dyfed]] to form the [[Kingdom of Deheubarth]]\n|-\n|align=center|920||align=center| ||The [[County of Horne]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|918||||[[Taejo of Goryeo|King Taejo]] establishes '''[[Goryeo Dynasty]]''' on the [[Korean Peninsula]]. [[Kaesong|Gaegyeong]] is the official capital.\n|-\n|align=center|918||align=center| ||The [[Kingdom of East Anglia]] is conquered by Wessex\n|-\n|align=center|918||align=center| ||The [[Kingdom of Mercia]] is absorbed into Wessex\n|-\n|align=center|917||||[[Liu Yan (emperor)|Gaozu]] establishes '''[[Southern Han]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Guangzhou|Xingwang]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|916-917||align=center| ||Mercia and Wessex reconquer the [[Five Boroughs of the Danelaw]] from the Danes\n|-\n|align=center|916||||[[Abaoji|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Liao dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|910||align=center|10&nbsp;December||The Kingdom of Asturias moves its capital to Le\u00f3n and becomes the [[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|907||||[[Wang Shenzhi|Taizu]] establishes '''[[Min Kingdom|Min]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Fuzhou|Changle]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||The [[Fatimids]] take [[Raqqada]] from the [[Aghlabid]] Emirate of [[Ifriqiya]], establishing the [[Fatimid Caliphate]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|907||||[[Zhu Wen|Taizu]] establishes the '''[[Later Liang (Five Dynasties)|Later Liang dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Luoyang]] and [[Kaifeng]] are the capitals.\n|-\n|||[[Wang Jian (Former Shu)|Gaozu]] establishes '''[[Former Shu]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[Yang Wo|Liezu]] establishes '''[[Yang Wu]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[Ma Yin|Wumu]] establishes '''[[Ma Chu]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|||[[Qian Liu|Taizu]] establishes '''[[Wuyue]]''' in '''[[China]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|905||||The '''[[Kh\u00fac clan]]''' establishes ''de facto'' rule over '''[[Vietnam]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|902||align=center| ||The Byzantine city of [[Taormina]], [[Sicily]] falls to the Emirate of Ifriqiya\n|}\n\n===9th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:81%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|895||||[[\u00c1rp\u00e1d|Grand Prince \u00c1rp\u00e1d]] establishes the '''[[Principality of Hungary]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|891||||The Byzantine Empire conquers [[Principality of Benevento|Benevento]] and establishes the [[Theme (Byzantine district)|Theme]] of [[Longobardia]].\n|-\n|align=center|891||||[[Harald Fairhair]] unifies the [[Petty kingdoms of Norway]] and establishes the [[Norway|Kingdom of Norway]]. [[Stavanger]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|880's||||Byzantine control in southern Italy is extended over most of [[Apulia]] and [[Calabria]].\n|-\n|align=center|880||||[[File:De karolingska rikena \u00e5r 888.jpg|thumb|Frankish kingdoms in 888]] The Kings of West Francia cede their portion of Lotharingia to East Francia by the [[Treaty of Ribemont]].\n|-\n|align=center|878||||The Emirate of Ifriqiya takes [[Syracuse, Sicily]] from the Byzantine Empire.\n|-\n|align=center|876||||The Byzantine Empire re-conquers [[Bari]].\n|-\n|align=center|873||||The Byzantine Empire re-conquers [[Otranto]] from the Saracens.\n|-\n|align=center|872||||The [[Kingdom of Norway]] is unified.\n|-\n|align=center|870||||As a result of the [[Treaty of Meerssen]], Lotharingia is divided between East and West Francia, and Provence is divided between East Francia, West Francia and the Kingdom of Italy.\n|-\n|align=center|860||||[[\u00c6thelberht of Wessex|\u00c6thelberht]] succeeds his brother [[\u00c6thelbald of Wessex|\u00c6thelbald]] as king of [[Kingdom of Wessex|Wessex]], thus uniting it with Sussex and Kent.\n|-\n|align=center|858||||\u00c6thelberht is crowned king of [[Kingdom of Sussex|Sussex]] and [[Kingdom of Kent|Kent]].\n|-\n|align=center|855||||Middle Francia is partitioned into the [[Kingdom of Italy (Holy Roman Empire)|Kingdom of Italy]], [[Lotharingia]] and the [[Kingdom of Provence]] by the [[Treaty of Pr\u00fcm]].\n|-\n|align=center|851||||The [[Principality of Salerno]] is [[Partition (politics)|partitioned]] from the Principality of Benevento.\n|-\n|align=center|843||||[[File:Partage de l'Empire carolingien au Trait\u00e9 de Verdun en 843.JPG|thumb|Partitions of Francia by the Treaty of Verdun]] [[Charles the Bald]], grandson of Emperor [[Charlemagne]], made [[Paris]] the capital of the '''[[Kingdom of the West Franks]]''', established as the result of the [[Treaty of Verdun]].\n|-\n|align=center|843||||The [[Kingdom of Scotland]] ([[Kingdom of Alba]]) is unified.\n|-\n|align=center|843||||The [[Carolingian Empire]] ([[Francia]]) is partitioned into three by the [[Treaty of Verdun]], forming [[West Francia|West]], [[Middle Francia|Middle]] and [[East Francia]].\n|-\n|align=center|831||September||[[Palermo]], Sicily is captured by the [[Aghlabid]] Emirate of [[Ifriqiya]], is renamed al-Madinah, and becomes the capital of [[Emirate of Sicily|Muslim Sicily]].\n|-\n|align=center|825||||The [[Kingdom of Essex]] is ceded to [[Kingdom of Wessex|Wessex]].\n|-\n|align=center|825||||The [[Kingdom of Sussex]] becomes subject to Wessex.\n|-\n|align=center|824||||The [[Kingdom of Pamplona]] (later Navarre) is established.\n|-\n|align=center|820||||The title Count of Aragon is usurped and [[County of Aragon|Aragon]] ceases to be a vassal of the Franks.\n|-\n|align=center|814||||Cornwall loses its independence to Wessex, possibly becoming a sub-kingdom.\n|-\n|align=center|804||||[[Charlemagne]] establishes the '''[[Holy Roman Empire]]'''. While Rome is the official capital of the empire, [[Aix-la-Chapelle]] is the [[de facto]] capital.\n|-\n|align=center|800||||Saxony is integrated into the Frankish Kingdom as the [[Duchy of Saxony]].\n|}\n\n===8th century===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n|align=center|795||align=center| ||The [[Francia|Franks]] create the [[Marca Hispanica]] as a buffer against the Moors\n|-\n|align=center|788||align=center| ||The Franks conquer [[Duchy of Bavaria|Bavaria]]<ref>Atlas of World History. Harper Collins. 2001. p. 106</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|788||align=center| ||The Franks annex [[Chieti]] from the Principality of Benevento to the [[Duchy of Spoleto]]\n|-\n|align=center|787||align=center| ||Benevento submits to Frankish overlordship but retain effective autonomy\n|-\n|align=center|785||align=center| ||Franks defeat [[Widukind]] thereby conquering the remaining [[Frisian Kingdom|Frisian]] lands east of the [[Lauwers]] and vassalizing [[Old Saxony|Saxony]].\n|-\n|align=center|774||align=center| ||Franks conquer the [[Kingdom of the Lombards]] (Italy)\n|-\n|align=center|774||align=center| ||The Lombard [[Duchy of Benevento]] in the south of Italy effectively becomes independent and becomes the Principality of Benevento\n|-\n|align=center|769||align=center| ||Franks conquer [[Duchy of Vasconia|Gascony]]\n|-\n|align=center|768-769||align=center| ||Franks conquer [[Aquitane|Aquitania]]\n|-\n|align=center|759||align=center| ||Franks conquer [[Septimania]]\n|-\n|align=center|754||align=center| ||The [[Papal States]] is established\n|-\n|align=center|751||align=center| ||The [[Exarchate of Ravenna]], the center of Byzantine power in Italy, is disestablished after the [[Lombards]] invade\n|-\n|align=center|744||align=center| ||Franks conquer [[Alemannia]]\n|-\n|align=center|734||align=center| ||Franks annexed the Frisian lands between the [[Vlie]] and the Lauwers\n|-\n|align=center|718||align=center| ||[[Kingdom of Asturias]] established\n|-\n|align=center|717||align=center| ||[[C\u00f3rdoba, Andalusia|C\u00f3rdoba]] becomes the capital of Muslim [[Al-Andalus]].\n|-\n|align=center|711||align=center| ||A [[Berber people|Berber]] force under the Berber general [[Tariq ibn Ziyad]], loyal to the [[Emir of Damascus]], enters the [[Iberian peninsula]] from North [[Africa]], thus starting the foundation of [[Al-Andalus]].\n|-\n|align=center|705||||The '''[[Tang dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]''' is restored under [[Emperor Zhongzong of Tang|Zhongzong]].\n|}\n\n===7th century===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6%\"|Year||style=\"width:8%\"|Date||style=\"width:86%\"|Event\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|690||||[[Go of Balhae|King Go]] establishes '''[[Balhae]]''' in [[Manchuria]] and northern [[Korean Peninsula]].\n|-\n|||[[Wu Zetian|Wu Zhao]] establishes '''[[Zhou dynasty (690\u2013705)|Wu Zhou]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Luoyang|Shendu]] is the capital.\n|-\n|||Muslims conquer North Africa<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www