bus]] and makes the renamed [[City of David]] (now [[Jerusalem]]) the capital of the '''[[United Kingdom of Israel and Judah]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1046&nbsp;BCE||[[King Wu of Zhou|Wu]] establishes '''[[Zhou dynasty#Western Zhou|Western Zhou dynasty]]''' in '''[[China]]'''. [[Fenghao]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1047&nbsp;BCE||[[Saul|Shaul ben Qysh]] establishes the '''[[United Kingdom of Israel and Judah]]'''. [[Gibeah]] is the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1070&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]] [[Nesbanebdjed I]] establishes the '''[[Twenty-first Dynasty of Egypt]]'''. [[Tanis]] becomes the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1077&nbsp;BCE||The New Kingdom of Egypt collapses, beginning the [[Third Intermediate Period of Egypt]]\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1184&nbsp;BCE||[[Greeks]] destroy the city-state of '''[[Troy]]'''.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1188&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]] [[Setnakhte]] establishes the '''[[Twentieth Dynasty of Egypt]]'''. [[Pi-Ramesses Aa-nakhtu]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1230&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]] [[Ramesses II]] builds a new capital for the '''[[Nineteenth Dynasty of Egypt]]''' at the site of [[Avaris]] and names it [[Pi-Ramesses Aa-nakhtu]].\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |about&nbsp;1243&nbsp;BCE\n|[[Ashur-nadin-apli]] of the '''[[Middle Assyrian Empire]]''' moves capital back to [[Assur]].\n|-\n|[[Tukulti-Ninurta I]] of the '''[[Middle Assyrian Empire]]''' moves capital to [[Kar-Tukulti-Ninurta]].\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1272&nbsp;BCE||[[Mursili III]] of the '''[[Hittite empire]]''' moves capital back to [[Hattusa]].\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1293&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]] [[Ramesses I]] establishes the '''[[Nineteenth Dynasty of Egypt]]'''. [[Memphis, Egypt|Memphis]] remains the capital.\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1295&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]] [[Muwatalli II]] of the '''[[Hittite empire]]''' moves capital to [[Tarhuntassa]].\n|-\n|align=center|about&nbsp;1332&nbsp;BCE||[[Pharaoh]]